window.trendingPapers = {
    "today": [{"paper": {"id": "2604.17295", "authors": [{"_id": "69e86f245f6b3d4e5af9acf0", "user": {"_id": "681c9583406f0740a9b048f2", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/681c9583406f0740a9b048f2/k5IhHJxKCHdgVpAPFMsIO.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Yueyang Ding", "user": "November-Rain", "type": "user", "name": "November-Rain"}, "name": "Yueyang Ding", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-22T13:08:27.318Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e86f245f6b3d4e5af9acf1", "name": "HaoPeng Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e86f245f6b3d4e5af9acf2", "user": {"_id": "661de9defdbc9c247f159d15", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/38e21e78327cc908201122405c48f41b.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Rui Dai", "user": "DerryD", "type": "user", "name": "DerryD"}, "name": "Rui Dai", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-22T07:20:36.889Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e86f245f6b3d4e5af9acf3", "name": "Yi Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e86f245f6b3d4e5af9acf4", "name": "Tianyu Zong", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e86f245f6b3d4e5af9acf5", "name": "Kaikui Liu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e86f245f6b3d4e5af9acf6", "name": "Xiangxiang Chu", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/661de9defdbc9c247f159d15/_wTHxwk_UYcmJSRRPpJN5.mp4"], "publishedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-24T09:39:11.227Z", "title": "LLaTiSA: Towards Difficulty-Stratified Time Series Reasoning from Visual Perception to Semantics", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "661de9defdbc9c247f159d15", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/38e21e78327cc908201122405c48f41b.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Rui Dai", "user": "DerryD", "type": "user", "name": "DerryD"}, "summary": "Comprehensive understanding of time series remains a significant challenge for Large Language Models (LLMs). Current research is hindered by fragmented task definitions and benchmarks with inherent ambiguities, precluding rigorous evaluation and the development of unified Time Series Reasoning Models(TSRMs). To bridge this gap, we formalize Time Series Reasoning (TSR) via a four-level taxonomy of increasing cognitive complexity. We introduce HiTSR, a hierarchical time series reasoning dataset comprising 83k samples with diverse task combinations and verified Chain-of-Thought (CoT) trajectories. Leveraging HiTSR, we propose LLaTiSA, a strong TSRM that integrates visualized patterns with precision-calibrated numerical tables to enhance the temporal perception of Vision-Language Models (VLMs). Through a multi-stage curriculum fine-tuning strategy, LLaTiSA achieves superior performance and exhibits robust out-of-distribution generalization across diverse TSR tasks and real-world scenarios. Our code is available at https://github.com/RainingNovember/LLaTiSA.", "upvotes": 75, "discussionId": "69e86f255f6b3d4e5af9acf7", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/RainingNovember/LLaTiSA", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "A hierarchical time series reasoning dataset and model are introduced to improve LLM understanding of temporal data through visualized patterns and numerical tables.", "ai_keywords": ["Time Series Reasoning", "TSRM", "Chain-of-Thought", "Vision-Language Models", "multi-stage curriculum fine-tuning"], "githubStars": 70, "organization": {"_id": "67d11771890254196d3174e5", "name": "GD-ML", "fullname": "AMAP-ML", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/67d116c47be76de1a40873ca/s5ukAx9E36ZZIKvbpBRi4.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u5927\u8bed\u8a00\u6a21\u578b\uff08LLMs\uff09\u5728\u7406\u89e3\u65f6\u95f4\u5e8f\u5217\u65b9\u9762\u9762\u4e34\u6311\u6218\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u73b0\u6709\u7814\u7a76\u56e0\u4efb\u52a1\u5b9a\u4e49\u4e0d\u6e05\u6670\u548c\u57fa\u51c6\u6a21\u7cca\u800c\u53d7\u9650\uff0c\u96be\u4ee5\u8fdb\u884c\u4e25\u683c\u8bc4\u4f30\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86\u4e00\u4e2a\u56db\u7ea7\u5206\u7c7b\u6cd5\uff0c\u7cfb\u7edf\u5316\u65f6\u95f4\u5e8f\u5217\u63a8\u7406\uff08TSR\uff09\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u63a8\u51fa\u4e86HiTSR\u6570\u636e\u96c6\uff0c\u5305\u542b83,000\u4e2a\u6837\u672c\uff0c\u5177\u6709\u591a\u6837\u7684\u4efb\u52a1\u7ec4\u5408\u548c\u9a8c\u8bc1\u7684\u601d\u7ef4\u94fe\u8f68\u8ff9\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u63d0\u51fa\u7684LLaTiSA\u6a21\u578b\u901a\u8fc7\u591a\u9636\u6bb5\u5fae\u8c03\u7b56\u7565\uff0c\u5728\u65f6\u95f4\u5e8f\u5217\u4efb\u52a1\u4e2d\u8868\u73b0\u51fa\u8272\uff0c\u5e76\u5177\u6709\u826f\u597d\u7684\u6cdb\u5316\u80fd\u529b\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Understanding time series is difficult for Large Language Models (LLMs) due to unclear task definitions and benchmarks.</li>\n    <li>We created a structured approach to Time Series Reasoning (TSR) with a four-level complexity taxonomy.</li>\n    <li>HiTSR is a new dataset with 83,000 samples that includes various tasks and validated reasoning paths.</li>\n    <li>LLaTiSA is a new model that combines visual patterns with accurate numerical data to improve time perception in models that understand both text and images.</li>\n    <li>LLaTiSA shows excellent performance and can adapt well to different tasks and real-world situations through a special training method.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-18T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "LLaTiSA: Towards Difficulty-Stratified Time Series Reasoning from Visual Perception to Semantics", "summary": "Comprehensive understanding of time series remains a significant challenge for Large Language Models (LLMs). Current research is hindered by fragmented task definitions and benchmarks with inherent ambiguities, precluding rigorous evaluation and the development of unified Time Series Reasoning Models(TSRMs). To bridge this gap, we formalize Time Series Reasoning (TSR) via a four-level taxonomy of increasing cognitive complexity. We introduce HiTSR, a hierarchical time series reasoning dataset comprising 83k samples with diverse task combinations and verified Chain-of-Thought (CoT) trajectories. Leveraging HiTSR, we propose LLaTiSA, a strong TSRM that integrates visualized patterns with precision-calibrated numerical tables to enhance the temporal perception of Vision-Language Models (VLMs). Through a multi-stage curriculum fine-tuning strategy, LLaTiSA achieves superior performance and exhibits robust out-of-distribution generalization across diverse TSR tasks and real-world scenarios. Our code is available at https://github.com/RainingNovember/LLaTiSA.", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/661de9defdbc9c247f159d15/_wTHxwk_UYcmJSRRPpJN5.mp4"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.17295.png", "numComments": 2, "submittedBy": {"_id": "661de9defdbc9c247f159d15", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/38e21e78327cc908201122405c48f41b.svg", "fullname": "Rui Dai", "name": "DerryD", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "67d11771890254196d3174e5", "name": "GD-ML", "fullname": "AMAP-ML", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/67d116c47be76de1a40873ca/s5ukAx9E36ZZIKvbpBRi4.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": true}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.21686", "authors": [{"_id": "69ead5b3a961c3f1b5f40d4d", "name": "Xiaojie Xu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead5b3a961c3f1b5f40d4e", "name": "Zhengyuan Lin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead5b3a961c3f1b5f40d4f", "name": "Kang He", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead5b3a961c3f1b5f40d50", "name": "Yukang Feng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead5b3a961c3f1b5f40d51", "name": "Xiaofeng Mao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead5b3a961c3f1b5f40d52", "name": "Yuanyang Yin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead5b3a961c3f1b5f40d53", "user": {"_id": "65f1713552c38a91e0a445e8", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/47ab3ada51c9b9976ac1cd0c4301c373.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "kaipeng", "user": "kpzhang996", "type": "user", "name": "kpzhang996"}, "name": "Kaipeng Zhang", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-24T13:57:05.891Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead5b3a961c3f1b5f40d54", "name": "Yongtao Ge", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/Y9Ba5_xSZMv-1XkrGcS1p.mp4"], "publishedAt": "2026-04-23T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-24T01:00:30.127Z", "title": "WorldMark: A Unified Benchmark Suite for Interactive Video World Models", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "taesiri", "user": "taesiri", "type": "user", "name": "taesiri"}, "summary": "Interactive video generation models such as Genie, YUME, HY-World, and Matrix-Game are advancing rapidly, yet every model is evaluated on its own benchmark with private scenes and trajectories, making fair cross-model comparison impossible. Existing public benchmarks offer useful metrics such as trajectory error, aesthetic scores, and VLM-based judgments, but none supplies the standardized test conditions -- identical scenes, identical action sequences, and a unified control interface -- needed to make those metrics comparable across models with heterogeneous inputs. We introduce WorldMark, the first benchmark that provides such a common playing field for interactive Image-to-Video world models. WorldMark contributes: (1) a unified action-mapping layer that translates a shared WASD-style action vocabulary into each model's native control format, enabling apples-to-apples comparison across six major models on identical scenes and trajectories; (2) a hierarchical test suite of 500 evaluation cases covering first- and third-person viewpoints, photorealistic and stylized scenes, and three difficulty tiers from Easy to Hard spanning 20-60s; and (3) a modular evaluation toolkit for Visual Quality, Control Alignment, and World Consistency, designed so that researchers can reuse our standardized inputs while plugging in their own metrics as the field evolves. We will release all data, evaluation code, and model outputs to facilitate future research. Beyond offline metrics, we launch World Model Arena (warena.ai), an online platform where anyone can pit leading world models against each other in side-by-side battles and watch the live leaderboard.", "upvotes": 29, "discussionId": "69ead5b3a961c3f1b5f40d55", "projectPage": "https://alaya-studio.github.io/WorldMark/", "ai_summary": "WorldMark establishes a standardized benchmark for evaluating interactive video generation models with unified controls, identical scenarios, and comprehensive evaluation metrics across multiple model architectures.", "ai_keywords": ["interactive video generation models", "world models", "action-mapping layer", "unified control interface", "hierarchical test suite", "visual quality", "control alignment", "world consistency", "evaluation toolkit", "live leaderboard"], "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>WorldMark\u662f\u7b2c\u4e00\u4e2a\u4e3a\u4e92\u52a8\u89c6\u9891\u751f\u6210\u6a21\u578b\u63d0\u4f9b\u7edf\u4e00\u57fa\u51c6\u7684\u5de5\u5177\uff0c\u5141\u8bb8\u516c\u5e73\u6bd4\u8f83\u4e0d\u540c\u6a21\u578b\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5b83\u5305\u62ec\u4e00\u4e2a\u7edf\u4e00\u7684\u52a8\u4f5c\u6620\u5c04\u5c42\uff0c\u4f7f\u5f97\u4e0d\u540c\u6a21\u578b\u53ef\u4ee5\u5728\u76f8\u540c\u573a\u666f\u548c\u8f68\u8ff9\u4e0b\u8fdb\u884c\u6bd4\u8f83\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u63d0\u4f9b\u4e86500\u4e2a\u6d4b\u8bd5\u6848\u4f8b\uff0c\u6db5\u76d6\u4e0d\u540c\u89c6\u89d2\u3001\u573a\u666f\u98ce\u683c\u548c\u96be\u5ea6\u7b49\u7ea7\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5305\u542b\u53ef\u91cd\u7528\u7684\u8bc4\u4f30\u5de5\u5177\uff0c\u652f\u6301\u89c6\u89c9\u8d28\u91cf\u3001\u63a7\u5236\u4e00\u81f4\u6027\u548c\u4e16\u754c\u4e00\u81f4\u6027\u8bc4\u4f30\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u63a8\u51fa\u4e86World Model Arena\uff08warena.ai\uff09\u5e73\u53f0\uff0c\u8ba9\u7528\u6237\u53ef\u4ee5\u5b9e\u65f6\u6bd4\u8f83\u4e0d\u540c\u6a21\u578b\u7684\u8868\u73b0\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>WorldMark is a new benchmark for comparing interactive video generation models like Genie and YUME fairly.</li>\n    <li>It provides a common testing environment with the same scenes and action sequences for all models.</li>\n    <li>WorldMark includes a system that translates actions from a standard format to each model's controls, allowing direct comparisons.</li>\n    <li>It features 500 test cases with various viewpoints and difficulties to evaluate the models thoroughly.</li>\n    <li>World Model Arena is an online platform where users can compare models in real-time and see live rankings.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-22T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "WorldMark: A Unified Benchmark Suite for Interactive Video World Models", "summary": "Interactive video generation models such as Genie, YUME, HY-World, and Matrix-Game are advancing rapidly, yet every model is evaluated on its own benchmark with private scenes and trajectories, making fair cross-model comparison impossible. Existing public benchmarks offer useful metrics such as trajectory error, aesthetic scores, and VLM-based judgments, but none supplies the standardized test conditions -- identical scenes, identical action sequences, and a unified control interface -- needed to make those metrics comparable across models with heterogeneous inputs. We introduce WorldMark, the first benchmark that provides such a common playing field for interactive Image-to-Video world models. WorldMark contributes: (1) a unified action-mapping layer that translates a shared WASD-style action vocabulary into each model's native control format, enabling apples-to-apples comparison across six major models on identical scenes and trajectories; (2) a hierarchical test suite of 500 evaluation cases covering first- and third-person viewpoints, photorealistic and stylized scenes, and three difficulty tiers from Easy to Hard spanning 20-60s; and (3) a modular evaluation toolkit for Visual Quality, Control Alignment, and World Consistency, designed so that researchers can reuse our standardized inputs while plugging in their own metrics as the field evolves. We will release all data, evaluation code, and model outputs to facilitate future research. Beyond offline metrics, we launch World Model Arena (warena.ai), an online platform where anyone can pit leading world models against each other in side-by-side battles and watch the live leaderboard.", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/Y9Ba5_xSZMv-1XkrGcS1p.mp4"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.21686.png", "numComments": 1, "submittedBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "fullname": "taesiri", "name": "taesiri", "type": "user", "isPro": true, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 280, "isUserFollowing": false}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.19734", "authors": [{"_id": "69ea5363a961c3f1b5f40be4", "name": "Boyu Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ea5363a961c3f1b5f40be5", "name": "Yi Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ea5363a961c3f1b5f40be6", "name": "Lu Qiu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ea5363a961c3f1b5f40be7", "name": "Jerry Bai", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ea5363a961c3f1b5f40be8", "name": "Yuying Ge", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ea5363a961c3f1b5f40be9", "name": "Yixiao Ge", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/60d045c4778bafd0fbcfa3f5/aLHNTvySjchHnca61-M-l.jpeg"], "publishedAt": "2026-04-21T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-24T00:53:51.931Z", "title": "UniT: Toward a Unified Physical Language for Human-to-Humanoid Policy Learning and World Modeling", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "60d045c4778bafd0fbcfa3f5", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/0cc0c2739c1934430ea09df7e9668c80.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Yi Chen", "user": "ChenYi99", "type": "user", "name": "ChenYi99"}, "summary": "Scaling humanoid foundation models is bottlenecked by the scarcity of robotic data. While massive egocentric human data offers a scalable alternative, bridging the cross-embodiment chasm remains a fundamental challenge due to kinematic mismatches. We introduce UniT (Unified Latent Action Tokenizer via Visual Anchoring), a framework that establishes a unified physical language for human-to-humanoid transfer. Grounded in the philosophy that heterogeneous kinematics share universal visual consequences, UniT employs a tri-branch cross-reconstruction mechanism: actions predict vision to anchor kinematics to physical outcomes, while vision reconstructs actions to filter out irrelevant visual confounders. Concurrently, a fusion branch synergies these purified modalities into a shared discrete latent space of embodiment-agnostic physical intents. We validate UniT across two paradigms: 1) Policy Learning (VLA-UniT): By predicting these unified tokens, it effectively leverages diverse human data to achieve state-of-the-art data efficiency and robust out-of-distribution (OOD) generalization on both humanoid simulation benchmark and real-world deployments, notably demonstrating zero-shot task transfer. 2) World Modeling (WM-UniT): By aligning cross-embodiment dynamics via unified tokens as conditions, it realizes direct human-to-humanoid action transfer. This alignment ensures that human data seamlessly translates into enhanced action controllability for humanoid video generation. Ultimately, by inducing a highly aligned cross-embodiment representation (empirically verified by t-SNE visualizations revealing the convergence of human and humanoid features into a shared manifold), UniT offers a scalable path to distill vast human knowledge into general-purpose humanoid capabilities.", "upvotes": 25, "discussionId": "69ea5364a961c3f1b5f40bea", "projectPage": "https://xpeng-robotics.github.io/unit/", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/xpeng-robotics/UniT", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "UniT enables human-to-humanoid transfer by creating a unified visual-language representation that bridges kinematic differences through cross-reconstruction mechanisms and shared latent spaces.", "ai_keywords": ["UniT", "unified latent action tokenizer", "visual anchoring", "tri-branch cross-reconstruction mechanism", "fusion branch", "discrete latent space", "embodiment-agnostic physical intents", "policy learning", "world modeling", "cross-embodiment dynamics", "t-SNE visualization"], "githubStars": 32, "organization": {"_id": "69c9fb20951b511f5c41dd0d", "name": "xpeng-robotics", "fullname": "xpeng-robotics", "avatar": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b3437743db998befe15fce93ec62355f?d=retro&size=100"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>UniT \u662f\u4e00\u79cd\u65b0\u6846\u67b6\uff0c\u65e8\u5728\u89e3\u51b3\u4eba\u7c7b\u548c\u7c7b\u4eba\u673a\u5668\u4eba\u4e4b\u95f4\u7684\u6570\u636e\u5dee\u5f02\u95ee\u9898\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u901a\u8fc7\u7edf\u4e00\u7684\u7269\u7406\u8bed\u8a00\uff0cUniT \u80fd\u591f\u66f4\u597d\u5730\u5c06\u4eba\u7c7b\u7684\u52a8\u4f5c\u8f6c\u79fb\u5230\u7c7b\u4eba\u673a\u5668\u4eba\u4e0a\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8be5\u6846\u67b6\u4f7f\u7528\u4e09\u652f\u5206\u652f\u673a\u5236\u6765\u540c\u65f6\u9884\u6d4b\u89c6\u89c9\u548c\u52a8\u4f5c\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u63d0\u9ad8\u6570\u636e\u6548\u7387\u548c\u9002\u5e94\u6027\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5728\u4e24\u4e2a\u5e94\u7528\u573a\u666f\u4e2d\u9a8c\u8bc1\u4e86 UniT \u7684\u6709\u6548\u6027\uff1a\u653f\u7b56\u5b66\u4e60\u548c\u4e16\u754c\u5efa\u6a21\uff0c\u5c55\u793a\u4e86\u5176\u5728\u7c7b\u4eba\u673a\u5668\u4eba\u6a21\u62df\u548c\u5b9e\u9645\u5e94\u7528\u4e2d\u7684\u4f18\u8d8a\u6027\u80fd\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6700\u7ec8\uff0cUniT \u63d0\u4f9b\u4e86\u4e00\u79cd\u53ef\u6269\u5c55\u7684\u65b9\u6cd5\uff0c\u5c06\u5927\u91cf\u4eba\u7c7b\u77e5\u8bc6\u8f6c\u5316\u4e3a\u7c7b\u4eba\u673a\u5668\u4eba\u7684\u901a\u7528\u80fd\u529b\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>UniT is a new framework designed to help transfer knowledge from humans to humanoid robots, addressing the issue of limited robotic data.</li>\n    <li>It works by creating a shared language for actions and visual outcomes, linking human movements to robotic actions.</li>\n    <li>UniT uses a unique approach that combines three methods to improve the understanding and transfer of actions between humans and humanoid robots.</li>\n    <li>It has been tested in two ways: improving learning efficiency in simulations and enabling direct transfer of actions from humans to humanoids for better video generation.</li>\n    <li>UniT shows promise for making humanoid robots more capable by effectively using large amounts of human data.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-20T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "UniT: Toward a Unified Physical Language for Human-to-Humanoid Policy Learning and World Modeling", "summary": "Scaling humanoid foundation models is bottlenecked by the scarcity of robotic data. While massive egocentric human data offers a scalable alternative, bridging the cross-embodiment chasm remains a fundamental challenge due to kinematic mismatches. We introduce UniT (Unified Latent Action Tokenizer via Visual Anchoring), a framework that establishes a unified physical language for human-to-humanoid transfer. Grounded in the philosophy that heterogeneous kinematics share universal visual consequences, UniT employs a tri-branch cross-reconstruction mechanism: actions predict vision to anchor kinematics to physical outcomes, while vision reconstructs actions to filter out irrelevant visual confounders. Concurrently, a fusion branch synergies these purified modalities into a shared discrete latent space of embodiment-agnostic physical intents. We validate UniT across two paradigms: 1) Policy Learning (VLA-UniT): By predicting these unified tokens, it effectively leverages diverse human data to achieve state-of-the-art data efficiency and robust out-of-distribution (OOD) generalization on both humanoid simulation benchmark and real-world deployments, notably demonstrating zero-shot task transfer. 2) World Modeling (WM-UniT): By aligning cross-embodiment dynamics via unified tokens as conditions, it realizes direct human-to-humanoid action transfer. This alignment ensures that human data seamlessly translates into enhanced action controllability for humanoid video generation. Ultimately, by inducing a highly aligned cross-embodiment representation (empirically verified by t-SNE visualizations revealing the convergence of human and humanoid features into a shared manifold), UniT offers a scalable path to distill vast human knowledge into general-purpose humanoid capabilities.", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/60d045c4778bafd0fbcfa3f5/aLHNTvySjchHnca61-M-l.jpeg"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.19734.png", "numComments": 2, "submittedBy": {"_id": "60d045c4778bafd0fbcfa3f5", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/0cc0c2739c1934430ea09df7e9668c80.svg", "fullname": "Yi Chen", "name": "ChenYi99", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 7, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "69c9fb20951b511f5c41dd0d", "name": "xpeng-robotics", "fullname": "xpeng-robotics", "avatar": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b3437743db998befe15fce93ec62355f?d=retro&size=100"}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.21689", "authors": [{"_id": "69ead908a961c3f1b5f40d66", "name": "Kwan Yun", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead908a961c3f1b5f40d67", "name": "Changmin Lee", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead908a961c3f1b5f40d68", "name": "Ayeong Jeong", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead908a961c3f1b5f40d69", "name": "Youngseo Kim", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead908a961c3f1b5f40d6a", "name": "Seungmi Lee", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead908a961c3f1b5f40d6b", "name": "Junyong Noh", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/639d445524af4747d8d2af52/ixnWIkjEuKtAqnWhbZhPW.png"], "publishedAt": "2026-04-23T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-24T01:16:16.073Z", "title": "StyleID: A Perception-Aware Dataset and Metric for Stylization-Agnostic Facial Identity Recognition", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "639d445524af4747d8d2af52", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/6ca870edc993fd3db6b0db4e4848ef7a.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "kwan yun", "user": "kwanY", "type": "user", "name": "kwanY"}, "summary": "Creative face stylization aims to render portraits in diverse visual idioms such as cartoons, sketches, and paintings while retaining recognizable identity. However, current identity encoders, which are typically trained and calibrated on natural photographs, exhibit severe brittleness under stylization. They often mistake changes in texture or color palette for identity drift or fail to detect geometric exaggerations. This reveals the lack of a style-agnostic framework to evaluate and supervise identity consistency across varying styles and strengths. To address this gap, we introduce StyleID, a human perception-aware dataset and evaluation framework for facial identity under stylization. StyleID comprises two datasets: (i) StyleBench-H, a benchmark that captures human same-different verification judgments across diffusion- and flow-matching-based stylization at multiple style strengths, and (ii) StyleBench-S, a supervision set derived from psychometric recognition-strength curves obtained through controlled two-alternative forced-choice (2AFC) experiments. Leveraging StyleBench-S, we fine-tune existing semantic encoders to align their similarity orderings with human perception across styles and strengths. Experiments demonstrate that our calibrated models yield significantly higher correlation with human judgments and enhanced robustness for out-of-domain, artist drawn portraits. All of our datasets, code, and pretrained models are publicly available at https://kwanyun.github.io/StyleID_page/", "upvotes": 18, "discussionId": "69ead908a961c3f1b5f40d6c", "projectPage": "https://kwanyun.github.io/StyleID_page/", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/kwanyun/StyleID", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "StyleID presents a human perception-aware dataset and evaluation framework for facial identity preservation under stylization, featuring two datasets derived from psychometric experiments and calibrated semantic encoders that improve correlation with human judgments.", "ai_keywords": ["style-agnostic framework", "identity encoders", "stylization", "diffusion models", "flow-matching-based stylization", "psychometric recognition-strength curves", "two-alternative forced-choice (2AFC) experiments", "semantic encoders", "human perception-aware dataset", "StyleBench-H", "StyleBench-S"], "githubStars": 16, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u521b\u610f\u9762\u90e8\u98ce\u683c\u5316\u65e8\u5728\u5c06\u8096\u50cf\u5448\u73b0\u4e3a\u591a\u79cd\u89c6\u89c9\u98ce\u683c\uff0c\u5982\u5361\u901a\u3001\u7d20\u63cf\u548c\u7ed8\u753b\uff0c\u540c\u65f6\u4fdd\u6301\u53ef\u8bc6\u522b\u7684\u8eab\u4efd\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5f53\u524d\u7684\u8eab\u4efd\u7f16\u7801\u5668\u5728\u98ce\u683c\u5316\u65f6\u8868\u73b0\u8106\u5f31\uff0c\u5e38\u5e38\u5c06\u7eb9\u7406\u6216\u8272\u5f69\u7684\u53d8\u5316\u8bef\u8ba4\u4e3a\u8eab\u4efd\u6f02\u79fb\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u4e3a\u4e86\u89e3\u51b3\u8fd9\u4e00\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u6211\u4eec\u63a8\u51fa\u4e86StyleID\uff0c\u8fd9\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u5173\u6ce8\u4eba\u7c7b\u611f\u77e5\u7684\u9762\u90e8\u8eab\u4efd\u8bc4\u4f30\u6846\u67b6\u3002</li>\n    <li>StyleID\u5305\u542b\u4e24\u4e2a\u6570\u636e\u96c6\uff1aStyleBench-H\u7528\u4e8e\u9a8c\u8bc1\u4eba\u7c7b\u7684\u76f8\u540c\u4e0d\u540c\u5224\u65ad\uff0cStyleBench-S\u7528\u4e8e\u76d1\u7763\u6a21\u578b\u7684\u8bad\u7ec3\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5b9e\u9a8c\u8868\u660e\uff0c\u7ecf\u8fc7\u8c03\u6574\u7684\u6a21\u578b\u4e0e\u4eba\u7c7b\u5224\u65ad\u7684\u76f8\u5173\u6027\u663e\u8457\u63d0\u9ad8\uff0c\u5e76\u4e14\u5728\u827a\u672f\u5bb6\u7ed8\u5236\u7684\u8096\u50cf\u4e0a\u8868\u73b0\u51fa\u66f4\u5f3a\u7684\u9c81\u68d2\u6027\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Creative face stylization transforms portraits into various art styles while keeping the person's identity clear.</li>\n    <li>Current identity detection methods struggle with stylization changes, leading to errors in recognizing faces.</li>\n    <li>StyleID is a new dataset and evaluation tool designed to assess identity consistency across different styles.</li>\n    <li>It includes two parts: StyleBench-H, which tests how well humans can recognize faces in stylized images, and StyleBench-S, which helps improve identity detection models.</li>\n    <li>Tests show that the improved models better match human recognition and work well with artist-drawn portraits.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-22T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "StyleID: A Perception-Aware Dataset and Metric for Stylization-Agnostic Facial Identity Recognition", "summary": "Creative face stylization aims to render portraits in diverse visual idioms such as cartoons, sketches, and paintings while retaining recognizable identity. However, current identity encoders, which are typically trained and calibrated on natural photographs, exhibit severe brittleness under stylization. They often mistake changes in texture or color palette for identity drift or fail to detect geometric exaggerations. This reveals the lack of a style-agnostic framework to evaluate and supervise identity consistency across varying styles and strengths. To address this gap, we introduce StyleID, a human perception-aware dataset and evaluation framework for facial identity under stylization. StyleID comprises two datasets: (i) StyleBench-H, a benchmark that captures human same-different verification judgments across diffusion- and flow-matching-based stylization at multiple style strengths, and (ii) StyleBench-S, a supervision set derived from psychometric recognition-strength curves obtained through controlled two-alternative forced-choice (2AFC) experiments. Leveraging StyleBench-S, we fine-tune existing semantic encoders to align their similarity orderings with human perception across styles and strengths. Experiments demonstrate that our calibrated models yield significantly higher correlation with human judgments and enhanced robustness for out-of-domain, artist drawn portraits. All of our datasets, code, and pretrained models are publicly available at https://kwanyun.github.io/StyleID_page/", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/639d445524af4747d8d2af52/ixnWIkjEuKtAqnWhbZhPW.png"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.21689.png", "numComments": 2, "submittedBy": {"_id": "639d445524af4747d8d2af52", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/6ca870edc993fd3db6b0db4e4848ef7a.svg", "fullname": "kwan yun", "name": "kwanY", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "isUserFollowing": false}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.20987", "authors": [{"_id": "69eaebb2a961c3f1b5f40df5", "name": "Xiyang Wu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eaebb2a961c3f1b5f40df6", "name": "Zongxia Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eaebb2a961c3f1b5f40df7", "name": "Guangyao Shi", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eaebb2a961c3f1b5f40df8", "name": "Alexander Duffy", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eaebb2a961c3f1b5f40df9", "name": "Tyler Marques", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eaebb2a961c3f1b5f40dfa", "name": "Matthew Lyle Olson", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eaebb2a961c3f1b5f40dfb", "name": "Tianyi Zhou", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eaebb2a961c3f1b5f40dfc", "name": "Dinesh Manocha", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-22T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-24T02:38:50.802Z", "title": "Co-Evolving LLM Decision and Skill Bank Agents for Long-Horizon Tasks", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "64ea62f918d79efd533c93fe", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/9985a789ce11b788de2cba12adfb72fc.svg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "Xiyang Wu", "user": "wuxiyang", "type": "user", "name": "wuxiyang"}, "summary": "Long horizon interactive environments are a testbed for evaluating agents skill usage abilities. These environments demand multi step reasoning, the chaining of multiple skills over many timesteps, and robust decision making under delayed rewards and partial observability. Games are a good testbed for evaluating agent skill usage in environments. Large Language Models (LLMs) offer a promising alternative as game playing agents, but they often struggle with consistent long horizon decision making because they lack a mechanism to discover, retain, and reuse structured skills across episodes. We present COSPLAY, a co evolution framework in which an LLM decision agent retrieves skills from a learnable skill bank to guide action taking, while an agent managed skill pipeline discovers reusable skills from the agents unlabeled rollouts to form a skill bank. Our framework improves both the decision agent to learn better skill retrieval and action generation, while the skill bank agent continually extracts, refines, and updates skills together with their contracts. Experiments across six game environments show that COSPLAY with an 8B base model achieves over 25.1 percent average reward improvement against four frontier LLM baselines on single player game benchmarks while remaining competitive on multi player social reasoning games.", "upvotes": 14, "discussionId": "69eaebb2a961c3f1b5f40dfd", "projectPage": "https://wuxiyang1996.github.io/COSPLAY_page/", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/wuxiyang1996/cos-play", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "A co-evolution framework enables large language models to discover, retain, and reuse structured skills across episodes in long-horizon interactive environments through a learnable skill bank and skill pipeline.", "ai_keywords": ["large language models", "skill bank", "co-evolution framework", "skill retrieval", "action generation", "skill discovery", "skill refinement", "delayed rewards", "partial observability", "multi-step reasoning", "skill chaining"], "githubStars": 6, "organization": {"_id": "68f6c59c5891a5ab9b841dbb", "name": "GoodStartLabs", "fullname": "Good Start Labs", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/646535720e6c7618f6138daa/3asR3UpjTBqvY1wgnPBcE.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u957f\u65f6\u95f4\u7684\u4e92\u52a8\u73af\u5883\u53ef\u4ee5\u7528\u6765\u8bc4\u4f30\u667a\u80fd\u4f53\u7684\u6280\u80fd\u4f7f\u7528\u80fd\u529b\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8fd9\u4e9b\u73af\u5883\u9700\u8981\u591a\u6b65\u63a8\u7406\u548c\u5728\u8bb8\u591a\u65f6\u95f4\u6b65\u4e2d\u94fe\u5f0f\u4f7f\u7528\u591a\u4e2a\u6280\u80fd\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5927\u578b\u8bed\u8a00\u6a21\u578b\uff08LLMs\uff09\u4f5c\u4e3a\u6e38\u620f\u4ee3\u7406\u6709\u6f5c\u529b\uff0c\u4f46\u5728\u957f\u671f\u51b3\u7b56\u65b9\u9762\u8868\u73b0\u4e0d\u7a33\u5b9a\u3002</li>\n    <li>COSPLAY\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u5171\u540c\u8fdb\u5316\u6846\u67b6\uff0c\u901a\u8fc7\u53ef\u5b66\u4e60\u7684\u6280\u80fd\u5e93\u5e2e\u52a9LLM\u667a\u80fd\u4f53\u68c0\u7d22\u6280\u80fd\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5b9e\u9a8c\u8868\u660e\uff0cCOSPLAY\u5728\u5355\u4eba\u6e38\u620f\u57fa\u51c6\u6d4b\u8bd5\u4e2d\u63d0\u5347\u4e8625.1%\u7684\u5e73\u5747\u5956\u52b1\uff0c\u4e0e\u591a\u73a9\u5bb6\u793e\u4ea4\u63a8\u7406\u6e38\u620f\u4e2d\u4e5f\u4fdd\u6301\u7ade\u4e89\u529b\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Long horizon interactive environments test how well agents can use skills over time.</li>\n    <li>Games are useful for evaluating how agents make decisions and use multiple skills together.</li>\n    <li>Large Language Models (LLMs) struggle with long-term decision making because they don't easily find and reuse skills.</li>\n    <li>COSPLAY is a new framework that helps LLMs improve their skill retrieval and decision-making by using a skill bank.</li>\n    <li>Testing shows that COSPLAY significantly improves performance in single-player games and remains competitive in multiplayer games.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-21T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "Co-Evolving LLM Decision and Skill Bank Agents for Long-Horizon Tasks", "summary": "Long horizon interactive environments are a testbed for evaluating agents skill usage abilities. These environments demand multi step reasoning, the chaining of multiple skills over many timesteps, and robust decision making under delayed rewards and partial observability. Games are a good testbed for evaluating agent skill usage in environments. Large Language Models (LLMs) offer a promising alternative as game playing agents, but they often struggle with consistent long horizon decision making because they lack a mechanism to discover, retain, and reuse structured skills across episodes. We present COSPLAY, a co evolution framework in which an LLM decision agent retrieves skills from a learnable skill bank to guide action taking, while an agent managed skill pipeline discovers reusable skills from the agents unlabeled rollouts to form a skill bank. Our framework improves both the decision agent to learn better skill retrieval and action generation, while the skill bank agent continually extracts, refines, and updates skills together with their contracts. Experiments across six game environments show that COSPLAY with an 8B base model achieves over 25.1 percent average reward improvement against four frontier LLM baselines on single player game benchmarks while remaining competitive on multi player social reasoning games.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.20987.png", "numComments": 1, "submittedBy": {"_id": "64ea62f918d79efd533c93fe", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/9985a789ce11b788de2cba12adfb72fc.svg", "fullname": "Xiyang Wu", "name": "wuxiyang", "type": "user", "isPro": true, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "68f6c59c5891a5ab9b841dbb", "name": "GoodStartLabs", "fullname": "Good Start Labs", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/646535720e6c7618f6138daa/3asR3UpjTBqvY1wgnPBcE.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.21931", "authors": [{"_id": "69ead309a961c3f1b5f40d27", "name": "Yen-Siang Wu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead309a961c3f1b5f40d28", "name": "Rundong Luo", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead309a961c3f1b5f40d29", "name": "Jingsen Zhu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead309a961c3f1b5f40d2a", "name": "Tao Tu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead309a961c3f1b5f40d2b", "name": "Ali Farhadi", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead309a961c3f1b5f40d2c", "name": "Matthew Wallingford", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead309a961c3f1b5f40d2d", "name": "Yu-Chiang Frank Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead309a961c3f1b5f40d2e", "name": "Steve Marschner", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead309a961c3f1b5f40d2f", "name": "Wei-Chiu Ma", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/DWHZnjLwXGiDhsthpZWKL.mp4"], "publishedAt": "2026-04-23T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-24T00:48:58.642Z", "title": "Seeing Fast and Slow: Learning the Flow of Time in Videos", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "taesiri", "user": "taesiri", "type": "user", "name": "taesiri"}, "summary": "How can we tell whether a video has been sped up or slowed down? How can we generate videos at different speeds? Although videos have been central to modern computer vision research, little attention has been paid to perceiving and controlling the passage of time. In this paper, we study time as a learnable visual concept and develop models for reasoning about and manipulating the flow of time in videos. We first exploit the multimodal cues and temporal structure naturally present in videos to learn, in a self-supervised manner, to detect speed changes and estimate playback speed. We then show that these learned temporal reasoning models enable us to curate the largest slow-motion video dataset to date from noisy in-the-wild sources. Such slow-motion footage, typically filmed by high-speed cameras, contains substantially richer temporal detail than standard videos. Using this data, we further develop models capable of temporal control, including speed-conditioned video generation, which produces motion at specified playback speed, and temporal super-resolution, which tranforms low-FPS, blurry videos into high-FPS sequences with fine-grained temporal details. Our findings highlight time as a manipulable, perceptual dimension in video learning, opening doors to temporally controllable video generation, temporal forensics detection, and potentially richer world-models that understand how events unfold over time.", "upvotes": 13, "discussionId": "69ead309a961c3f1b5f40d30", "projectPage": "https://seeing-fast-and-slow.github.io/", "ai_summary": "Video speed manipulation and perception models are developed through self-supervised temporal reasoning, enabling speed detection, slow-motion video generation, and temporal super-resolution from in-the-wild sources.", "ai_keywords": ["temporal reasoning", "self-supervised learning", "speed detection", "playback speed estimation", "temporal control", "video generation", "temporal super-resolution", "slow-motion video dataset", "high-speed cameras", "temporal forensics"], "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u7814\u7a76\u89c6\u9891\u7684\u901f\u5ea6\u53d8\u5316\uff0c\u5982\u4f55\u5224\u65ad\u89c6\u9891\u662f\u52a0\u901f\u8fd8\u662f\u51cf\u901f\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5efa\u7acb\u6a21\u578b\u6765\u7406\u89e3\u548c\u64cd\u63a7\u89c6\u9891\u4e2d\u7684\u65f6\u95f4\u6d41\u52a8\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5229\u7528\u89c6\u9891\u4e2d\u7684\u591a\u79cd\u7ebf\u7d22\uff0c\u81ea\u6211\u5b66\u4e60\u68c0\u6d4b\u901f\u5ea6\u53d8\u5316\u5e76\u4f30\u8ba1\u64ad\u653e\u901f\u5ea6\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u521b\u5efa\u4e86\u6700\u5927\u7684\u6162\u52a8\u4f5c\u89c6\u9891\u6570\u636e\u96c6\uff0c\u4ee5\u4fbf\u83b7\u53d6\u66f4\u4e30\u5bcc\u7684\u65f6\u95f4\u7ec6\u8282\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5f00\u53d1\u4e86\u80fd\u591f\u63a7\u5236\u65f6\u95f4\u7684\u6a21\u578b\uff0c\u5305\u62ec\u6307\u5b9a\u64ad\u653e\u901f\u5ea6\u7684\u89c6\u9891\u751f\u6210\u548c\u4f4e\u5e27\u7387\u89c6\u9891\u7684\u9ad8\u5e27\u7387\u8f6c\u5316\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>The paper explores how to detect and control the speed of videos, focusing on understanding time as a visual concept.</li>\n    <li>It presents methods that automatically learn to identify speed changes and estimate playback speeds in videos.</li>\n    <li>The research creates a large dataset of slow-motion videos from various sources, which provides more detailed temporal information than regular videos.</li>\n    <li>New models are developed for generating videos at specific speeds and enhancing low-frame-rate videos to higher frame rates with sharper details.</li>\n    <li>This work aims to improve video generation and analysis, making it easier to understand how events happen over time.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-22T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "Seeing Fast and Slow: Learning the Flow of Time in Videos", "summary": "How can we tell whether a video has been sped up or slowed down? How can we generate videos at different speeds? Although videos have been central to modern computer vision research, little attention has been paid to perceiving and controlling the passage of time. In this paper, we study time as a learnable visual concept and develop models for reasoning about and manipulating the flow of time in videos. We first exploit the multimodal cues and temporal structure naturally present in videos to learn, in a self-supervised manner, to detect speed changes and estimate playback speed. We then show that these learned temporal reasoning models enable us to curate the largest slow-motion video dataset to date from noisy in-the-wild sources. Such slow-motion footage, typically filmed by high-speed cameras, contains substantially richer temporal detail than standard videos. Using this data, we further develop models capable of temporal control, including speed-conditioned video generation, which produces motion at specified playback speed, and temporal super-resolution, which tranforms low-FPS, blurry videos into high-FPS sequences with fine-grained temporal details. Our findings highlight time as a manipulable, perceptual dimension in video learning, opening doors to temporally controllable video generation, temporal forensics detection, and potentially richer world-models that understand how events unfold over time.", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/DWHZnjLwXGiDhsthpZWKL.mp4"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.21931.png", "numComments": 1, "submittedBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "fullname": "taesiri", "name": "taesiri", "type": "user", "isPro": true, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 280, "isUserFollowing": false}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.21375", "authors": [{"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d8b", "name": "Qijun Han", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d8c", "name": "Haoqin Tu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d8d", "name": "Zijun Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d8e", "name": "Haoyue Dai", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d8f", "name": "Yiyang Zhou", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d90", "name": "Nancy Lau", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d91", "name": "Alvaro A. Cardenas", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d92", "name": "Yuhui Xu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d93", "name": "Ran Xu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d94", "name": "Caiming Xiong", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d95", "name": "Zeyu Zheng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d96", "name": "Huaxiu Yao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d97", "name": "Yuyin Zhou", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eadf57a961c3f1b5f40d98", "name": "Cihang Xie", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-23T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-24T01:43:15.614Z", "title": "VLAA-GUI: Knowing When to Stop, Recover, and Search, A Modular Framework for GUI Automation", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "645eb61da3c5cd8a16efffff", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/9112bfeed598dfabf9e077e69e09ecc9.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Cihang Xie", "user": "cihangxie", "type": "user", "name": "cihangxie"}, "summary": "Autonomous GUI agents face two fundamental challenges: early stopping, where agents prematurely declare success without verifiable evidence, and repetitive loops, where agents cycle through the same failing actions without recovery. We present VLAA-GUI, a modular GUI agentic framework built around three integrated components that guide the system on when to Stop, Recover, and Search. First, a mandatory Completeness Verifier enforces UI-observable success criteria and verification at every finish step -- with an agent-level verifier that cross-examines completion claims with decision rules, rejecting those lacking direct visual evidence. Second, a mandatory Loop Breaker provides multi-tier filtering: switching interaction mode after repeated failures, forcing strategy changes after persistent screen-state recurrence, and binding reflection signals to strategy shifts. Third, an on-demand Search Agent searches online for unfamiliar workflows by directly querying a capable LLM with search ability, returning results as plain text. We additionally integrate a Coding Agent for code-intensive actions and a Grounding Agent for precise action grounding, both invoked on demand when required. We evaluate VLAA-GUI across five top-tier backbones, including Opus 4.5, 4.6 and Gemini 3.1 Pro, on two benchmarks with Linux and Windows tasks, achieving top performance on both (77.5% on OSWorld and 61.0% on WindowsAgentArena). Notably, three of the five backbones surpass human performance (72.4%) on OSWorld in a single pass. Ablation studies show that all three proposed components consistently improve a strong backbone, while a weaker backbone benefits more from these tools when the step budget is sufficient. Further analysis also shows that the Loop Breaker nearly halves wasted steps for loop-prone models.", "upvotes": 10, "discussionId": "69eadf58a961c3f1b5f40d99", "projectPage": "https://ucsc-vlaa.github.io/VLAA-GUI/", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/UCSC-VLAA/VLAA-GUI", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "VLAA-GUI is a modular GUI agent framework that addresses early stopping and repetitive loop issues through integrated components for verification, loop breaking, and search capabilities.", "ai_keywords": ["GUI agentic framework", "Completeness Verifier", "Loop Breaker", "Search Agent", "Coding Agent", "Grounding Agent", "Opus 4.5", "Opus 4.6", "Gemini 3.1 Pro", "OSWorld", "WindowsAgentArena", "ablation studies"], "githubStars": 8, "organization": {"_id": "65346047b3852ed1cec0c2f4", "name": "UCSC-VLAA", "fullname": "UCSC-VLAA", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/645eb61da3c5cd8a16efffff/E7m3g_fFhz32pGsnK0eqX.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u81ea\u4e3b\u56fe\u5f62\u7528\u6237\u754c\u9762\uff08GUI\uff09\u4ee3\u7406\u9762\u4e34\u4e24\u4e2a\u4e3b\u8981\u6311\u6218\uff1a\u65e9\u671f\u505c\u6b62\u548c\u91cd\u590d\u5faa\u73af\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86VLAA-GUI\u6846\u67b6\uff0c\u5305\u62ec\u4e09\u4e2a\u7ec4\u4ef6\uff1a\u5b8c\u6210\u9a8c\u8bc1\u5668\u3001\u5faa\u73af\u6253\u7834\u5668\u548c\u641c\u7d22\u4ee3\u7406\uff0c\u5e2e\u52a9\u7cfb\u7edf\u51b3\u7b56\u4f55\u65f6\u505c\u6b62\u3001\u6062\u590d\u548c\u641c\u7d22\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5b8c\u6210\u9a8c\u8bc1\u5668\u786e\u4fdd\u6bcf\u4e2a\u6b65\u9aa4\u90fd\u6709\u53ef\u9a8c\u8bc1\u7684\u6210\u529f\u6807\u51c6\uff0c\u5e76\u62d2\u7edd\u7f3a\u4e4f\u89c6\u89c9\u8bc1\u636e\u7684\u5b8c\u6210\u58f0\u660e\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5faa\u73af\u6253\u7834\u5668\u901a\u8fc7\u591a\u5c42\u6b21\u8fc7\u6ee4\u6765\u5904\u7406\u91cd\u590d\u5931\u8d25\u7684\u60c5\u51b5\uff0c\u6539\u53d8\u4ea4\u4e92\u6a21\u5f0f\u548c\u7b56\u7565\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5728\u4e94\u4e2a\u9876\u7ea7\u57fa\u7840\u6a21\u578b\u4e0a\u8bc4\u4f30VLAA-GUI\uff0c\u83b7\u5f97\u6700\u4f73\u6027\u80fd\uff0c\u4e14\u90e8\u5206\u6a21\u578b\u8d85\u8fc7\u4eba\u7c7b\u8868\u73b0\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>VLAA-GUI is a new framework for autonomous GUI agents that helps them handle two main issues: stopping too early and getting stuck in repetitive actions.</li>\n    <li>It includes three key components: a Completeness Verifier to check for real success, a Loop Breaker to change strategies when failures happen repeatedly, and a Search Agent to find new workflows online.</li>\n    <li>The framework also features a Coding Agent for complex code tasks and a Grounding Agent for precise actions, both used when necessary.</li>\n    <li>Tests show VLAA-GUI performs well on Linux and Windows tasks, with some models outperforming humans in certain benchmarks.</li>\n    <li>Research indicates that the components of VLAA-GUI significantly improve performance, especially for models that struggle with repetitive tasks.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-22T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "VLAA-GUI: Knowing When to Stop, Recover, and Search, A Modular Framework for GUI Automation", "summary": "Autonomous GUI agents face two fundamental challenges: early stopping, where agents prematurely declare success without verifiable evidence, and repetitive loops, where agents cycle through the same failing actions without recovery. We present VLAA-GUI, a modular GUI agentic framework built around three integrated components that guide the system on when to Stop, Recover, and Search. First, a mandatory Completeness Verifier enforces UI-observable success criteria and verification at every finish step -- with an agent-level verifier that cross-examines completion claims with decision rules, rejecting those lacking direct visual evidence. Second, a mandatory Loop Breaker provides multi-tier filtering: switching interaction mode after repeated failures, forcing strategy changes after persistent screen-state recurrence, and binding reflection signals to strategy shifts. Third, an on-demand Search Agent searches online for unfamiliar workflows by directly querying a capable LLM with search ability, returning results as plain text. We additionally integrate a Coding Agent for code-intensive actions and a Grounding Agent for precise action grounding, both invoked on demand when required. We evaluate VLAA-GUI across five top-tier backbones, including Opus 4.5, 4.6 and Gemini 3.1 Pro, on two benchmarks with Linux and Windows tasks, achieving top performance on both (77.5% on OSWorld and 61.0% on WindowsAgentArena). Notably, three of the five backbones surpass human performance (72.4%) on OSWorld in a single pass. Ablation studies show that all three proposed components consistently improve a strong backbone, while a weaker backbone benefits more from these tools when the step budget is sufficient. Further analysis also shows that the Loop Breaker nearly halves wasted steps for loop-prone models.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.21375.png", "numComments": 1, "submittedBy": {"_id": "645eb61da3c5cd8a16efffff", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/9112bfeed598dfabf9e077e69e09ecc9.svg", "fullname": "Cihang Xie", "name": "cihangxie", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 3, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "65346047b3852ed1cec0c2f4", "name": "UCSC-VLAA", "fullname": "UCSC-VLAA", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/645eb61da3c5cd8a16efffff/E7m3g_fFhz32pGsnK0eqX.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.21889", "authors": [{"_id": "69eae126a961c3f1b5f40db5", "name": "Jun Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eae126a961c3f1b5f40db6", "user": {"_id": "6430bdd8cd31d174a9f900fb", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/noauth/Y9SPnRfpKSbYc7MhNdP-H.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Ziyin Zhang", "user": "Geralt-Targaryen", "type": "user", "name": "Geralt-Targaryen"}, "name": "Ziyin Zhang", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-24T13:56:57.205Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eae126a961c3f1b5f40db7", "name": "Rui Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eae126a961c3f1b5f40db8", "name": "Hang Yu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eae126a961c3f1b5f40db9", "name": "Peng Di", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69eae126a961c3f1b5f40dba", "name": "Rui Wang", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-23T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-24T01:53:33.572Z", "title": "TingIS: Real-time Risk Event Discovery from Noisy Customer Incidents at Enterprise Scale", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "6430bdd8cd31d174a9f900fb", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/noauth/Y9SPnRfpKSbYc7MhNdP-H.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Ziyin Zhang", "user": "Geralt-Targaryen", "type": "user", "name": "Geralt-Targaryen"}, "summary": "Real-time detection and mitigation of technical anomalies are critical for large-scale cloud-native services, where even minutes of downtime can result in massive financial losses and diminished user trust. While customer incidents serve as a vital signal for discovering risks missed by monitoring, extracting actionable intelligence from this data remains challenging due to extreme noise, high throughput, and semantic complexity of diverse business lines. In this paper, we present TingIS, an end-to-end system designed for enterprise-grade incident discovery. At the core of TingIS is a multi-stage event linking engine that synergizes efficient indexing techniques with Large Language Models (LLMs) to make informed decisions on event merging, enabling the stable extraction of actionable incidents from just a handful of diverse user descriptions. This engine is complemented by a cascaded routing mechanism for precise business attribution and a multi-dimensional noise reduction pipeline that integrates domain knowledge, statistical patterns, and behavioral filtering. Deployed in a production environment handling a peak throughput of over 2,000 messages per minute and 300,000 messages per day, TingIS achieves a P90 alert latency of 3.5 minutes and a 95\\% discovery rate for high-priority incidents. Benchmarks constructed from real-world data demonstrate that TingIS significantly outperforms baseline methods in routing accuracy, clustering quality, and Signal-to-Noise Ratio.", "upvotes": 9, "discussionId": "69eae127a961c3f1b5f40dbb", "ai_summary": "TingIS is an enterprise-grade incident discovery system that uses multi-stage event linking with LLMs, cascaded routing, and noise reduction to efficiently identify critical issues from high-volume, noisy customer reports.", "ai_keywords": ["Large Language Models", "event linking engine", "cascaded routing mechanism", "noise reduction pipeline", "multi-dimensional filtering", "business attribution", "incident discovery"], "organization": {"_id": "64f97f402003abb61b3d68de", "name": "codefuse-ai", "fullname": "CodeFuse AI", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/64ed861f254de0e729dba8f1/IxbJCzRWm0Ov645jLyupL.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u5728\u5927\u89c4\u6a21\u4e91\u670d\u52a1\u4e2d\uff0c\u5b9e\u65f6\u68c0\u6d4b\u548c\u89e3\u51b3\u6280\u672f\u5f02\u5e38\u975e\u5e38\u91cd\u8981\uff0c\u51e0\u5206\u949f\u7684\u505c\u673a\u53ef\u80fd\u5bfc\u81f4\u5de8\u5927\u7684\u8d22\u52a1\u635f\u5931\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5ba2\u6237\u4e8b\u4ef6\u662f\u53d1\u73b0\u6f5c\u5728\u98ce\u9669\u7684\u91cd\u8981\u4fe1\u53f7\uff0c\u4f46\u4ece\u8fd9\u4e9b\u6570\u636e\u4e2d\u63d0\u53d6\u53ef\u64cd\u4f5c\u7684\u4fe1\u606f\u5f88\u5177\u6311\u6218\u6027\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u672c\u6587\u4ecb\u7ecd\u4e86TingIS\uff0c\u4e00\u4e2a\u7528\u4e8e\u4f01\u4e1a\u7ea7\u4e8b\u4ef6\u53d1\u73b0\u7684\u7aef\u5230\u7aef\u7cfb\u7edf\u3002</li>\n    <li>TingIS\u7684\u6838\u5fc3\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u591a\u9636\u6bb5\u4e8b\u4ef6\u94fe\u63a5\u5f15\u64ce\uff0c\u7ed3\u5408\u9ad8\u6548\u7d22\u5f15\u6280\u672f\u548c\u5927\u578b\u8bed\u8a00\u6a21\u578b\uff0c\u80fd\u591f\u4ece\u5c11\u91cf\u7528\u6237\u63cf\u8ff0\u4e2d\u63d0\u53d6\u53ef\u64cd\u4f5c\u4e8b\u4ef6\u3002</li>\n    <li>TingIS\u5728\u751f\u4ea7\u73af\u5883\u4e2d\u8868\u73b0\u4f18\u5f02\uff0c\u5904\u7406\u9ad8\u8fbe\u6bcf\u5206\u949f2000\u6761\u6d88\u606f\uff0c\u4e14\u9ad8\u4f18\u5148\u7ea7\u4e8b\u4ef6\u7684\u53d1\u73b0\u7387\u8fbe\u523095%\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Real-time detection of technical issues is crucial for cloud services, as downtime can lead to major financial losses and reduced user trust.</li>\n    <li>Customer incidents help identify risks that monitoring might miss, but analyzing this data is difficult due to noise and complexity.</li>\n    <li>TingIS is a new system that helps discover incidents effectively by using advanced indexing and Large Language Models to combine user reports.</li>\n    <li>The system includes methods to ensure accurate business tracking and reduce noise using various analytical techniques.</li>\n    <li>In real-world use, TingIS processes over 2,000 messages per minute and has a high incident discovery rate with quick alert responses.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-22T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "TingIS: Real-time Risk Event Discovery from Noisy Customer Incidents at Enterprise Scale", "summary": "Real-time detection and mitigation of technical anomalies are critical for large-scale cloud-native services, where even minutes of downtime can result in massive financial losses and diminished user trust. While customer incidents serve as a vital signal for discovering risks missed by monitoring, extracting actionable intelligence from this data remains challenging due to extreme noise, high throughput, and semantic complexity of diverse business lines. In this paper, we present TingIS, an end-to-end system designed for enterprise-grade incident discovery. At the core of TingIS is a multi-stage event linking engine that synergizes efficient indexing techniques with Large Language Models (LLMs) to make informed decisions on event merging, enabling the stable extraction of actionable incidents from just a handful of diverse user descriptions. This engine is complemented by a cascaded routing mechanism for precise business attribution and a multi-dimensional noise reduction pipeline that integrates domain knowledge, statistical patterns, and behavioral filtering. Deployed in a production environment handling a peak throughput of over 2,000 messages per minute and 300,000 messages per day, TingIS achieves a P90 alert latency of 3.5 minutes and a 95\\% discovery rate for high-priority incidents. Benchmarks constructed from real-world data demonstrate that TingIS significantly outperforms baseline methods in routing accuracy, clustering quality, and Signal-to-Noise Ratio.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.21889.png", "numComments": 2, "submittedBy": {"_id": "6430bdd8cd31d174a9f900fb", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/noauth/Y9SPnRfpKSbYc7MhNdP-H.jpeg", "fullname": "Ziyin Zhang", "name": "Geralt-Targaryen", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 13, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "64f97f402003abb61b3d68de", "name": "codefuse-ai", "fullname": "CodeFuse AI", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/64ed861f254de0e729dba8f1/IxbJCzRWm0Ov645jLyupL.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": true}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.20244", "authors": [{"_id": "69ea1253a961c3f1b5f40a08", "name": "Wenhong Zhu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ea1253a961c3f1b5f40a09", "name": "Ruobing Xie", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ea1253a961c3f1b5f40a0a", "name": "Rui Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ea1253a961c3f1b5f40a0b", "name": "Pengfei Liu", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-22T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-24T03:32:20.845Z", "title": "Hybrid Policy Distillation for LLMs", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "649a456296d5747b35e04d36", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/649a456296d5747b35e04d36/DD3vBPFE8qm6VIHP5GsDq.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "SII-Wenhong", "user": "wh-zhu", "type": "user", "name": "wh-zhu"}, "summary": "Knowledge distillation (KD) is a powerful paradigm for compressing large language models (LLMs), whose effectiveness depends on intertwined choices of divergence direction, optimization strategy, and data regime. We break down the design of existing KD methods and present a unified view that establishes connections between them, reformulating KD as a reweighted log-likelihood objective at the token level. We further propose Hybrid Policy Distillation (HPD), which integrates the complementary advantages of forward and reverse KL to balance mode coverage and mode-seeking, and combines off-policy data with lightweight, approximate on-policy sampling. We validate HPD on long-generation math reasoning as well as short-generation dialogue and code tasks, demonstrating improved optimization stability, computational efficiency, and final performance across diverse model families and scales. The code related to this work is available at https://github.com/zwhong714/Hybrid-Policy-Distillation.", "upvotes": 9, "discussionId": "69ea1253a961c3f1b5f40a0c", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/zwhong714/Hybrid-Policy-Distillation", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "Hybrid Policy Distillation combines forward and reverse KL divergence approaches to improve knowledge distillation stability and efficiency across different model sizes and tasks.", "ai_keywords": ["knowledge distillation", "large language models", "divergence direction", "optimization strategy", "data regime", "reweighted log-likelihood", "forward KL", "reverse KL", "mode coverage", "mode-seeking", "off-policy data", "on-policy sampling"], "githubStars": 3, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u77e5\u8bc6\u84b8\u998f\uff08KD\uff09\u662f\u4e00\u79cd\u538b\u7f29\u5927\u578b\u8bed\u8a00\u6a21\u578b\u7684\u6709\u6548\u65b9\u6cd5\uff0c\u5176\u6548\u679c\u4f9d\u8d56\u4e8e\u4e0d\u540c\u7684\u9009\u62e9\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u5206\u6790\u4e86\u73b0\u6709\u7684KD\u65b9\u6cd5\uff0c\u5e76\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86\u4e00\u4e2a\u7edf\u4e00\u7684\u89c6\u89d2\uff0c\u5c06KD\u91cd\u65b0\u5b9a\u4e49\u4e3a\u4ee4\u724c\u7ea7\u522b\u7684\u52a0\u6743\u5bf9\u6570\u4f3c\u7136\u76ee\u6807\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86\u6df7\u5408\u7b56\u7565\u84b8\u998f\uff08HPD\uff09\uff0c\u7ed3\u5408\u4e86\u6b63\u5411\u548c\u53cd\u5411KL\u7684\u4f18\u70b9\uff0c\u4ee5\u5e73\u8861\u6a21\u5f0f\u8986\u76d6\u548c\u6a21\u5f0f\u5bfb\u6c42\u3002</li>\n    <li>HPD\u7ed3\u5408\u4e86\u79bb\u7ebf\u6570\u636e\u548c\u8f7b\u91cf\u7ea7\u3001\u8fd1\u4f3c\u7684\u5728\u7ebf\u91c7\u6837\uff0c\u9a8c\u8bc1\u4e86\u5176\u5728\u6570\u5b66\u63a8\u7406\u548c\u5bf9\u8bdd\u3001\u4ee3\u7801\u4efb\u52a1\u4e2d\u7684\u6548\u679c\u3002</li>\n    <li>HPD\u5728\u4e0d\u540c\u6a21\u578b\u548c\u89c4\u6a21\u4e0a\u5c55\u793a\u4e86\u4f18\u5316\u7a33\u5b9a\u6027\u3001\u8ba1\u7b97\u6548\u7387\u548c\u6700\u7ec8\u6027\u80fd\u7684\u63d0\u9ad8\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n  <li>Knowledge distillation (KD) helps to make large language models smaller and more efficient.</li>\n  <li>The effectiveness of KD relies on the choices made regarding how to measure differences, how to optimize, and what data to use.</li>\n  <li>The authors provide a new way of looking at KD methods, linking them together and redefining it as a different mathematical objective.</li>\n  <li>They introduce a new method called Hybrid Policy Distillation (HPD), which combines different techniques to improve performance and efficiency.</li>\n  <li>HPD shows better results in tasks like math reasoning, dialogue, and coding, with more stable optimization and better overall performance.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-21T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "Hybrid Policy Distillation for LLMs", "summary": "Knowledge distillation (KD) is a powerful paradigm for compressing large language models (LLMs), whose effectiveness depends on intertwined choices of divergence direction, optimization strategy, and data regime. We break down the design of existing KD methods and present a unified view that establishes connections between them, reformulating KD as a reweighted log-likelihood objective at the token level. We further propose Hybrid Policy Distillation (HPD), which integrates the complementary advantages of forward and reverse KL to balance mode coverage and mode-seeking, and combines off-policy data with lightweight, approximate on-policy sampling. We validate HPD on long-generation math reasoning as well as short-generation dialogue and code tasks, demonstrating improved optimization stability, computational efficiency, and final performance across diverse model families and scales. The code related to this work is available at https://github.com/zwhong714/Hybrid-Policy-Distillation.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.20244.png", "numComments": 1, "submittedBy": {"_id": "649a456296d5747b35e04d36", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/649a456296d5747b35e04d36/DD3vBPFE8qm6VIHP5GsDq.jpeg", "fullname": "SII-Wenhong", "name": "wh-zhu", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 1, "isUserFollowing": false}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.21921", "authors": [{"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d37", "name": "Ceyuan Yang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d38", "name": "Zhijie Lin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d39", "name": "Yang Zhao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d3a", "name": "Fei Xiao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d3b", "name": "Hao He", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d3c", "name": "Qi Zhao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d3d", "name": "Chaorui Deng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d3e", "name": "Kunchang Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d3f", "name": "Zihan Ding", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d40", "name": "Yuwei Guo", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d41", "name": "Fuyun Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d42", "name": "Fangqi Zhu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d43", "name": "Xiaonan Nie", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d44", "name": "Shenhan Zhu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d45", "name": "Shanchuan Lin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d46", "name": "Hongsheng Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d47", "name": "Weilin Huang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d48", "name": "Guang Shi", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d49", "name": "Haoqi Fan", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-23T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-24T00:56:53.719Z", "title": "Context Unrolling in Omni Models", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "taesiri", "user": "taesiri", "type": "user", "name": "taesiri"}, "summary": "We present Omni, a unified multimodal model natively trained on diverse modalities, including text, images, videos, 3D geometry, and hidden representations. We find that such training enables Context Unrolling, where the model explicitly reasons across multiple modal representations before producing predictions. This process enables the model to aggregate complementary information across heterogeneous modalities, facilitating a more faithful approximation of the shared multimodal knowledge manifold and improving downstream reasoning fidelity. As a result, Omni achieves strong performance on both multimodal generation and understanding benchmarks, while demonstrating advanced multimodal reasoning capabilities, including in-context generation of text, image, video, and 3D geometry.", "upvotes": 5, "discussionId": "69ead3d8a961c3f1b5f40d4a", "projectPage": "https://omni-model.com/", "ai_summary": "Omni is a unified multimodal model trained on diverse data types that enables context unrolling for improved reasoning across heterogeneous modalities.", "ai_keywords": ["multimodal model", "context unrolling", "multimodal knowledge manifold", "downstream reasoning", "in-context generation"], "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>Omni \u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u7edf\u4e00\u7684\u591a\u6a21\u6001\u6a21\u578b\uff0c\u80fd\u591f\u5904\u7406\u6587\u672c\u3001\u56fe\u50cf\u3001\u89c6\u9891\u30013D\u51e0\u4f55\u548c\u9690\u85cf\u8868\u793a\u7b49\u591a\u79cd\u6570\u636e\u5f62\u5f0f\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8be5\u6a21\u578b\u901a\u8fc7\u591a\u6a21\u6001\u8bad\u7ec3\uff0c\u80fd\u591f\u5728\u751f\u6210\u9884\u6d4b\u4e4b\u524d\uff0c\u660e\u786e\u5730\u5728\u4e0d\u540c\u6a21\u6001\u4e4b\u95f4\u8fdb\u884c\u63a8\u7406\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8fd9\u79cd\u63a8\u7406\u65b9\u5f0f\u5e2e\u52a9\u6a21\u578b\u6574\u5408\u5404\u7c7b\u4fe1\u606f\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u66f4\u51c6\u786e\u5730\u7406\u89e3\u591a\u6a21\u6001\u77e5\u8bc6\u3002</li>\n    <li>Omni \u5728\u591a\u6a21\u6001\u751f\u6210\u548c\u7406\u89e3\u7684\u57fa\u51c6\u6d4b\u8bd5\u4e2d\u8868\u73b0\u51fa\u8272\uff0c\u5e76\u5c55\u793a\u4e86\u5148\u8fdb\u7684\u591a\u6a21\u6001\u63a8\u7406\u80fd\u529b\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8be5\u6a21\u578b\u80fd\u591f\u5728\u4e0a\u4e0b\u6587\u4e2d\u751f\u6210\u6587\u672c\u3001\u56fe\u50cf\u3001\u89c6\u9891\u548c3D\u51e0\u4f55\u7b49\u5185\u5bb9\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Omni is a new model that can work with different types of information, like text, images, videos, and 3D shapes.</li>\n    <li>It uses a method called Context Unrolling to think about and combine information from these different types before making predictions.</li>\n    <li>This approach helps the model better understand and connect various types of information.</li>\n    <li>As a result, Omni performs well on tasks that involve creating and understanding multimodal content.</li>\n    <li>It shows advanced skills in generating and reasoning about text, images, videos, and 3D data together.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-22T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "Context Unrolling in Omni Models", "summary": "We present Omni, a unified multimodal model natively trained on diverse modalities, including text, images, videos, 3D geometry, and hidden representations. We find that such training enables Context Unrolling, where the model explicitly reasons across multiple modal representations before producing predictions. This process enables the model to aggregate complementary information across heterogeneous modalities, facilitating a more faithful approximation of the shared multimodal knowledge manifold and improving downstream reasoning fidelity. As a result, Omni achieves strong performance on both multimodal generation and understanding benchmarks, while demonstrating advanced multimodal reasoning capabilities, including in-context generation of text, image, video, and 3D geometry.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.21921.png", "numComments": 0, "submittedBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "fullname": "taesiri", "name": "taesiri", "type": "user", "isPro": true, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 280, "isUserFollowing": false}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}],
    "week": [{"paper": {"id": "2604.20796", "authors": [{"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b407c", "name": "Inclusion AI", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b407d", "name": "Tiwei Bie", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b407e", "user": {"_id": "63898c562a897944ea5f07a2", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/63898c562a897944ea5f07a2/oG1ia44ICpAk1tReIaX0G.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Haoxing chen", "user": "HaoxingChen", "type": "user", "name": "HaoxingChen"}, "name": "Haoxing Chen", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-23T07:49:48.104Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b407f", "name": "Tieyuan Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4080", "name": "Zhenglin Cheng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4081", "name": "Long Cui", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4082", "name": "Kai Gan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4083", "name": "Zhicheng Huang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4084", "name": "Zhenzhong Lan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4085", "name": "Haoquan Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4086", "name": "Jianguo Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4087", "name": "Tao Lin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4088", "user": {"_id": "66bb136002fd8eb58bc84ffb", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/122cb8f59c502392768099b3c2afe043.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "qinqi", "user": "Dakerqi", "type": "user", "name": "Dakerqi"}, "name": "Qi Qin", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-23T07:49:44.838Z", "hidden": true}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4089", "name": "Hongjun Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b408a", "name": "Xiaomei Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b408b", "name": "Haoyuan Wu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b408c", "name": "Yi Xin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b408d", "name": "Junbo Zhao", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-22T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-23T00:36:39.828Z", "title": "LLaDA2.0-Uni: Unifying Multimodal Understanding and Generation with Diffusion Large Language Model", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "taesiri", "user": "taesiri", "type": "user", "name": "taesiri"}, "summary": "We present LLaDA2.0-Uni, a unified discrete diffusion large language model (dLLM) that supports multimodal understanding and generation within a natively integrated framework. Its architecture combines a fully semantic discrete tokenizer, a MoE-based dLLM backbone, and a diffusion decoder. By discretizing continuous visual inputs via SigLIP-VQ, the model enables block-level masked diffusion for both text and vision inputs within the backbone, while the decoder reconstructs visual tokens into high-fidelity images. Inference efficiency is enhanced beyond parallel decoding through prefix-aware optimizations in the backbone and few-step distillation in the decoder. Supported by carefully curated large-scale data and a tailored multi-stage training pipeline, LLaDA2.0-Uni matches specialized VLMs in multimodal understanding while delivering strong performance in image generation and editing. Its native support for interleaved generation and reasoning establishes a promising and scalable paradigm for next-generation unified foundation models. Codes and models are available at https://github.com/inclusionAI/LLaDA2.0-Uni.", "upvotes": 208, "discussionId": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b408e", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/inclusionAI/LLaDA2.0-Uni", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "LLaDA2.0-Uni is a unified discrete diffusion language model that integrates multimodal understanding and generation through a semantic discrete tokenizer, MoE-based backbone, and diffusion decoder, achieving performance comparable to specialized vision-language models while enabling efficient inference and high-fidelity image generation.", "ai_keywords": ["discrete diffusion", "large language model", "multimodal understanding", "multimodal generation", "semantic discrete tokenizer", "MoE-based backbone", "diffusion decoder", "SigLIP-VQ", "block-level masked diffusion", "parallel decoding", "prefix-aware optimizations", "few-step distillation", "large-scale data", "multi-stage training pipeline", "interleaved generation", "reasoning"], "githubStars": 98, "organization": {"_id": "67aea5c8f086ab0f70ed97c9", "name": "inclusionAI", "fullname": "inclusionAI", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/662e1f9da266499277937d33/fyKuazRifqiaIO34xrhhm.jpeg"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u4ecb\u7ecd\u4e86LLaDA2.0-Uni\uff0c\u8fd9\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u7edf\u4e00\u7684\u79bb\u6563\u6269\u6563\u5927\u8bed\u8a00\u6a21\u578b\uff0c\u652f\u6301\u591a\u6a21\u6001\u7406\u89e3\u548c\u751f\u6210\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8be5\u6a21\u578b\u7ed3\u5408\u4e86\u5b8c\u5168\u8bed\u4e49\u7684\u79bb\u6563\u6807\u8bb0\u5668\u3001\u57fa\u4e8eMoE\u7684dLLM\u9aa8\u5e72\u548c\u6269\u6563\u89e3\u7801\u5668\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u901a\u8fc7SigLIP-VQ\u5bf9\u8fde\u7eed\u89c6\u89c9\u8f93\u5165\u8fdb\u884c\u79bb\u6563\u5316\uff0c\u6a21\u578b\u5b9e\u73b0\u4e86\u6587\u672c\u548c\u89c6\u89c9\u8f93\u5165\u7684\u5757\u7ea7\u63a9\u853d\u6269\u6563\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6a21\u578b\u5728\u63a8\u7406\u6548\u7387\u4e0a\u8fdb\u884c\u4e86\u4f18\u5316\uff0c\u80fd\u591f\u5feb\u901f\u751f\u6210\u9ad8\u8d28\u91cf\u7684\u56fe\u50cf\u3002</li>\n    <li>LLaDA2.0-Uni\u5728\u591a\u6a21\u6001\u7406\u89e3\u548c\u56fe\u50cf\u751f\u6210\u65b9\u9762\u8868\u73b0\u51fa\u8272\uff0c\u9002\u5408\u4e0b\u4e00\u4ee3\u7edf\u4e00\u57fa\u7840\u6a21\u578b\u7684\u5f00\u53d1\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>LLaDA2.0-Uni is a new model that can understand and create both text and images together.</li>\n    <li>It uses a special method to turn visual information into a format the model can work with, allowing it to handle both text and images effectively.</li>\n    <li>The model is designed to work efficiently, making it faster to generate outputs compared to other models.</li>\n    <li>LLaDA2.0-Uni performs well in understanding and generating images, similar to specialized models made just for visual tasks.</li>\n    <li>You can find the codes and models for LLaDA2.0-Uni online at GitHub.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-21T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "LLaDA2.0-Uni: Unifying Multimodal Understanding and Generation with Diffusion Large Language Model", "summary": "We present LLaDA2.0-Uni, a unified discrete diffusion large language model (dLLM) that supports multimodal understanding and generation within a natively integrated framework. Its architecture combines a fully semantic discrete tokenizer, a MoE-based dLLM backbone, and a diffusion decoder. By discretizing continuous visual inputs via SigLIP-VQ, the model enables block-level masked diffusion for both text and vision inputs within the backbone, while the decoder reconstructs visual tokens into high-fidelity images. Inference efficiency is enhanced beyond parallel decoding through prefix-aware optimizations in the backbone and few-step distillation in the decoder. Supported by carefully curated large-scale data and a tailored multi-stage training pipeline, LLaDA2.0-Uni matches specialized VLMs in multimodal understanding while delivering strong performance in image generation and editing. Its native support for interleaved generation and reasoning establishes a promising and scalable paradigm for next-generation unified foundation models. Codes and models are available at https://github.com/inclusionAI/LLaDA2.0-Uni.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.20796.png", "numComments": 1, "submittedBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "fullname": "taesiri", "name": "taesiri", "type": "user", "isPro": true, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 280, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "67aea5c8f086ab0f70ed97c9", "name": "inclusionAI", "fullname": "inclusionAI", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/662e1f9da266499277937d33/fyKuazRifqiaIO34xrhhm.jpeg"}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.18168", "authors": [{"_id": "69e6efbe76b653026bd83dc7", "name": "Chenxi Zhao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6efbe76b653026bd83dc8", "name": "Chen Zhu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6efbe76b653026bd83dc9", "name": "Xiaokun Feng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6efbe76b653026bd83dca", "name": "Aiming Hao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6efbe76b653026bd83dcb", "name": "Jiashu Zhu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6efbe76b653026bd83dcc", "name": "Jiachen Lei", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6efbe76b653026bd83dcd", "name": "Jiahong Wu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6efbe76b653026bd83dce", "name": "Xiangxiang Chu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6efbe76b653026bd83dcf", "name": "Jufeng Yang", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/66d255e3947594430c723ff6/FOg8SfjukAkgqzM47lY55.mp4"], "publishedAt": "2026-04-20T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-21T06:55:15.692Z", "title": "Extending One-Step Image Generation from Class Labels to Text via Discriminative Text Representation", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "66d255e3947594430c723ff6", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/c56e4792332a01bf34085a75ee64916e.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "xiaochonglinghu", "user": "xiaochonglinghu", "type": "user", "name": "xiaochonglinghu"}, "summary": "Few-step generation has been a long-standing goal, with recent one-step generation methods exemplified by MeanFlow achieving remarkable results. Existing research on MeanFlow primarily focuses on class-to-image generation. However, an intuitive yet unexplored direction is to extend the condition from fixed class labels to flexible text inputs, enabling richer content creation. Compared to the limited class labels, text conditions pose greater challenges to the model's understanding capability, necessitating the effective integration of powerful text encoders into the MeanFlow framework. Surprisingly, although incorporating text conditions appears straightforward, we find that integrating powerful LLM-based text encoders using conventional training strategies results in unsatisfactory performance. To uncover the underlying cause, we conduct detailed analyses and reveal that, due to the extremely limited number of refinement steps in the MeanFlow generation, such as only one step, the text feature representations are required to possess sufficiently high discriminability. This also explains why discrete and easily distinguishable class features perform well within the MeanFlow framework. Guided by these insights, we leverage a powerful LLM-based text encoder validated to possess the required semantic properties and adapt the MeanFlow generation process to this framework, resulting in efficient text-conditioned synthesis for the first time. Furthermore, we validate our approach on the widely used diffusion model, demonstrating significant generation performance improvements. We hope this work provides a general and practical reference for future research on text-conditioned MeanFlow generation. The code is available at https://github.com/AMAP-ML/EMF.", "upvotes": 86, "discussionId": "69e6efbe76b653026bd83dd0", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/AMAP-ML/EMF", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "Researchers extend MeanFlow generation from class labels to text inputs by integrating powerful LLM-based text encoders, overcoming limitations of few-step refinement through enhanced semantic feature representation.", "ai_keywords": ["MeanFlow", "text-conditioned synthesis", "LLM-based text encoders", "semantic properties", "diffusion model", "class-to-image generation", "refinement steps", "discriminability", "generation performance improvements"], "githubStars": 85, "organization": {"_id": "67d11771890254196d3174e5", "name": "GD-ML", "fullname": "AMAP-ML", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/67d116c47be76de1a40873ca/s5ukAx9E36ZZIKvbpBRi4.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u5c11\u6b65\u751f\u6210\u4e00\u76f4\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u76ee\u6807\uff0cMeanFlow\u7b49\u4e00\u7ad9\u5f0f\u751f\u6210\u65b9\u6cd5\u53d6\u5f97\u4e86\u663e\u8457\u6210\u679c\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u73b0\u6709\u7814\u7a76\u4e3b\u8981\u96c6\u4e2d\u5728\u7c7b\u5230\u56fe\u50cf\u751f\u6210\u4e0a\uff0c\u4f46\u5c06\u6761\u4ef6\u4ece\u56fa\u5b9a\u7c7b\u6807\u7b7e\u6269\u5c55\u5230\u7075\u6d3b\u7684\u6587\u672c\u8f93\u5165\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u672a\u63a2\u7d22\u7684\u65b9\u5411\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6587\u672c\u6761\u4ef6\u6bd4\u6709\u9650\u7684\u7c7b\u6807\u7b7e\u5bf9\u6a21\u578b\u7406\u89e3\u80fd\u529b\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86\u66f4\u5927\u6311\u6218\uff0c\u9700\u8981\u6709\u6548\u6574\u5408\u5f3a\u5927\u7684\u6587\u672c\u7f16\u7801\u5668\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5c3d\u7ba1\u5c06\u6587\u672c\u6761\u4ef6\u6574\u5408\u8d77\u6765\u4f3c\u4e4e\u7b80\u5355\uff0c\u4f46\u4f7f\u7528\u4f20\u7edf\u8bad\u7ec3\u7b56\u7565\u4f1a\u5bfc\u81f4\u6027\u80fd\u4e0d\u4f73\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u7684\u7814\u7a76\u8868\u660e\uff0cMeanFlow\u751f\u6210\u8fc7\u7a0b\u4e2d\u7684\u6781\u5c11\u6570\u7ec6\u5316\u6b65\u9aa4\u8981\u6c42\u6587\u672c\u7279\u5f81\u5177\u6709\u9ad8\u533a\u5206\u6027\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u6210\u529f\u5b9e\u73b0\u4e86\u6587\u672c\u6761\u4ef6\u5408\u6210\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>The study explores improving image generation by using flexible text inputs instead of just fixed class labels.</li>\n    <li>Integrating powerful text encoders into the MeanFlow framework faces challenges due to the limited number of generation steps.</li>\n    <li>Conventional training methods for text encoders did not yield good results, highlighting the need for better discriminability in text features.</li>\n    <li>The researchers adapted the MeanFlow framework to effectively use a strong text encoder, achieving better text-conditioned image generation.</li>\n    <li>The approach was validated on a popular diffusion model, showing significant improvements in generation performance.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-19T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "Extending One-Step Image Generation from Class Labels to Text via Discriminative Text Representation", "summary": "Few-step generation has been a long-standing goal, with recent one-step generation methods exemplified by MeanFlow achieving remarkable results. Existing research on MeanFlow primarily focuses on class-to-image generation. However, an intuitive yet unexplored direction is to extend the condition from fixed class labels to flexible text inputs, enabling richer content creation. Compared to the limited class labels, text conditions pose greater challenges to the model's understanding capability, necessitating the effective integration of powerful text encoders into the MeanFlow framework. Surprisingly, although incorporating text conditions appears straightforward, we find that integrating powerful LLM-based text encoders using conventional training strategies results in unsatisfactory performance. To uncover the underlying cause, we conduct detailed analyses and reveal that, due to the extremely limited number of refinement steps in the MeanFlow generation, such as only one step, the text feature representations are required to possess sufficiently high discriminability. This also explains why discrete and easily distinguishable class features perform well within the MeanFlow framework. Guided by these insights, we leverage a powerful LLM-based text encoder validated to possess the required semantic properties and adapt the MeanFlow generation process to this framework, resulting in efficient text-conditioned synthesis for the first time. Furthermore, we validate our approach on the widely used diffusion model, demonstrating significant generation performance improvements. We hope this work provides a general and practical reference for future research on text-conditioned MeanFlow generation. The code is available at https://github.com/AMAP-ML/EMF.", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/66d255e3947594430c723ff6/FOg8SfjukAkgqzM47lY55.mp4"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.18168.png", "numComments": 1, "submittedBy": {"_id": "66d255e3947594430c723ff6", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/c56e4792332a01bf34085a75ee64916e.svg", "fullname": "xiaochonglinghu", "name": "xiaochonglinghu", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 9, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "67d11771890254196d3174e5", "name": "GD-ML", "fullname": "AMAP-ML", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/67d116c47be76de1a40873ca/s5ukAx9E36ZZIKvbpBRi4.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.19748", "authors": [{"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab4d", "name": "Mengting Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab4e", "name": "Zhengrui Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab4f", "name": "Yongchao Du", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab50", "name": "Zuan Gao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab51", "user": {"_id": "634bec6ca5d4e109c6aa4895", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/2f55327097b3782f6f4f59041f3b04b5.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "hu", "user": "taihang", "type": "user", "name": "taihang"}, "name": "Taihang Hu", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-22T07:21:43.278Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab52", "name": "Jinsong Lan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab53", "name": "Chao Lin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab54", "user": {"_id": "63818941f496d57325c661c7", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/2fd3f2846041f7273ccd18b4810f52d0.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "shen", "user": "DukeShen", "type": "user", "name": "DukeShen"}, "name": "Yefeng Shen", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-22T07:21:14.103Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab55", "user": {"_id": "6690b0ecf5262777d8cb831a", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/51c2837ef71a2a61f36d7cbbe475a69a.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Xingjian Wang", "user": "CyberPegasus", "type": "user", "name": "CyberPegasus"}, "name": "Xingjian Wang", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-22T07:21:41.049Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab56", "name": "Zhao Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab57", "name": "Zhengtao Wu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab58", "name": "Xiaoli Xu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab59", "name": "Zhengze Xu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab5a", "name": "Hao Yan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab5b", "name": "Mingzhou Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab5c", "name": "Jun Zheng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab5d", "name": "Qinye Zhou", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab5e", "name": "Xiaoyong Zhu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab5f", "name": "Bo Zheng", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-21T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-22T00:40:29.628Z", "title": "Tstars-Tryon 1.0: Robust and Realistic Virtual Try-On for Diverse Fashion Items", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "taesiri", "user": "taesiri", "type": "user", "name": "taesiri"}, "summary": "Recent advances in image generation and editing have opened new opportunities for virtual try-on. However, existing methods still struggle to meet complex real-world demands. We present Tstars-Tryon 1.0, a commercial-scale virtual try-on system that is robust, realistic, versatile, and highly efficient. First, our system maintains a high success rate across challenging cases like extreme poses, severe illumination variations, motion blur, and other in-the-wild conditions. Second, it delivers highly photorealistic results with fine-grained details, faithfully preserving garment texture, material properties, and structural characteristics, while largely avoiding common AI-generated artifacts. Third, beyond apparel try-on, our model supports flexible multi-image composition (up to 6 reference images) across 8 fashion categories, with coordinated control over person identity and background. Fourth, to overcome the latency bottlenecks of commercial deployment, our system is heavily optimized for inference speed, delivering near real-time generation for a seamless user experience. These capabilities are enabled by an integrated system design spanning end-to-end model architecture, a scalable data engine, robust infrastructure, and a multi-stage training paradigm. Extensive evaluation and large-scale product deployment demonstrate that Tstars-Tryon1.0 achieves leading overall performance. To support future research, we also release a comprehensive benchmark. The model has been deployed at an industrial scale on the Taobao App, serving millions of users with tens of millions of requests.", "upvotes": 80, "discussionId": "69e82e0e5f6b3d4e5af9ab60", "projectPage": "https://huggingface.co/datasets/TaobaoTmall-AlgorithmProducts/Tstars-VTON", "ai_summary": "A commercial-scale virtual try-on system achieves high success rates, photorealistic results, and real-time performance through integrated system design and multi-stage training.", "ai_keywords": ["virtual try-on", "image generation", "image editing", "photorealistic results", "multi-stage training", "end-to-end model architecture", "scalable data engine", "robust infrastructure"], "organization": {"_id": "64488b334988ee01f2a8d856", "name": "alibaba-inc", "fullname": "alibaba-inc", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/61ac8f8a00d01045fca0ad2f/MX4wxQVaFm1A1wqnrL2WU.jpeg"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>Tstars-Tryon 1.0\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u5546\u4e1a\u7ea7\u865a\u62df\u8bd5\u8863\u7cfb\u7edf\uff0c\u5177\u6709\u5f3a\u5927\u7684\u7a33\u5b9a\u6027\u548c\u9ad8\u6548\u6027\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8be5\u7cfb\u7edf\u5728\u6781\u7aef\u59ff\u52bf\u3001\u5149\u7167\u53d8\u5316\u548c\u8fd0\u52a8\u6a21\u7cca\u7b49\u590d\u6742\u60c5\u51b5\u4e0b\u4ecd\u80fd\u4fdd\u6301\u9ad8\u6210\u529f\u7387\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u63d0\u4f9b\u9ad8\u5ea6\u771f\u5b9e\u7684\u7ed3\u679c\uff0c\u4fdd\u7559\u670d\u88c5\u7684\u7eb9\u7406\u3001\u6750\u6599\u7279\u6027\u548c\u7ed3\u6784\u7ec6\u8282\uff0c\u907f\u514d\u5e38\u89c1\u7684AI\u751f\u6210\u4f2a\u5f71\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u652f\u6301\u6700\u591a6\u5f20\u53c2\u8003\u56fe\u7247\u7684\u7075\u6d3b\u591a\u56fe\u7ec4\u5408\uff0c\u6db5\u76d68\u4e2a\u65f6\u5c1a\u7c7b\u522b\uff0c\u5e76\u53ef\u63a7\u5236\u4eba\u7269\u8eab\u4efd\u548c\u80cc\u666f\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u7ecf\u8fc7\u4f18\u5316\uff0c\u7cfb\u7edf\u5b9e\u73b0\u4e86\u63a5\u8fd1\u5b9e\u65f6\u7684\u751f\u6210\u901f\u5ea6\uff0c\u5df2\u5728\u6dd8\u5b9dApp\u4e0a\u5927\u89c4\u6a21\u90e8\u7f72\uff0c\u670d\u52a1\u6570\u767e\u4e07\u7528\u6237\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Tstars-Tryon 1.0 is a new virtual try-on system that is effective, realistic, and fast.</li>\n    <li>It performs well in difficult situations, like unusual poses and bad lighting, and avoids common AI mistakes.</li>\n    <li>The system provides detailed and lifelike images, accurately showing clothing textures and styles.</li>\n    <li>It can handle multiple images from different fashion categories and allows for control over the person's appearance and background.</li>\n    <li>Tstars-Tryon 1.0 is designed for quick use, making it suitable for large-scale deployment, and is available on the Taobao App for many users.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-20T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "Tstars-Tryon 1.0: Robust and Realistic Virtual Try-On for Diverse Fashion Items", "summary": "Recent advances in image generation and editing have opened new opportunities for virtual try-on. However, existing methods still struggle to meet complex real-world demands. We present Tstars-Tryon 1.0, a commercial-scale virtual try-on system that is robust, realistic, versatile, and highly efficient. First, our system maintains a high success rate across challenging cases like extreme poses, severe illumination variations, motion blur, and other in-the-wild conditions. Second, it delivers highly photorealistic results with fine-grained details, faithfully preserving garment texture, material properties, and structural characteristics, while largely avoiding common AI-generated artifacts. Third, beyond apparel try-on, our model supports flexible multi-image composition (up to 6 reference images) across 8 fashion categories, with coordinated control over person identity and background. Fourth, to overcome the latency bottlenecks of commercial deployment, our system is heavily optimized for inference speed, delivering near real-time generation for a seamless user experience. These capabilities are enabled by an integrated system design spanning end-to-end model architecture, a scalable data engine, robust infrastructure, and a multi-stage training paradigm. Extensive evaluation and large-scale product deployment demonstrate that Tstars-Tryon1.0 achieves leading overall performance. To support future research, we also release a comprehensive benchmark. The model has been deployed at an industrial scale on the Taobao App, serving millions of users with tens of millions of requests.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.19748.png", "numComments": 6, "submittedBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "fullname": "taesiri", "name": "taesiri", "type": "user", "isPro": true, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 277, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "64488b334988ee01f2a8d856", "name": "alibaba-inc", "fullname": "alibaba-inc", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/61ac8f8a00d01045fca0ad2f/MX4wxQVaFm1A1wqnrL2WU.jpeg"}, "isAuthorParticipating": true}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.18486", "authors": [{"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d1d", "name": "Jinghui Lu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d1e", "name": "Jiayi Guan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d1f", "name": "Zhijian Huang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d20", "user": {"_id": "6571d7245ad5f099a62f483d", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/1f34ae744ee2a9ade8f2d7328aeb5fb5.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Jinlong Li", "user": "TyroneDragon", "type": "user", "name": "TyroneDragon"}, "name": "Jinlong Li", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-21T14:15:09.607Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d21", "name": "Guang Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d22", "name": "Lingdong Kong", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d23", "name": "Yingyan Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d24", "name": "Han Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d25", "name": "Shaoqing Xu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d26", "name": "Yuechen Luo", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d27", "name": "Fang Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d28", "name": "Chenxu Dang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d29", "name": "Junli Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d2a", "name": "Tao Xu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d2b", "name": "Jing Wu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d2c", "name": "Jianhua Wu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d2d", "name": "Xiaoshuai Hao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d2e", "name": "Wen Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d2f", "user": {"_id": "6895e7f146763431aea25ca4", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/52e550c3f7e8da2e31b63413e2e71e6c.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Tianyi Jiang", "user": "LumosJiang", "type": "user", "name": "LumosJiang"}, "name": "Tianyi Jiang", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-21T14:15:43.125Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d30", "name": "Lingfeng Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d31", "name": "Lei Zhou", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d32", "name": "Yingbo Tang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d33", "name": "Jie Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d34", "name": "Yinfeng Gao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d35", "name": "Xizhou Bu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d36", "name": "Haochen Tian", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d37", "name": "Yihang Qiu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d38", "name": "Feiyang Jia", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d39", "name": "Lin Liu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d3a", "name": "Yigu Ge", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d3b", "name": "Hanbing Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d3c", "name": "Yuannan Shen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d3d", "name": "Jianwei Cui", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d3e", "name": "Hongwei Xie", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d3f", "name": "Bing Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d40", "name": "Haiyang Sun", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d41", "name": "Jingwei Zhao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d42", "name": "Jiahui Huang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d43", "name": "Pei Liu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d44", "name": "Zeyu Zhu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d45", "name": "Yuncheng Jiang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d46", "name": "Zibin Guo", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d47", "name": "Chuhong Gong", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d48", "name": "Hanchao Leng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d49", "name": "Kun Ma", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d4a", "name": "Naiyang Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d4b", "name": "Guang Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d4c", "name": "Kuiyuan Yang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d4d", "name": "Hangjun Ye", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d4e", "name": "Long Chen", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-20T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-21T01:34:55.226Z", "title": "OneVL: One-Step Latent Reasoning and Planning with Vision-Language Explanation", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "62df78222d89ce551ce0f71d", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/89fba294cff2d2f941d121c1923e4c76.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Lingdong Kong", "user": "ldkong", "type": "user", "name": "ldkong"}, "summary": "Chain-of-Thought (CoT) reasoning has become a powerful driver of trajectory prediction in VLA-based autonomous driving, yet its autoregressive nature imposes a latency cost that is prohibitive for real-time deployment. Latent CoT methods attempt to close this gap by compressing reasoning into continuous hidden states, but consistently fall short of their explicit counterparts. We suggest that this is due to purely linguistic latent representations compressing a symbolic abstraction of the world, rather than the causal dynamics that actually govern driving. Thus, we present OneVL (One-step latent reasoning and planning with Vision-Language explanations), a unified VLA and World Model framework that routes reasoning through compact latent tokens supervised by dual auxiliary decoders. Alongside a language decoder that reconstructs text CoT, we introduce a visual world model decoder that predicts future-frame tokens, forcing the latent space to internalize the causal dynamics of road geometry, agent motion, and environmental change. A three-stage training pipeline progressively aligns these latents with trajectory, language, and visual objectives, ensuring stable joint optimization. At inference, the auxiliary decoders are discarded and all latent tokens are prefilled in a single parallel pass, matching the speed of answer-only prediction. Across four benchmarks, OneVL becomes the first latent CoT method to surpass explicit CoT, delivering state-of-the-art accuracy at answer-only latency, and providing direct evidence that tighter compression, when guided in both language and world-model supervision, produces more generalizable representations than verbose token-by-token reasoning. Project Page: https://xiaomi-embodied-intelligence.github.io/OneVL", "upvotes": 65, "discussionId": "69e6e8be76b653026bd83d4f", "projectPage": "https://xiaomi-embodied-intelligence.github.io/OneVL/", "ai_summary": "OneVL presents a unified vision-language-action framework that improves latent chain-of-thought reasoning for autonomous driving by integrating language and visual world model supervision for faster, more accurate trajectory prediction.", "ai_keywords": ["chain-of-thought", "latent CoT", "vision-language action", "world model", "auxiliary decoders", "visual world model decoder", "language decoder", "trajectory prediction", "three-stage training pipeline", "latent tokens", "parallel pass", "autoregressive nature"], "organization": {"_id": "6821ba7e5a7efab94a235406", "name": "xiaomi-research", "fullname": "Xiaomi Research", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/673735e4373ad40af7f81ea1/DR4m0bz2Du1l0Z8Txg351.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u94fe\u5f0f\u601d\u7ef4\uff08CoT\uff09\u63a8\u7406\u5728\u81ea\u4e3b\u9a7e\u9a76\u7684\u8f68\u8ff9\u9884\u6d4b\u4e2d\u975e\u5e38\u6709\u6548\uff0c\u4f46\u5176\u81ea\u56de\u5f52\u7279\u6027\u5bfc\u81f4\u5b9e\u65f6\u90e8\u7f72\u65f6\u5b58\u5728\u5ef6\u8fdf\u95ee\u9898\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6f5c\u5728CoT\u65b9\u6cd5\u8bd5\u56fe\u901a\u8fc7\u538b\u7f29\u63a8\u7406\u4e3a\u8fde\u7eed\u7684\u9690\u85cf\u72b6\u6001\u6765\u89e3\u51b3\u8fd9\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u4f46\u6548\u679c\u4e0d\u5982\u663e\u5f0f\u65b9\u6cd5\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86OneVL\uff0c\u8fd9\u662f\u4e00\u79cd\u7ed3\u5408\u89c6\u89c9-\u8bed\u8a00\uff08VLA\uff09\u548c\u4e16\u754c\u6a21\u578b\u7684\u6846\u67b6\uff0c\u901a\u8fc7\u7d27\u51d1\u7684\u6f5c\u5728\u6807\u8bb0\u8fdb\u884c\u63a8\u7406\u3002</li>\n    <li>OneVL\u540c\u65f6\u4f7f\u7528\u8bed\u8a00\u89e3\u7801\u5668\u548c\u89c6\u89c9\u4e16\u754c\u6a21\u578b\u89e3\u7801\u5668\u6765\u9884\u6d4b\u672a\u6765\u5e27\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u8ba9\u6f5c\u5728\u7a7a\u95f4\u80fd\u591f\u5185\u5316\u5b9e\u9645\u7684\u56e0\u679c\u52a8\u6001\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5728\u56db\u4e2a\u57fa\u51c6\u6d4b\u8bd5\u4e2d\uff0cOneVL\u6210\u4e3a\u9996\u4e2a\u5728\u7b54\u6848\u5ef6\u8fdf\u4e0b\u8d85\u8fc7\u663e\u5f0fCoT\u7684\u65b9\u6cd5\uff0c\u63d0\u4f9b\u4e86\u66f4\u5177\u901a\u7528\u6027\u7684\u8868\u793a\u80fd\u529b\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Chain-of-Thought (CoT) reasoning helps predict trajectories in autonomous driving but is slow for real-time use.</li>\n    <li>Latent CoT methods are faster but often don't perform as well as explicit methods because they focus too much on language rather than real-world dynamics.</li>\n    <li>OneVL introduces a new framework that combines Vision-Language explanations with world modeling to improve reasoning and planning.</li>\n    <li>It uses two decoders: one for language and another for predicting future scenarios based on the driving environment.</li>\n    <li>OneVL shows better accuracy than previous methods while maintaining fast prediction speeds, proving that combining language and world-modeling helps create better representations.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-19T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "OneVL: One-Step Latent Reasoning and Planning with Vision-Language Explanation", "summary": "Chain-of-Thought (CoT) reasoning has become a powerful driver of trajectory prediction in VLA-based autonomous driving, yet its autoregressive nature imposes a latency cost that is prohibitive for real-time deployment. Latent CoT methods attempt to close this gap by compressing reasoning into continuous hidden states, but consistently fall short of their explicit counterparts. We suggest that this is due to purely linguistic latent representations compressing a symbolic abstraction of the world, rather than the causal dynamics that actually govern driving. Thus, we present OneVL (One-step latent reasoning and planning with Vision-Language explanations), a unified VLA and World Model framework that routes reasoning through compact latent tokens supervised by dual auxiliary decoders. Alongside a language decoder that reconstructs text CoT, we introduce a visual world model decoder that predicts future-frame tokens, forcing the latent space to internalize the causal dynamics of road geometry, agent motion, and environmental change. A three-stage training pipeline progressively aligns these latents with trajectory, language, and visual objectives, ensuring stable joint optimization. At inference, the auxiliary decoders are discarded and all latent tokens are prefilled in a single parallel pass, matching the speed of answer-only prediction. Across four benchmarks, OneVL becomes the first latent CoT method to surpass explicit CoT, delivering state-of-the-art accuracy at answer-only latency, and providing direct evidence that tighter compression, when guided in both language and world-model supervision, produces more generalizable representations than verbose token-by-token reasoning. Project Page: https://xiaomi-embodied-intelligence.github.io/OneVL", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.18486.png", "numComments": 2, "submittedBy": {"_id": "62df78222d89ce551ce0f71d", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/89fba294cff2d2f941d121c1923e4c76.svg", "fullname": "Lingdong Kong", "name": "ldkong", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 6, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "6821ba7e5a7efab94a235406", "name": "xiaomi-research", "fullname": "Xiaomi Research", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/673735e4373ad40af7f81ea1/DR4m0bz2Du1l0Z8Txg351.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.18292", "authors": [{"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d00", "user": {"_id": "61cd4b833dd34ba1985e0753", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/61cd4b833dd34ba1985e0753/BfHfrwotoMESpXZOHiIe4.png", "isPro": false, "fullname": "KABI", "user": "dongguanting", "type": "user", "name": "dongguanting"}, "name": "Guanting Dong", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-21T14:16:06.370Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d01", "name": "Junting Lu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d02", "name": "Junjie Huang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d03", "name": "Wanjun Zhong", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d04", "name": "Longxiang Liu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d05", "user": {"_id": "64ce05c631c655ff8a2e183c", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/f2de7f8a1348b05f46946085e3e9718e.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Shijue Huang", "user": "JoeYing", "type": "user", "name": "JoeYing"}, "name": "Shijue Huang", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-21T14:16:03.551Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d06", "name": "Zhenyu Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d07", "name": "Yang Zhao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d08", "name": "Xiaoshuai Song", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d09", "name": "Xiaoxi Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d0a", "name": "Jiajie Jin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d0b", "name": "Yutao Zhu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d0c", "name": "Hanbin Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d0d", "name": "Fangyu Lei", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d0e", "name": "Qinyu Luo", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d0f", "name": "Mingyang Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d10", "name": "Zehui Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d11", "name": "Jiazhan Feng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d12", "name": "Ji-Rong Wen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d13", "name": "Zhicheng Dou", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-20T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-21T02:01:56.026Z", "title": "Agent-World: Scaling Real-World Environment Synthesis for Evolving General Agent Intelligence", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "61cd4b833dd34ba1985e0753", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/61cd4b833dd34ba1985e0753/BfHfrwotoMESpXZOHiIe4.png", "isPro": false, "fullname": "KABI", "user": "dongguanting", "type": "user", "name": "dongguanting"}, "summary": "Large language models are increasingly expected to serve as general-purpose agents that interact with external, stateful tool environments. The Model Context Protocol (MCP) and broader agent skills offer a unified interface for connecting agents with scalable real-world services, but training robust agents remains limited by the lack of realistic environments and principled mechanisms for life-long learning. In this paper, we present Agent-World, a self-evolving training arena for advancing general agent intelligence through scalable environments. Agent-World has two main components: (1) Agentic Environment-Task Discovery, which autonomously explores topic-aligned databases and executable tool ecosystems from thousands of real-world environment themes and synthesizes verifiable tasks with controllable difficulty; and (2) Continuous Self-Evolving Agent Training, which combines multi-environment reinforcement learning with a self-evolving agent arena that automatically identifies capability gaps through dynamic task synthesis and drives targeted learning, enabling the co-evolution of agent policies and environments. Across 23 challenging agent benchmarks, Agent-World-8B and 14B consistently outperforms strong proprietary models and environment scaling baselines. Further analyses reveal scaling trends in relation to environment diversity and self-evolution rounds, offering insights for building general agent intelligence.", "upvotes": 61, "discussionId": "69e6e86076b653026bd83d14", "projectPage": "https://agent-tars-world.github.io/-/", "ai_summary": "Agent-World introduces a self-evolving training framework that advances general agent intelligence through autonomous environment discovery and continuous learning across diverse real-world scenarios.", "ai_keywords": ["Model Context Protocol", "agent skills", "self-evolving training arena", "agentic environment-task discovery", "continuous self-evolving agent training", "multi-environment reinforcement learning", "dynamic task synthesis", "co-evolution of agent policies and environments"], "organization": {"_id": "67d1140985ea0644e2f14b99", "name": "ByteDance-Seed", "fullname": "ByteDance Seed", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6535c9e88bde2fae19b6fb25/flkDUqd_YEuFsjeNET3r-.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u5927\u578b\u8bed\u8a00\u6a21\u578b\u88ab\u671f\u671b\u80fd\u4f5c\u4e3a\u901a\u7528\u667a\u80fd\u4f53\u4e0e\u5916\u90e8\u5de5\u5177\u73af\u5883\u4e92\u52a8\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u63d0\u51fa\u7684Agent-World\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u81ea\u6211\u8fdb\u5316\u7684\u8bad\u7ec3\u5e73\u53f0\uff0c\u65e8\u5728\u901a\u8fc7\u53ef\u6269\u5c55\u73af\u5883\u63d0\u5347\u667a\u80fd\u4f53\u7684\u667a\u80fd\u3002</li>\n    <li>Agent-World\u5305\u542b\u4e24\u4e2a\u4e3b\u8981\u90e8\u5206\uff1a\u73af\u5883\u4efb\u52a1\u53d1\u73b0\u548c\u6301\u7eed\u81ea\u6211\u8fdb\u5316\u7684\u667a\u80fd\u4f53\u8bad\u7ec3\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8be5\u5e73\u53f0\u80fd\u591f\u81ea\u52a8\u63a2\u7d22\u6570\u636e\u5e93\uff0c\u751f\u6210\u53ef\u63a7\u96be\u5ea6\u7684\u4efb\u52a1\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u4fc3\u8fdb\u667a\u80fd\u4f53\u7684\u5b66\u4e60\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u572823\u4e2a\u6311\u6218\u6027\u57fa\u51c6\u6d4b\u8bd5\u4e2d\uff0cAgent-World\u6a21\u578b\u8868\u73b0\u4f18\u4e8e\u5f3a\u5927\u7684\u4e13\u6709\u6a21\u578b\u548c\u73af\u5883\u6269\u5c55\u57fa\u51c6\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Large language models are being developed to act as versatile agents that can work with various real-world tools.</li>\n    <li>The Model Context Protocol (MCP) helps connect these agents to scalable services, but better training environments are needed.</li>\n    <li>Agent-World is introduced as a training platform that helps improve agent intelligence by creating realistic environments.</li>\n    <li>It has two main features: discovering tasks from real-world themes and continuously training agents to improve their skills.</li>\n    <li>Agent-World outperformed existing models in challenging benchmarks, providing insights for enhancing agent intelligence.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-19T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "Agent-World: Scaling Real-World Environment Synthesis for Evolving General Agent Intelligence", "summary": "Large language models are increasingly expected to serve as general-purpose agents that interact with external, stateful tool environments. The Model Context Protocol (MCP) and broader agent skills offer a unified interface for connecting agents with scalable real-world services, but training robust agents remains limited by the lack of realistic environments and principled mechanisms for life-long learning. In this paper, we present Agent-World, a self-evolving training arena for advancing general agent intelligence through scalable environments. Agent-World has two main components: (1) Agentic Environment-Task Discovery, which autonomously explores topic-aligned databases and executable tool ecosystems from thousands of real-world environment themes and synthesizes verifiable tasks with controllable difficulty; and (2) Continuous Self-Evolving Agent Training, which combines multi-environment reinforcement learning with a self-evolving agent arena that automatically identifies capability gaps through dynamic task synthesis and drives targeted learning, enabling the co-evolution of agent policies and environments. Across 23 challenging agent benchmarks, Agent-World-8B and 14B consistently outperforms strong proprietary models and environment scaling baselines. Further analyses reveal scaling trends in relation to environment diversity and self-evolution rounds, offering insights for building general agent intelligence.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.18292.png", "numComments": 2, "submittedBy": {"_id": "61cd4b833dd34ba1985e0753", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/61cd4b833dd34ba1985e0753/BfHfrwotoMESpXZOHiIe4.png", "fullname": "KABI", "name": "dongguanting", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 72, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "67d1140985ea0644e2f14b99", "name": "ByteDance-Seed", "fullname": "ByteDance Seed", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6535c9e88bde2fae19b6fb25/flkDUqd_YEuFsjeNET3r-.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": true}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.19636", "authors": [{"_id": "69e830e25f6b3d4e5af9ab8d", "user": {"_id": "668df98de9e585e8718f767f", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/2be52f4ae88a0991c8ae584f8e870734.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Xiangyang Luo", "user": "XiangyangLuo02", "type": "user", "name": "XiangyangLuo02"}, "name": "Xiangyang Luo", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-22T07:20:51.893Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e830e25f6b3d4e5af9ab8e", "user": {"_id": "6628717c9176f1c30508f0dc", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/59386be57360b9e6883a18e3d7211429.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "george", "user": "georgexin", "type": "user", "name": "georgexin"}, "name": "Xiaozhe Xin", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-22T07:21:03.262Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e830e25f6b3d4e5af9ab8f", "name": "Tao Feng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e830e25f6b3d4e5af9ab90", "user": {"_id": "67d50738fed7787297d737d6", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/30d7126f7c3feda732c5783ea3db9c7f.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "xuguo", "user": "XuGuo699", "type": "user", "name": "XuGuo699"}, "name": "Xu Guo", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-22T07:20:49.963Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e830e25f6b3d4e5af9ab91", "name": "Meiguang Jin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e830e25f6b3d4e5af9ab92", "name": "Junfeng Ma", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/67d50738fed7787297d737d6/NEsqk-w2bp0Kuwqu8kKyJ.mp4"], "publishedAt": "2026-04-21T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-22T01:07:24.586Z", "title": "CoInteract: Physically-Consistent Human-Object Interaction Video Synthesis via Spatially-Structured Co-Generation", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "67d50738fed7787297d737d6", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/30d7126f7c3feda732c5783ea3db9c7f.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "xuguo", "user": "XuGuo699", "type": "user", "name": "XuGuo699"}, "summary": "Synthesizing human--object interaction (HOI) videos has broad practical value in e-commerce, digital advertising, and virtual marketing. However, current diffusion models, despite their photorealistic rendering capability, still frequently fail on (i) the structural stability of sensitive regions such as hands and faces and (ii) physically plausible contact (e.g., avoiding hand--object interpenetration). We present CoInteract, an end-to-end framework for HOI video synthesis conditioned on a person reference image, a product reference image, text prompts, and speech audio. CoInteract introduces two complementary designs embedded into a Diffusion Transformer (DiT) backbone. First, we propose a Human-Aware Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) that routes tokens to lightweight, region-specialized experts via spatially supervised routing, improving fine-grained structural fidelity with minimal parameter overhead. Second, we propose Spatially-Structured Co-Generation, a dual-stream training paradigm that jointly models an RGB appearance stream and an auxiliary HOI structure stream to inject interaction geometry priors. During training, the HOI stream attends to RGB tokens and its supervision regularizes shared backbone weights; at inference, the HOI branch is removed for zero-overhead RGB generation. Experimental results demonstrate that CoInteract significantly outperforms existing methods in structural stability, logical consistency, and interaction realism.", "upvotes": 59, "discussionId": "69e830e25f6b3d4e5af9ab93", "projectPage": "https://xinxiaozhe12345.github.io/CoInteract_Project/", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/luoxyhappy/CoInteract", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "CoInteract presents an end-to-end framework for human-object interaction video synthesis using a Diffusion Transformer backbone with specialized modules for structural stability and physical plausibility.", "ai_keywords": ["Diffusion Transformer", "Human-Aware Mixture-of-Experts", "spatially supervised routing", "region-specialized experts", "Spatially-Structured Co-Generation", "dual-stream training paradigm", "RGB appearance stream", "HOI structure stream", "interaction geometry priors"], "githubStars": 44, "organization": {"_id": "64488b334988ee01f2a8d856", "name": "alibaba-inc", "fullname": "alibaba-inc", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/61ac8f8a00d01045fca0ad2f/MX4wxQVaFm1A1wqnrL2WU.jpeg"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>CoInteract\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u7528\u4e8e\u5408\u6210\u4eba-\u7269\u4f53\u4e92\u52a8\u89c6\u9891\u7684\u6846\u67b6\uff0c\u9002\u7528\u4e8e\u7535\u5546\u548c\u865a\u62df\u8425\u9500\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8be5\u6846\u67b6\u89e3\u51b3\u4e86\u73b0\u6709\u6a21\u578b\u5728\u624b\u90e8\u548c\u9762\u90e8\u7ed3\u6784\u7a33\u5b9a\u6027\u4ee5\u53ca\u7269\u7406\u63a5\u89e6\u5408\u7406\u6027\u65b9\u9762\u7684\u4e0d\u8db3\u3002</li>\n    <li>CoInteract\u7ed3\u5408\u4e86\u4eba\u7c7b\u611f\u77e5\u7684\u4e13\u5bb6\u7cfb\u7edf\u548c\u7a7a\u95f4\u7ed3\u6784\u7684\u5171\u540c\u751f\u6210\u65b9\u6cd5\uff0c\u4ee5\u63d0\u9ad8\u7ec6\u8282\u8868\u73b0\u548c\u4e92\u52a8\u771f\u5b9e\u6027\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5728\u8bad\u7ec3\u65f6\uff0c\u6846\u67b6\u901a\u8fc7RGB\u548c\u4e92\u52a8\u7ed3\u6784\u6d41\u7684\u53cc\u91cd\u5efa\u6a21\u6765\u6ce8\u5165\u4e92\u52a8\u51e0\u4f55\u5148\u9a8c\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5b9e\u9a8c\u7ed3\u679c\u8868\u660e\uff0cCoInteract\u5728\u7ed3\u6784\u7a33\u5b9a\u6027\u3001\u903b\u8f91\u4e00\u81f4\u6027\u548c\u4e92\u52a8\u771f\u5b9e\u611f\u65b9\u9762\u663e\u8457\u4f18\u4e8e\u73b0\u6709\u65b9\u6cd5\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>CoInteract is a new system for creating videos of people interacting with objects, useful for e-commerce and marketing.</li>\n    <li>Current video models struggle with realistic hand and face movements and proper contact between hands and objects.</li>\n    <li>CoInteract uses a special framework that combines different expert models to improve detail and accuracy in video synthesis.</li>\n    <li>It also includes a dual training approach to ensure both appearance and interaction geometry are accurately represented.</li>\n    <li>Tests show CoInteract performs better than existing methods in terms of stability, consistency, and realism of interactions.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-20T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "CoInteract: Physically-Consistent Human-Object Interaction Video Synthesis via Spatially-Structured Co-Generation", "summary": "Synthesizing human--object interaction (HOI) videos has broad practical value in e-commerce, digital advertising, and virtual marketing. However, current diffusion models, despite their photorealistic rendering capability, still frequently fail on (i) the structural stability of sensitive regions such as hands and faces and (ii) physically plausible contact (e.g., avoiding hand--object interpenetration). We present CoInteract, an end-to-end framework for HOI video synthesis conditioned on a person reference image, a product reference image, text prompts, and speech audio. CoInteract introduces two complementary designs embedded into a Diffusion Transformer (DiT) backbone. First, we propose a Human-Aware Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) that routes tokens to lightweight, region-specialized experts via spatially supervised routing, improving fine-grained structural fidelity with minimal parameter overhead. Second, we propose Spatially-Structured Co-Generation, a dual-stream training paradigm that jointly models an RGB appearance stream and an auxiliary HOI structure stream to inject interaction geometry priors. During training, the HOI stream attends to RGB tokens and its supervision regularizes shared backbone weights; at inference, the HOI branch is removed for zero-overhead RGB generation. Experimental results demonstrate that CoInteract significantly outperforms existing methods in structural stability, logical consistency, and interaction realism.", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/67d50738fed7787297d737d6/NEsqk-w2bp0Kuwqu8kKyJ.mp4"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.19636.png", "numComments": 3, "submittedBy": {"_id": "67d50738fed7787297d737d6", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/30d7126f7c3feda732c5783ea3db9c7f.svg", "fullname": "xuguo", "name": "XuGuo699", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 14, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "64488b334988ee01f2a8d856", "name": "alibaba-inc", "fullname": "alibaba-inc", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/61ac8f8a00d01045fca0ad2f/MX4wxQVaFm1A1wqnrL2WU.jpeg"}, "isAuthorParticipating": true}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.18394", "authors": [{"_id": "69e7021276b653026bd83eb4", "name": "Yilei Jiang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e7021276b653026bd83eb5", "name": "Jinyuan Hu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e7021276b653026bd83eb6", "name": "Qianyin Xiao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e7021276b653026bd83eb7", "user": {"_id": "6836a2eb648698b112bd8be6", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/8e2e2065f380ba9fdbb42b12c27feb73.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "ZHENG Yaozhi", "user": "Jimmyzheng-10", "type": "user", "name": "Jimmyzheng-10"}, "name": "Yaozhi Zheng", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-21T14:00:25.222Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e7021276b653026bd83eb8", "name": "Ruize Ma", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e7021276b653026bd83eb9", "name": "Kaituo Feng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e7021276b653026bd83eba", "name": "Jiaming Han", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e7021276b653026bd83ebb", "name": "Tianshuo Peng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e7021276b653026bd83ebc", "name": "Kaixuan Fan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e7021276b653026bd83ebd", "name": "Manyuan Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e7021276b653026bd83ebe", "name": "Xiangyu Yue", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/62318c0386753f5f41d0e261/LlP3Oh9ts9lG7KB8ypINN.mp4"], "publishedAt": "2026-04-20T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-21T03:26:21.704Z", "title": "OpenGame: Open Agentic Coding for Games", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "62318c0386753f5f41d0e261", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/62318c0386753f5f41d0e261/xO_5PvOf7lXhQPnQLcmnq.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Jiaming Han", "user": "csuhan", "type": "user", "name": "csuhan"}, "summary": "Game development sits at the intersection of creative design and intricate software engineering, demanding the joint orchestration of game engines, real-time loops, and tightly coupled state across many files. While Large Language Models (LLMs) and code agents now solve isolated programming tasks with ease, they consistently stumble when asked to produce a fully playable game from a high-level design, collapsing under cross-file inconsistencies, broken scene wiring, and logical incoherence. We bridge this gap with OpenGame, the first open-source agentic framework explicitly designed for end-to-end web game creation. At its core lies Game Skill, a reusable, evolving capability composed of a Template Skill that grows a library of project skeletons from experience and a Debug Skill that maintains a living protocol of verified fixes - together enabling the agent to scaffold stable architectures and systematically repair integration errors rather than patch isolated syntax bugs. Powering this framework is GameCoder-27B, a code LLM specialized for game engine mastery through a three-stage pipeline of continual pre-training, supervised fine-tuning, and execution-grounded reinforcement learning. Since verifying interactive playability is fundamentally harder than checking static code, we further introduce OpenGame-Bench, an evaluation pipeline that scores agentic game generation along Build Health, Visual Usability, and Intent Alignment via headless browser execution and VLM judging. Across 150 diverse game prompts, OpenGame establishes a new state-of-the-art. We hope OpenGame pushes code agents beyond discrete software engineering problems and toward building complex, interactive real-world applications. Our framework will be fully open-sourced.", "upvotes": 49, "discussionId": "69e7021276b653026bd83ebf", "projectPage": "https://www.opengame-project-page.com/", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/leigest519/OpenGame", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "OpenGame is an open-source agentic framework for end-to-end web game creation that uses specialized code models and evaluation benchmarks to overcome challenges in interactive application development.", "ai_keywords": ["Large Language Models", "code agents", "game engines", "real-time loops", "cross-file inconsistencies", "scene wiring", "logical incoherence", "Game Skill", "Template Skill", "Debug Skill", "GameCoder-27B", "continual pre-training", "supervised fine-tuning", "execution-grounded reinforcement learning", "OpenGame-Bench", "Build Health", "Visual Usability", "Intent Alignment", "headless browser execution", "VLM judging"], "githubStars": 67, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u6e38\u620f\u5f00\u53d1\u7ed3\u5408\u4e86\u521b\u610f\u8bbe\u8ba1\u548c\u590d\u6742\u7684\u8f6f\u4ef6\u5de5\u7a0b\uff0c\u9700\u8981\u534f\u8c03\u6e38\u620f\u5f15\u64ce\u548c\u5b9e\u65f6\u5faa\u73af\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u867d\u7136\u5927\u578b\u8bed\u8a00\u6a21\u578b\uff08LLMs\uff09\u53ef\u4ee5\u8f7b\u677e\u89e3\u51b3\u5b64\u7acb\u7684\u7f16\u7a0b\u4efb\u52a1\uff0c\u4f46\u5728\u4ece\u9ad8\u5c42\u8bbe\u8ba1\u5236\u4f5c\u5b8c\u6574\u53ef\u73a9\u6e38\u620f\u65f6\u8868\u73b0\u4e0d\u4f73\u3002</li>\n    <li>OpenGame\u662f\u7b2c\u4e00\u4e2a\u4e13\u4e3a\u7aef\u5230\u7aef\u7f51\u9875\u6e38\u620f\u521b\u4f5c\u8bbe\u8ba1\u7684\u5f00\u6e90\u6846\u67b6\uff0c\u80fd\u89e3\u51b3\u8de8\u6587\u4ef6\u4e0d\u4e00\u81f4\u6027\u7b49\u95ee\u9898\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6846\u67b6\u6838\u5fc3\u662fGame Skill\uff0c\u5305\u62ec\u4e00\u4e2a\u4ece\u7ecf\u9a8c\u4e2d\u6210\u957f\u7684\u6a21\u677f\u6280\u80fd\u548c\u4e00\u4e2a\u4fdd\u6301\u9a8c\u8bc1\u4fee\u590d\u7684\u8c03\u8bd5\u6280\u80fd\u3002</li>\n    <li>OpenGame-Bench\u8bc4\u4f30\u751f\u6210\u7684\u6e38\u620f\u8d28\u91cf\uff0c\u57fa\u4e8e\u6784\u5efa\u5065\u5eb7\u3001\u89c6\u89c9\u53ef\u7528\u6027\u548c\u610f\u56fe\u4e00\u81f4\u6027\uff0c\u5c55\u793a\u4e86\u65b0\u7684\u6280\u672f\u6c34\u5e73\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Game development combines creative design and complex software engineering, which makes it challenging for current AI tools to create complete games from high-level designs.</li>\n    <li>OpenGame is a new open-source framework designed for building web games from start to finish, addressing issues that AI faces in game creation.</li>\n    <li>The framework includes Game Skill, which helps organize projects and fix errors systematically, instead of just correcting small coding mistakes.</li>\n    <li>GameCoder-27B is a specialized AI model that improves game engine coding through a unique training process.</li>\n    <li>OpenGame-Bench evaluates the quality of generated games through specific criteria and has set a new standard in game generation, with plans to make the framework publicly available.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-19T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "OpenGame: Open Agentic Coding for Games", "summary": "Game development sits at the intersection of creative design and intricate software engineering, demanding the joint orchestration of game engines, real-time loops, and tightly coupled state across many files. While Large Language Models (LLMs) and code agents now solve isolated programming tasks with ease, they consistently stumble when asked to produce a fully playable game from a high-level design, collapsing under cross-file inconsistencies, broken scene wiring, and logical incoherence. We bridge this gap with OpenGame, the first open-source agentic framework explicitly designed for end-to-end web game creation. At its core lies Game Skill, a reusable, evolving capability composed of a Template Skill that grows a library of project skeletons from experience and a Debug Skill that maintains a living protocol of verified fixes - together enabling the agent to scaffold stable architectures and systematically repair integration errors rather than patch isolated syntax bugs. Powering this framework is GameCoder-27B, a code LLM specialized for game engine mastery through a three-stage pipeline of continual pre-training, supervised fine-tuning, and execution-grounded reinforcement learning. Since verifying interactive playability is fundamentally harder than checking static code, we further introduce OpenGame-Bench, an evaluation pipeline that scores agentic game generation along Build Health, Visual Usability, and Intent Alignment via headless browser execution and VLM judging. Across 150 diverse game prompts, OpenGame establishes a new state-of-the-art. We hope OpenGame pushes code agents beyond discrete software engineering problems and toward building complex, interactive real-world applications. Our framework will be fully open-sourced.", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/62318c0386753f5f41d0e261/LlP3Oh9ts9lG7KB8ypINN.mp4"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.18394.png", "numComments": 1, "submittedBy": {"_id": "62318c0386753f5f41d0e261", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/62318c0386753f5f41d0e261/xO_5PvOf7lXhQPnQLcmnq.jpeg", "fullname": "Jiaming Han", "name": "csuhan", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 29, "isUserFollowing": false}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.20733", "authors": [{"_id": "69e9b358d49e77f7389b4196", "name": "Chuanyu Qin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e9b358d49e77f7389b4197", "name": "Chenxu Yang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e9b358d49e77f7389b4198", "name": "Qingyi Si", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e9b358d49e77f7389b4199", "name": "Naibin Gu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e9b358d49e77f7389b419a", "name": "Dingyu Yao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e9b358d49e77f7389b419b", "name": "Zheng Lin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e9b358d49e77f7389b419c", "name": "Peng Fu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e9b358d49e77f7389b419d", "name": "Nan Duan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e9b358d49e77f7389b419e", "name": "Jiaqi Wang", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-22T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-23T04:24:20.928Z", "title": "Near-Future Policy Optimization", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "66f4d2b62dc07e76a1dc464b", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/b1884b750a6ec46a83d247e933d59d63.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "steven young", "user": "iieycx", "type": "user", "name": "iieycx"}, "summary": "Reinforcement learning with verifiable rewards (RLVR) has become a core post-training recipe. Introducing suitable off-policy trajectories into on-policy exploration accelerates RLVR convergence and raises the performance ceiling, yet finding a source of such trajectories remains the key challenge. Existing mixed-policy methods either import trajectories from external teachers (high-quality but distributionally far) or replay past training trajectories (close but capped in quality), and neither simultaneously satisfies the strong enough (higher Q , more new knowledge to learn) and close enough (lower V , more readily absorbed) conditions required to maximize the effective learning signal S = Q/V. We propose Near-Future Policy Optimization (NPO), a simple mixed-policy scheme that learns from a policy's own near-future self: a later checkpoint from the same training run is a natural source of auxiliary trajectories that is both stronger than the current policy and closer than any external source, directly balancing trajectory quality against variance cost. We validate NPO through two manual interventions, early-stage bootstrapping and late-stage plateau breakthrough, and further propose AutoNPO,an adaptive variant that automatically triggers interventions from online training signals and selects the guide checkpoint that maximizes S. On Qwen3-VL-8B-Instruct with GRPO, NPO improves average performance from 57.88 to 62.84, and AutoNPO pushes it to 63.15, raising the final performance ceiling while accelerating convergence.", "upvotes": 44, "discussionId": "69e9b359d49e77f7389b419f", "ai_summary": "Mixed-policy reinforcement learning approach using near-future policy optimization to accelerate convergence and improve performance by balancing trajectory quality and variance.", "ai_keywords": ["reinforcement learning", "verifiable rewards", "off-policy trajectories", "on-policy exploration", "mixed-policy methods", "policy optimization", "Q-value", "value function", "effective learning signal", "bootstrapping", "plateau breakthrough", "adaptive variants", "online training signals"], "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u5f3a\u5316\u5b66\u4e60\u4e0e\u53ef\u9a8c\u8bc1\u5956\u52b1\uff08RLVR\uff09\u5df2\u6210\u4e3a\u6838\u5fc3\u7684\u8bad\u7ec3\u540e\u65b9\u6cd5\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5f15\u5165\u9002\u5408\u7684\u79bb\u7b56\u7565\u8f68\u8ff9\u53ef\u4ee5\u52a0\u901fRLVR\u7684\u6536\u655b\u5e76\u63d0\u9ad8\u6027\u80fd\uff0c\u4f46\u627e\u5230\u8fd9\u4e9b\u8f68\u8ff9\u7684\u6765\u6e90\u662f\u4e3b\u8981\u6311\u6218\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u73b0\u6709\u65b9\u6cd5\u8981\u4e48\u662f\u4ece\u5916\u90e8\u6559\u5e08\u5f15\u5165\u9ad8\u8d28\u91cf\u7684\u8f68\u8ff9\uff0c\u8981\u4e48\u662f\u91cd\u653e\u8fc7\u53bb\u7684\u8bad\u7ec3\u8f68\u8ff9\uff0c\u4f46\u4e24\u8005\u90fd\u65e0\u6cd5\u540c\u65f6\u6ee1\u8db3\u5f3a\u5ea6\u548c\u63a5\u8fd1\u5ea6\u7684\u8981\u6c42\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86\u8fd1\u672a\u6765\u7b56\u7565\u4f18\u5316\uff08NPO\uff09\uff0c\u901a\u8fc7\u540c\u4e00\u8bad\u7ec3\u8fc7\u7a0b\u4e2d\u7684\u540e\u671f\u68c0\u67e5\u70b9\u5b66\u4e60\uff0c\u83b7\u5f97\u65e2\u5f3a\u53c8\u8fd1\u7684\u8f85\u52a9\u8f68\u8ff9\u3002</li>\n    <li>NPO\u5728Qwen3-VL-8B-Instruct\u4e0a\u5c06\u5e73\u5747\u6027\u80fd\u4ece57.88\u63d0\u9ad8\u523062.84\uff0cAutoNPO\u8fdb\u4e00\u6b65\u63d0\u5347\u81f363.15\uff0c\u52a0\u901f\u6536\u655b\u5e76\u63d0\u9ad8\u6700\u7ec8\u6027\u80fd\u4e0a\u9650\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Reinforcement learning with verifiable rewards (RLVR) is a method that improves learning after training.</li>\n    <li>Using off-policy trajectories helps improve the learning speed and performance but finding the right ones is challenging.</li>\n    <li>Current methods either use high-quality external trajectories or replay past ones, but both have limitations.</li>\n    <li>The proposed Near-Future Policy Optimization (NPO) uses improved trajectories from the same training run, balancing quality and absorption of new knowledge.</li>\n    <li>NPO shows significant performance improvements in tests, and an adaptive version called AutoNPO further enhances results.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-21T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "Near-Future Policy Optimization", "summary": "Reinforcement learning with verifiable rewards (RLVR) has become a core post-training recipe. Introducing suitable off-policy trajectories into on-policy exploration accelerates RLVR convergence and raises the performance ceiling, yet finding a source of such trajectories remains the key challenge. Existing mixed-policy methods either import trajectories from external teachers (high-quality but distributionally far) or replay past training trajectories (close but capped in quality), and neither simultaneously satisfies the strong enough (higher Q , more new knowledge to learn) and close enough (lower V , more readily absorbed) conditions required to maximize the effective learning signal S = Q/V. We propose Near-Future Policy Optimization (NPO), a simple mixed-policy scheme that learns from a policy's own near-future self: a later checkpoint from the same training run is a natural source of auxiliary trajectories that is both stronger than the current policy and closer than any external source, directly balancing trajectory quality against variance cost. We validate NPO through two manual interventions, early-stage bootstrapping and late-stage plateau breakthrough, and further propose AutoNPO,an adaptive variant that automatically triggers interventions from online training signals and selects the guide checkpoint that maximizes S. On Qwen3-VL-8B-Instruct with GRPO, NPO improves average performance from 57.88 to 62.84, and AutoNPO pushes it to 63.15, raising the final performance ceiling while accelerating convergence.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.20733.png", "numComments": 2, "submittedBy": {"_id": "66f4d2b62dc07e76a1dc464b", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/b1884b750a6ec46a83d247e933d59d63.svg", "fullname": "steven young", "name": "iieycx", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 1, "isUserFollowing": false}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.19859", "authors": [{"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b4041", "name": "Venus Team", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b4042", "name": "Sunhao Dai", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b4043", "name": "Yong Deng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b4044", "name": "Jinzhen Lin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b4045", "name": "Yusheng Song", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b4046", "name": "Guoqing Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b4047", "name": "Xiaofeng Wu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b4048", "user": {"_id": "62cfccfa80c9d4ceb2ff43ec", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/4be9e6c06f77d3c8ad2cc6322c11b782.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Yuqi Zhou", "user": "Yuqi-Zhou", "type": "user", "name": "Yuqi-Zhou"}, "name": "Yuqi Zhou", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-23T07:49:52.220Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b4049", "name": "Shuo Yang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b404a", "name": "Zhenzhe Ying", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b404b", "name": "Zhanwei Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b404c", "name": "Changhua Meng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97d4dd49e77f7389b404d", "name": "Weiqiang Wang", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-21T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-23T00:32:32.416Z", "title": "DR-Venus: Towards Frontier Edge-Scale Deep Research Agents with Only 10K Open Data", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "64db88993725f8d9a908c077", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/64db88993725f8d9a908c077/JZEGk0kius6mrANlwOWw9.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Sunhao Dai", "user": "KID-22", "type": "user", "name": "KID-22"}, "summary": "Edge-scale deep research agents based on small language models are attractive for real-world deployment due to their advantages in cost, latency, and privacy. In this work, we study how to train a strong small deep research agent under limited open-data by improving both data quality and data utilization. We present DR-Venus, a frontier 4B deep research agent for edge-scale deployment, built entirely on open data. Our training recipe consists of two stages. In the first stage, we use agentic supervised fine-tuning (SFT) to establish basic agentic capability, combining strict data cleaning with resampling of long-horizon trajectories to improve data quality and utilization. In the second stage, we apply agentic reinforcement learning (RL) to further improve execution reliability on long-horizon deep research tasks. To make RL effective for small agents in this setting, we build on IGPO and design turn-level rewards based on information gain and format-aware regularization, thereby enhancing supervision density and turn-level credit assignment. Built entirely on roughly 10K open-data, DR-Venus-4B significantly outperforms prior agentic models under 9B parameters on multiple deep research benchmarks, while also narrowing the gap to much larger 30B-class systems. Our further analysis shows that 4B agents already possess surprisingly strong performance potential, highlighting both the deployment promise of small models and the value of test-time scaling in this setting. We release our models, code, and key recipes to support reproducible research on edge-scale deep research agents.", "upvotes": 38, "discussionId": "69e97d4ed49e77f7389b404e", "projectPage": "https://huggingface.co/collections/inclusionAI/dr-venus", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/inclusionAI/DR-Venus", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "DR-Venus-4B is a 4-billion-parameter deep research agent trained entirely on open data using agentic supervised fine-tuning and reinforcement learning with turn-level rewards to achieve superior performance on research benchmarks while maintaining edge-scale deployment advantages.", "ai_keywords": ["agentic supervised fine-tuning", "agentic reinforcement learning", "information gain", "format-aware regularization", "turn-level rewards", "deep research agent", "edge-scale deployment", "test-time scaling"], "githubStars": 35, "organization": {"_id": "67aea5c8f086ab0f70ed97c9", "name": "inclusionAI", "fullname": "inclusionAI", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/662e1f9da266499277937d33/fyKuazRifqiaIO34xrhhm.jpeg"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u7814\u7a76\u5c0f\u578b\u8bed\u8a00\u6a21\u578b\u7684\u6df1\u5ea6\u7814\u7a76\u4ee3\u7406\uff0c\u9002\u5408\u8fb9\u7f18\u8ba1\u7b97\u7684\u5b9e\u9645\u5e94\u7528\uff0c\u5177\u6709\u6210\u672c\u4f4e\u3001\u5ef6\u8fdf\u5c0f\u548c\u9690\u79c1\u4fdd\u62a4\u7684\u4f18\u70b9\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86DR-Venus\uff0c\u4e00\u4e2a\u57fa\u4e8e\u5f00\u653e\u6570\u636e\u76844B\u6df1\u5ea6\u7814\u7a76\u4ee3\u7406\uff0c\u901a\u8fc7\u63d0\u9ad8\u6570\u636e\u8d28\u91cf\u548c\u5229\u7528\u7387\u8fdb\u884c\u8bad\u7ec3\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8bad\u7ec3\u8fc7\u7a0b\u5206\u4e3a\u4e24\u4e2a\u9636\u6bb5\uff1a\u7b2c\u4e00\u9636\u6bb5\u4f7f\u7528\u76d1\u7763\u5fae\u8c03\uff08SFT\uff09\u5efa\u7acb\u57fa\u672c\u80fd\u529b\uff0c\u7b2c\u4e8c\u9636\u6bb5\u5e94\u7528\u5f3a\u5316\u5b66\u4e60\uff08RL\uff09\u63d0\u9ad8\u6267\u884c\u53ef\u9760\u6027\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u901a\u8fc7\u8bbe\u8ba1\u57fa\u4e8e\u4fe1\u606f\u589e\u76ca\u7684\u5956\u52b1\u673a\u5236\uff0c\u4f7f\u5c0f\u578b\u4ee3\u7406\u7684\u5f3a\u5316\u5b66\u4e60\u66f4\u52a0\u6709\u6548\uff0c\u663e\u8457\u63d0\u5347\u4e86\u6027\u80fd\u3002</li>\n    <li>DR-Venus\u5728\u591a\u4e2a\u57fa\u51c6\u6d4b\u8bd5\u4e2d\u8868\u73b0\u4f18\u4e8e\u4e4b\u524d\u76849B\u53c2\u6570\u6a21\u578b\uff0c\u5e76\u4e14\u63a5\u8fd130B\u7ea7\u522b\u7684\u7cfb\u7edf\uff0c\u5c55\u793a\u4e86\u5c0f\u578b\u6a21\u578b\u7684\u6f5c\u529b\u548c\u8fb9\u7f18\u8ba1\u7b97\u7684\u5e94\u7528\u524d\u666f\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>We developed DR-Venus, a small but powerful deep research agent designed for use on edge devices, focusing on cost, speed, and privacy.</li>\n    <li>Training involves two stages: first, improving data quality and usage through supervised fine-tuning, and second, enhancing performance using reinforcement learning.</li>\n    <li>DR-Venus is built using only 10,000 open data samples and performs better than larger models, showing that smaller agents can still be very effective.</li>\n    <li>The model demonstrates strong potential for real-world applications, emphasizing the benefits of using smaller models in research tasks.</li>\n    <li>We have made our models and methods available for others to use and replicate in their own research.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-20T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "DR-Venus: Towards Frontier Edge-Scale Deep Research Agents with Only 10K Open Data", "summary": "Edge-scale deep research agents based on small language models are attractive for real-world deployment due to their advantages in cost, latency, and privacy. In this work, we study how to train a strong small deep research agent under limited open-data by improving both data quality and data utilization. We present DR-Venus, a frontier 4B deep research agent for edge-scale deployment, built entirely on open data. Our training recipe consists of two stages. In the first stage, we use agentic supervised fine-tuning (SFT) to establish basic agentic capability, combining strict data cleaning with resampling of long-horizon trajectories to improve data quality and utilization. In the second stage, we apply agentic reinforcement learning (RL) to further improve execution reliability on long-horizon deep research tasks. To make RL effective for small agents in this setting, we build on IGPO and design turn-level rewards based on information gain and format-aware regularization, thereby enhancing supervision density and turn-level credit assignment. Built entirely on roughly 10K open-data, DR-Venus-4B significantly outperforms prior agentic models under 9B parameters on multiple deep research benchmarks, while also narrowing the gap to much larger 30B-class systems. Our further analysis shows that 4B agents already possess surprisingly strong performance potential, highlighting both the deployment promise of small models and the value of test-time scaling in this setting. We release our models, code, and key recipes to support reproducible research on edge-scale deep research agents.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.19859.png", "numComments": 2, "submittedBy": {"_id": "64db88993725f8d9a908c077", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/64db88993725f8d9a908c077/JZEGk0kius6mrANlwOWw9.jpeg", "fullname": "Sunhao Dai", "name": "KID-22", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 5, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "67aea5c8f086ab0f70ed97c9", "name": "inclusionAI", "fullname": "inclusionAI", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/662e1f9da266499277937d33/fyKuazRifqiaIO34xrhhm.jpeg"}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.18564", "authors": [{"_id": "69e6eada76b653026bd83d66", "user": {"_id": "6590f7880c993129053a2344", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/5cf5c5185d10feeaecd5e8add7c4330d.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Haoyu wu", "user": "Haoyuwu", "type": "user", "name": "Haoyuwu"}, "name": "Haoyu Wu", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-21T14:15:41.328Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6eada76b653026bd83d67", "name": "Jiwen Yu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6eada76b653026bd83d68", "name": "Yingtian Zou", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e6eada76b653026bd83d69", "name": "Xihui Liu", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-20T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-21T01:43:55.153Z", "title": "MultiWorld: Scalable Multi-Agent Multi-View Video World Models", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "6590f7880c993129053a2344", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/5cf5c5185d10feeaecd5e8add7c4330d.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Haoyu wu", "user": "Haoyuwu", "type": "user", "name": "Haoyuwu"}, "summary": "Video world models have achieved remarkable success in simulating environmental dynamics in response to actions by users or agents. They are modeled as action-conditioned video generation models that take historical frames and current actions as input to predict future frames. Yet, most existing approaches are limited to single-agent scenarios and fail to capture the complex interactions inherent in real-world multi-agent systems. We present MultiWorld, a unified framework for multi-agent multi-view world modeling that enables accurate control of multiple agents while maintaining multi-view consistency. We introduce the Multi-Agent Condition Module to achieve precise multi-agent controllability, and the Global State Encoder to ensure coherent observations across different views. MultiWorld supports flexible scaling of agent and view counts, and synthesizes different views in parallel for high efficiency. Experiments on multi-player game environments and multi-robot manipulation tasks demonstrate that MultiWorld outperforms baselines in video fidelity, action-following ability, and multi-view consistency. Project page: https://multi-world.github.io/", "upvotes": 35, "discussionId": "69e6eadb76b653026bd83d6a", "projectPage": "https://multi-world.github.io/", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/CIntellifusion/MultiWorld", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "MultiWorld is a unified framework for multi-agent multi-view world modeling that achieves accurate multi-agent control while maintaining multi-view consistency through specialized modules for condition handling and global state encoding.", "ai_keywords": ["video world models", "action-conditioned video generation", "multi-agent systems", "multi-view consistency", "Multi-Agent Condition Module", "Global State Encoder"], "githubStars": 77, "organization": {"_id": "67ea9ecfc234715db8dbf339", "name": "hkuhk", "fullname": "The University of Hong Kong", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/67ea9e8d2d95c10a0da11b0c/FNnR4M7YqKRuG43N5771B.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u89c6\u9891\u4e16\u754c\u6a21\u578b\u53ef\u4ee5\u6a21\u62df\u73af\u5883\u52a8\u6001\uff0c\u54cd\u5e94\u7528\u6237\u6216\u4ee3\u7406\u7684\u52a8\u4f5c\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u73b0\u6709\u6a21\u578b\u4e3b\u8981\u9002\u7528\u4e8e\u5355\u4ee3\u7406\u573a\u666f\uff0c\u65e0\u6cd5\u6355\u6349\u591a\u4ee3\u7406\u7cfb\u7edf\u4e2d\u7684\u590d\u6742\u4e92\u52a8\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86\u4e00\u4e2a\u540d\u4e3aMultiWorld\u7684\u6846\u67b6\uff0c\u652f\u6301\u591a\u4ee3\u7406\u548c\u591a\u89c6\u89d2\u7684\u4e16\u754c\u5efa\u6a21\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5f15\u5165\u4e86\u591a\u4ee3\u7406\u6761\u4ef6\u6a21\u5757\u548c\u5168\u5c40\u72b6\u6001\u7f16\u7801\u5668\uff0c\u4ee5\u63d0\u9ad8\u591a\u4ee3\u7406\u7684\u53ef\u63a7\u6027\u548c\u4e0d\u540c\u89c6\u89d2\u7684\u4e00\u81f4\u6027\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5b9e\u9a8c\u8868\u660e\uff0cMultiWorld\u5728\u89c6\u9891\u8d28\u91cf\u3001\u52a8\u4f5c\u8ddf\u968f\u80fd\u529b\u548c\u591a\u89c6\u89d2\u4e00\u81f4\u6027\u65b9\u9762\u4f18\u4e8e\u73b0\u6709\u6a21\u578b\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Video world models can simulate how environments change based on user actions.</li>\n    <li>Most current models only work with single agents and can't handle multiple agents interacting.</li>\n    <li>The new framework, MultiWorld, allows for accurate control of multiple agents and consistent views.</li>\n    <li>It includes a special module for controlling multiple agents and maintaining coherence across views.</li>\n    <li>Tests show that MultiWorld performs better in video quality and action tracking compared to existing methods.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-19T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "MultiWorld: Scalable Multi-Agent Multi-View Video World Models", "summary": "Video world models have achieved remarkable success in simulating environmental dynamics in response to actions by users or agents. They are modeled as action-conditioned video generation models that take historical frames and current actions as input to predict future frames. Yet, most existing approaches are limited to single-agent scenarios and fail to capture the complex interactions inherent in real-world multi-agent systems. We present MultiWorld, a unified framework for multi-agent multi-view world modeling that enables accurate control of multiple agents while maintaining multi-view consistency. We introduce the Multi-Agent Condition Module to achieve precise multi-agent controllability, and the Global State Encoder to ensure coherent observations across different views. MultiWorld supports flexible scaling of agent and view counts, and synthesizes different views in parallel for high efficiency. Experiments on multi-player game environments and multi-robot manipulation tasks demonstrate that MultiWorld outperforms baselines in video fidelity, action-following ability, and multi-view consistency. Project page: https://multi-world.github.io/", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.18564.png", "numComments": 2, "submittedBy": {"_id": "6590f7880c993129053a2344", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/5cf5c5185d10feeaecd5e8add7c4330d.svg", "fullname": "Haoyu wu", "name": "Haoyuwu", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 3, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "67ea9ecfc234715db8dbf339", "name": "hkuhk", "fullname": "The University of Hong Kong", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/67ea9e8d2d95c10a0da11b0c/FNnR4M7YqKRuG43N5771B.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": true}],
    "month": [{"paper": {"id": "2603.28032", "authors": [{"_id": "69cb2bce22f9e9dce3fe1e94", "user": {"_id": "68c9076a8afebb210e6de398", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/e418191eb05523e79a9c2e9edee82aa4.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "tianlezeng", "user": "tianlezeng", "type": "user", "name": "tianlezeng"}, "name": "Tianle Zeng", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-03-31T09:28:54.957Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69cb2bce22f9e9dce3fe1e95", "name": "Hanxuan Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69cb2bce22f9e9dce3fe1e96", "name": "Yanci Wen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69cb2bce22f9e9dce3fe1e97", "name": "Hong Zhang", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/68c9076a8afebb210e6de398/FkkB1gx1d2b6ZZkufqm7K.gif"], "publishedAt": "2026-03-30T04:49:29.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-01T00:26:58.369Z", "title": "CARLA-Air: Fly Drones Inside a CARLA World -- A Unified Infrastructure for Air-Ground Embodied Intelligence", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "68c9076a8afebb210e6de398", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/e418191eb05523e79a9c2e9edee82aa4.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "tianlezeng", "user": "tianlezeng", "type": "user", "name": "tianlezeng"}, "summary": "The convergence of low-altitude economies, embodied intelligence, and air-ground cooperative systems creates growing demand for simulation infrastructure capable of jointly modeling aerial and ground agents within a single physically coherent environment. Existing open-source platforms remain domain-segregated: driving simulators lack aerial dynamics, while multirotor simulators lack realistic ground scenes. Bridge-based co-simulation introduces synchronization overhead and cannot guarantee strict spatial-temporal consistency.\n  We present CARLA-Air, an open-source infrastructure that unifies high-fidelity urban driving and physics-accurate multirotor flight within a single Unreal Engine process. The platform preserves both CARLA and AirSim native Python APIs and ROS 2 interfaces, enabling zero-modification code reuse. Within a shared physics tick and rendering pipeline, CARLA-Air delivers photorealistic environments with rule-compliant traffic, socially-aware pedestrians, and aerodynamically consistent UAV dynamics, synchronously capturing up to 18 sensor modalities across all platforms at each tick. The platform supports representative air-ground embodied intelligence workloads spanning cooperation, embodied navigation and vision-language action, multi-modal perception and dataset construction, and reinforcement-learning-based policy training. An extensible asset pipeline allows integration of custom robot platforms into the shared world. By inheriting AirSim's aerial capabilities -- whose upstream development has been archived -- CARLA-Air ensures this widely adopted flight stack continues to evolve within a modern infrastructure.\n  Released with prebuilt binaries and full source: https://github.com/louiszengCN/CarlaAir", "upvotes": 228, "discussionId": "69cb2bcf22f9e9dce3fe1e98", "projectPage": "https://github.com/louiszengCN/CarlaAir", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/louiszengCN/CarlaAir", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": " CARLA-Air integrates high-fidelity driving and multirotor flight simulation within a unified Unreal Engine framework, supporting joint air-ground agent modeling with photorealistic environments and multi-modal sensing capabilities.", "ai_keywords": ["co-simulation", "physics-accurate", "aerodynamic consistency", "sensor modalities", "embodied intelligence", "reinforcement-learning-based policy training", "Unreal Engine", "CARLA", "AirSim", "ROS 2"], "githubStars": 250, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>CARLA-Air \u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u5f00\u6e90\u5e73\u53f0\uff0c\u7ed3\u5408\u4e86\u57ce\u5e02\u9a7e\u9a76\u548c\u591a\u65cb\u7ffc\u98de\u884c\u7684\u6a21\u62df\uff0c\u63d0\u4f9b\u771f\u5b9e\u7684\u7269\u7406\u73af\u5883\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8be5\u5e73\u53f0\u652f\u6301 CARLA \u548c AirSim \u7684\u539f\u751f Python API \u548c ROS 2 \u63a5\u53e3\uff0c\u5141\u8bb8\u7528\u6237\u65e0\u4fee\u6539\u590d\u7528\u4ee3\u7801\u3002</li>\n    <li>CARLA-Air \u80fd\u591f\u540c\u6b65\u6355\u6349\u591a\u8fbe 18 \u79cd\u4f20\u611f\u5668\u6570\u636e\uff0c\u63d0\u4f9b\u7b26\u5408\u89c4\u5219\u7684\u4ea4\u901a\u548c\u793e\u4f1a\u610f\u8bc6\u7684\u884c\u4eba\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8be5\u5e73\u53f0\u652f\u6301\u591a\u79cd\u667a\u80fd\u4efb\u52a1\uff0c\u5305\u62ec\u5408\u4f5c\u3001\u5bfc\u822a\u3001\u89c6\u89c9\u8bed\u8a00\u884c\u52a8\u548c\u5f3a\u5316\u5b66\u4e60\u8bad\u7ec3\u3002</li>\n    <li>CARLA-Air \u5141\u8bb8\u7528\u6237\u5c06\u81ea\u5b9a\u4e49\u673a\u5668\u4eba\u5e73\u53f0\u96c6\u6210\u5230\u5171\u4eab\u73af\u5883\u4e2d\uff0c\u786e\u4fdd\u98de\u884c\u6280\u672f\u7684\u6301\u7eed\u53d1\u5c55\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>CARLA-Air is a new open-source platform that combines realistic driving and flying simulations in one environment.</li>\n    <li>It allows users to use existing code from CARLA and AirSim without any changes, making it easy to integrate and use.</li>\n    <li>The platform features realistic city environments with accurate traffic, pedestrians, and drone physics.</li>\n    <li>It supports various applications like cooperation between air and ground agents, navigation, and training AI models.</li>\n    <li>CARLA-Air is available with prebuilt binaries and source code for developers to use and customize.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-03-30T00:49:29.000Z", "title": "CARLA-Air: Fly Drones Inside a CARLA World -- A Unified Infrastructure for Air-Ground Embodied Intelligence", "summary": "The convergence of low-altitude economies, embodied intelligence, and air-ground cooperative systems creates growing demand for simulation infrastructure capable of jointly modeling aerial and ground agents within a single physically coherent environment. Existing open-source platforms remain domain-segregated: driving simulators lack aerial dynamics, while multirotor simulators lack realistic ground scenes. Bridge-based co-simulation introduces synchronization overhead and cannot guarantee strict spatial-temporal consistency.\n  We present CARLA-Air, an open-source infrastructure that unifies high-fidelity urban driving and physics-accurate multirotor flight within a single Unreal Engine process. The platform preserves both CARLA and AirSim native Python APIs and ROS 2 interfaces, enabling zero-modification code reuse. Within a shared physics tick and rendering pipeline, CARLA-Air delivers photorealistic environments with rule-compliant traffic, socially-aware pedestrians, and aerodynamically consistent UAV dynamics, synchronously capturing up to 18 sensor modalities across all platforms at each tick. The platform supports representative air-ground embodied intelligence workloads spanning cooperation, embodied navigation and vision-language action, multi-modal perception and dataset construction, and reinforcement-learning-based policy training. An extensible asset pipeline allows integration of custom robot platforms into the shared world. By inheriting AirSim's aerial capabilities -- whose upstream development has been archived -- CARLA-Air ensures this widely adopted flight stack continues to evolve within a modern infrastructure.\n  Released with prebuilt binaries and full source: https://github.com/louiszengCN/CarlaAir", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/68c9076a8afebb210e6de398/FkkB1gx1d2b6ZZkufqm7K.gif"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2603.28032.png", "numComments": 2, "submittedBy": {"_id": "68c9076a8afebb210e6de398", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/e418191eb05523e79a9c2e9edee82aa4.svg", "fullname": "tianlezeng", "name": "tianlezeng", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "isUserFollowing": false}, "isAuthorParticipating": true}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.08626", "authors": [{"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebb3", "name": "Weikai Huang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebb4", "name": "Jieyu Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebb5", "name": "Sijun Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebb6", "name": "Taoyang Jia", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebb7", "name": "Jiafei Duan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebb8", "name": "Yunqian Cheng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebb9", "name": "Jaemin Cho", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebba", "name": "Mattew Wallingford", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebbb", "name": "Rustin Soraki", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebbc", "name": "Chris Dongjoo Kim", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebbd", "name": "Donovan Clay", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebbe", "name": "Taira Anderson", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebbf", "name": "Winson Han", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebc0", "name": "Ali Farhadi", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebc1", "name": "Bharath Hariharan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebc2", "name": "Zhongzheng Ren", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebc3", "name": "Ranjay Krishna", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/65cb0dcc4913057ac82a7a31/Onf0nOlpPSatpYaymwMfL.mp4", "https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/65cb0dcc4913057ac82a7a31/7SFbSWR7S6Y3s-TEjWTRk.mp4", "https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/65cb0dcc4913057ac82a7a31/TDAZbcNevNWEDH-RNEfwG.mp4", "https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/65cb0dcc4913057ac82a7a31/Y1X8199ofaaxXgB9JbRKQ.mp4"], "publishedAt": "2026-04-09T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-13T00:47:44.980Z", "title": "WildDet3D: Scaling Promptable 3D Detection in the Wild", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "65cb0dcc4913057ac82a7a31", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/034f39dc2a5af0d42015c013aad44490.svg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "Weikai Huang", "user": "weikaih", "type": "user", "name": "weikaih"}, "summary": "Understanding objects in 3D from a single image is a cornerstone of spatial intelligence. A key step toward this goal is monocular 3D object detection--recovering the extent, location, and orientation of objects from an input RGB image. To be practical in the open world, such a detector must generalize beyond closed-set categories, support diverse prompt modalities, and leverage geometric cues when available. Progress is hampered by two bottlenecks: existing methods are designed for a single prompt type and lack a mechanism to incorporate additional geometric cues, and current 3D datasets cover only narrow categories in controlled environments, limiting open-world transfer. In this work we address both gaps. First, we introduce WildDet3D, a unified geometry-aware architecture that natively accepts text, point, and box prompts and can incorporate auxiliary depth signals at inference time. Second, we present WildDet3D-Data, the largest open 3D detection dataset to date, constructed by generating candidate 3D boxes from existing 2D annotations and retaining only human-verified ones, yielding over 1M images across 13.5K categories in diverse real-world scenes. WildDet3D establishes a new state-of-the-art across multiple benchmarks and settings. In the open-world setting, it achieves 22.6/24.8 AP3D on our newly introduced WildDet3D-Bench with text and box prompts. On Omni3D, it reaches 34.2/36.4 AP3D with text and box prompts, respectively. In zero-shot evaluation, it achieves 40.3/48.9 ODS on Argoverse 2 and ScanNet. Notably, incorporating depth cues at inference time yields substantial additional gains (+20.7 AP on average across settings).", "upvotes": 213, "discussionId": "69dc4e4b2b6b8dc66ffeebc4", "projectPage": "https://allenai.github.io/WildDet3D/", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/allenai/WildDet3D", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "A unified 3D object detection framework with a large-scale dataset enables open-world detection with multiple prompt types and geometric cue integration.", "ai_keywords": ["monocular 3D object detection", "geometry-aware architecture", "text prompts", "point prompts", "box prompts", "depth signals", "open-world transfer", "3D detection dataset", "3D object detection", "spatial intelligence"], "githubStars": 269, "organization": {"_id": "5e70f3648ce3c604d78fe132", "name": "allenai", "fullname": "Ai2", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/652db071b62cf1f8463221e2/CxxwFiaomTa1MCX_B7-pT.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u7406\u89e33D\u7269\u4f53\u7684\u5173\u952e\u662f\u4ece\u5355\u5f20\u56fe\u7247\u4e2d\u68c0\u6d4b\u7269\u4f53\u7684\u5f62\u72b6\u3001\u4f4d\u7f6e\u548c\u65b9\u5411\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u73b0\u6709\u65b9\u6cd5\u53ea\u652f\u6301\u5355\u4e00\u7684\u63d0\u793a\u7c7b\u578b\uff0c\u4e14\u65e0\u6cd5\u5f88\u597d\u5730\u5229\u7528\u51e0\u4f55\u4fe1\u606f\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86WildDet3D\uff0c\u4e00\u4e2a\u53ef\u4ee5\u540c\u65f6\u63a5\u53d7\u6587\u672c\u3001\u70b9\u548c\u6846\u63d0\u793a\u7684\u7edf\u4e00\u67b6\u6784\uff0c\u5e76\u5728\u63a8\u65ad\u65f6\u7ed3\u5408\u8f85\u52a9\u6df1\u5ea6\u4fe1\u53f7\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u63a8\u51fa\u4e86WildDet3D-Data\uff0c\u8fd9\u662f\u8fc4\u4eca\u4e3a\u6b62\u6700\u5927\u7684\u5f00\u653e3D\u68c0\u6d4b\u6570\u636e\u96c6\uff0c\u5305\u542b\u8d85\u8fc7100\u4e07\u5f20\u56fe\u7247\u548c13500\u4e2a\u7c7b\u522b\u3002</li>\n    <li>WildDet3D\u5728\u591a\u9879\u57fa\u51c6\u6d4b\u8bd5\u4e2d\u53d6\u5f97\u4e86\u65b0\u7684\u6700\u4f73\u6210\u7ee9\uff0c\u5e76\u5728\u5f00\u653e\u4e16\u754c\u573a\u666f\u4e2d\u8868\u73b0\u4f18\u5f02\uff0c\u5c24\u5176\u662f\u5728\u5229\u7528\u6df1\u5ea6\u4fe1\u606f\u65f6\uff0c\u6027\u80fd\u663e\u8457\u63d0\u5347\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>The study focuses on improving 3D object detection from a single image, which is important for understanding spatial information.</li>\n    <li>It introduces WildDet3D, a new system that can use different types of prompts (text, point, box) and can also use depth information when available.</li>\n    <li>The researchers created WildDet3D-Data, a large 3D detection dataset with over 1 million images across 13,500 categories, aimed at real-world applications.</li>\n    <li>WildDet3D achieves top performance in multiple tests, including a new benchmark, with significant improvements when including depth information.</li>\n    <li>In zero-shot tests, WildDet3D performs well on existing datasets, demonstrating its capability to generalize beyond known categories.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-08T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "WildDet3D: Scaling Promptable 3D Detection in the Wild", "summary": "Understanding objects in 3D from a single image is a cornerstone of spatial intelligence. A key step toward this goal is monocular 3D object detection--recovering the extent, location, and orientation of objects from an input RGB image. To be practical in the open world, such a detector must generalize beyond closed-set categories, support diverse prompt modalities, and leverage geometric cues when available. Progress is hampered by two bottlenecks: existing methods are designed for a single prompt type and lack a mechanism to incorporate additional geometric cues, and current 3D datasets cover only narrow categories in controlled environments, limiting open-world transfer. In this work we address both gaps. First, we introduce WildDet3D, a unified geometry-aware architecture that natively accepts text, point, and box prompts and can incorporate auxiliary depth signals at inference time. Second, we present WildDet3D-Data, the largest open 3D detection dataset to date, constructed by generating candidate 3D boxes from existing 2D annotations and retaining only human-verified ones, yielding over 1M images across 13.5K categories in diverse real-world scenes. WildDet3D establishes a new state-of-the-art across multiple benchmarks and settings. In the open-world setting, it achieves 22.6/24.8 AP3D on our newly introduced WildDet3D-Bench with text and box prompts. On Omni3D, it reaches 34.2/36.4 AP3D with text and box prompts, respectively. In zero-shot evaluation, it achieves 40.3/48.9 ODS on Argoverse 2 and ScanNet. Notably, incorporating depth cues at inference time yields substantial additional gains (+20.7 AP on average across settings).", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/65cb0dcc4913057ac82a7a31/Onf0nOlpPSatpYaymwMfL.mp4", "https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/65cb0dcc4913057ac82a7a31/7SFbSWR7S6Y3s-TEjWTRk.mp4", "https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/65cb0dcc4913057ac82a7a31/TDAZbcNevNWEDH-RNEfwG.mp4", "https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/65cb0dcc4913057ac82a7a31/Y1X8199ofaaxXgB9JbRKQ.mp4"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.08626.png", "numComments": 3, "submittedBy": {"_id": "65cb0dcc4913057ac82a7a31", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/034f39dc2a5af0d42015c013aad44490.svg", "fullname": "Weikai Huang", "name": "weikaih", "type": "user", "isPro": true, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 7, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "5e70f3648ce3c604d78fe132", "name": "allenai", "fullname": "Ai2", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/652db071b62cf1f8463221e2/CxxwFiaomTa1MCX_B7-pT.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.20796", "authors": [{"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b407c", "name": "Inclusion AI", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b407d", "name": "Tiwei Bie", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b407e", "user": {"_id": "63898c562a897944ea5f07a2", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/63898c562a897944ea5f07a2/oG1ia44ICpAk1tReIaX0G.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Haoxing chen", "user": "HaoxingChen", "type": "user", "name": "HaoxingChen"}, "name": "Haoxing Chen", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-23T07:49:48.104Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b407f", "name": "Tieyuan Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4080", "name": "Zhenglin Cheng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4081", "name": "Long Cui", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4082", "name": "Kai Gan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4083", "name": "Zhicheng Huang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4084", "name": "Zhenzhong Lan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4085", "name": "Haoquan Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4086", "name": "Jianguo Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4087", "name": "Tao Lin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4088", "user": {"_id": "66bb136002fd8eb58bc84ffb", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/122cb8f59c502392768099b3c2afe043.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "qinqi", "user": "Dakerqi", "type": "user", "name": "Dakerqi"}, "name": "Qi Qin", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-23T07:49:44.838Z", "hidden": true}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b4089", "name": "Hongjun Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b408a", "name": "Xiaomei Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b408b", "name": "Haoyuan Wu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b408c", "name": "Yi Xin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b408d", "name": "Junbo Zhao", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-22T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-23T00:36:39.828Z", "title": "LLaDA2.0-Uni: Unifying Multimodal Understanding and Generation with Diffusion Large Language Model", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "taesiri", "user": "taesiri", "type": "user", "name": "taesiri"}, "summary": "We present LLaDA2.0-Uni, a unified discrete diffusion large language model (dLLM) that supports multimodal understanding and generation within a natively integrated framework. Its architecture combines a fully semantic discrete tokenizer, a MoE-based dLLM backbone, and a diffusion decoder. By discretizing continuous visual inputs via SigLIP-VQ, the model enables block-level masked diffusion for both text and vision inputs within the backbone, while the decoder reconstructs visual tokens into high-fidelity images. Inference efficiency is enhanced beyond parallel decoding through prefix-aware optimizations in the backbone and few-step distillation in the decoder. Supported by carefully curated large-scale data and a tailored multi-stage training pipeline, LLaDA2.0-Uni matches specialized VLMs in multimodal understanding while delivering strong performance in image generation and editing. Its native support for interleaved generation and reasoning establishes a promising and scalable paradigm for next-generation unified foundation models. Codes and models are available at https://github.com/inclusionAI/LLaDA2.0-Uni.", "upvotes": 208, "discussionId": "69e97eabd49e77f7389b408e", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/inclusionAI/LLaDA2.0-Uni", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "LLaDA2.0-Uni is a unified discrete diffusion language model that integrates multimodal understanding and generation through a semantic discrete tokenizer, MoE-based backbone, and diffusion decoder, achieving performance comparable to specialized vision-language models while enabling efficient inference and high-fidelity image generation.", "ai_keywords": ["discrete diffusion", "large language model", "multimodal understanding", "multimodal generation", "semantic discrete tokenizer", "MoE-based backbone", "diffusion decoder", "SigLIP-VQ", "block-level masked diffusion", "parallel decoding", "prefix-aware optimizations", "few-step distillation", "large-scale data", "multi-stage training pipeline", "interleaved generation", "reasoning"], "githubStars": 98, "organization": {"_id": "67aea5c8f086ab0f70ed97c9", "name": "inclusionAI", "fullname": "inclusionAI", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/662e1f9da266499277937d33/fyKuazRifqiaIO34xrhhm.jpeg"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u4ecb\u7ecd\u4e86LLaDA2.0-Uni\uff0c\u8fd9\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u7edf\u4e00\u7684\u79bb\u6563\u6269\u6563\u5927\u8bed\u8a00\u6a21\u578b\uff0c\u652f\u6301\u591a\u6a21\u6001\u7406\u89e3\u548c\u751f\u6210\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8be5\u6a21\u578b\u7ed3\u5408\u4e86\u5b8c\u5168\u8bed\u4e49\u7684\u79bb\u6563\u6807\u8bb0\u5668\u3001\u57fa\u4e8eMoE\u7684dLLM\u9aa8\u5e72\u548c\u6269\u6563\u89e3\u7801\u5668\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u901a\u8fc7SigLIP-VQ\u5bf9\u8fde\u7eed\u89c6\u89c9\u8f93\u5165\u8fdb\u884c\u79bb\u6563\u5316\uff0c\u6a21\u578b\u5b9e\u73b0\u4e86\u6587\u672c\u548c\u89c6\u89c9\u8f93\u5165\u7684\u5757\u7ea7\u63a9\u853d\u6269\u6563\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6a21\u578b\u5728\u63a8\u7406\u6548\u7387\u4e0a\u8fdb\u884c\u4e86\u4f18\u5316\uff0c\u80fd\u591f\u5feb\u901f\u751f\u6210\u9ad8\u8d28\u91cf\u7684\u56fe\u50cf\u3002</li>\n    <li>LLaDA2.0-Uni\u5728\u591a\u6a21\u6001\u7406\u89e3\u548c\u56fe\u50cf\u751f\u6210\u65b9\u9762\u8868\u73b0\u51fa\u8272\uff0c\u9002\u5408\u4e0b\u4e00\u4ee3\u7edf\u4e00\u57fa\u7840\u6a21\u578b\u7684\u5f00\u53d1\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>LLaDA2.0-Uni is a new model that can understand and create both text and images together.</li>\n    <li>It uses a special method to turn visual information into a format the model can work with, allowing it to handle both text and images effectively.</li>\n    <li>The model is designed to work efficiently, making it faster to generate outputs compared to other models.</li>\n    <li>LLaDA2.0-Uni performs well in understanding and generating images, similar to specialized models made just for visual tasks.</li>\n    <li>You can find the codes and models for LLaDA2.0-Uni online at GitHub.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-21T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "LLaDA2.0-Uni: Unifying Multimodal Understanding and Generation with Diffusion Large Language Model", "summary": "We present LLaDA2.0-Uni, a unified discrete diffusion large language model (dLLM) that supports multimodal understanding and generation within a natively integrated framework. Its architecture combines a fully semantic discrete tokenizer, a MoE-based dLLM backbone, and a diffusion decoder. By discretizing continuous visual inputs via SigLIP-VQ, the model enables block-level masked diffusion for both text and vision inputs within the backbone, while the decoder reconstructs visual tokens into high-fidelity images. Inference efficiency is enhanced beyond parallel decoding through prefix-aware optimizations in the backbone and few-step distillation in the decoder. Supported by carefully curated large-scale data and a tailored multi-stage training pipeline, LLaDA2.0-Uni matches specialized VLMs in multimodal understanding while delivering strong performance in image generation and editing. Its native support for interleaved generation and reasoning establishes a promising and scalable paradigm for next-generation unified foundation models. Codes and models are available at https://github.com/inclusionAI/LLaDA2.0-Uni.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.20796.png", "numComments": 1, "submittedBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "fullname": "taesiri", "name": "taesiri", "type": "user", "isPro": true, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 280, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "67aea5c8f086ab0f70ed97c9", "name": "inclusionAI", "fullname": "inclusionAI", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/662e1f9da266499277937d33/fyKuazRifqiaIO34xrhhm.jpeg"}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.05015", "authors": [{"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8078", "user": {"_id": "653b268cd1041ca9188954da", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/653b268cd1041ca9188954da/5Qy0fyQdRCIUUAzV6fg1k.png", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Chaoyou Fu", "user": "BradyFU", "type": "user", "name": "BradyFU"}, "name": "Chaoyou Fu", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-08T08:05:21.473Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8079", "name": "Haozhi Yuan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae807a", "user": {"_id": "652965773a416e1f2173443b", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/652965773a416e1f2173443b/y9MB8YgHzbwCXAc4EI9T3.jpeg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "Yuhao Dong", "user": "THUdyh", "type": "user", "name": "THUdyh"}, "name": "Yuhao Dong", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-08T08:05:27.685Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae807b", "user": {"_id": "623d8ca4c29adf5ef6175615", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/623d8ca4c29adf5ef6175615/q7lHao7UPwU1u7YLSP56m.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Yi-Fan Zhang", "user": "yifanzhang114", "type": "user", "name": "yifanzhang114"}, "name": "Yi-Fan Zhang", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-08T08:57:19.701Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae807c", "user": {"_id": "6483143902f98c3f05aff915", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6483143902f98c3f05aff915/ZhWFFgrlRsQf4MXiInh5p.jpeg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "\u6c88\u4e91\u822a Yunhang Shen", "user": "shenyunhang", "type": "user", "name": "shenyunhang"}, "name": "Yunhang Shen", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-08T08:05:24.695Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae807d", "name": "Xiaoxing Hu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae807e", "name": "Xueying Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae807f", "name": "Jinsen Su", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8080", "name": "Chengwu Long", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8081", "name": "Xiaoyao Xie", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8082", "name": "Yongkang Xie", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8083", "name": "Xiawu Zheng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8084", "user": {"_id": "648e77184cae4f6921dbb382", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/648e77184cae4f6921dbb382/zAAJRvOStC0wZplqVWrk_.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Xue Yang", "user": "yangxue", "type": "user", "name": "yangxue"}, "name": "Xue Yang", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-08T08:57:22.259Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8085", "user": {"_id": "641c1a85999935676ec7ead4", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/738a4e43bb3ddd4de287acfa26095b3d.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "caohaoyu", "user": "rechy", "type": "user", "name": "rechy"}, "name": "Haoyu Cao", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-08T11:40:48.723Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8086", "name": "Yunsheng Wu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8087", "name": "Ziwei Liu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8088", "user": {"_id": "647401e50da364bd0d002f2a", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/no-auth/vPuPn7EV092mLBOM2YZXd.png", "isPro": false, "fullname": "XING SUN", "user": "tedsun", "type": "user", "name": "tedsun"}, "name": "Xing Sun", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-08T08:05:19.307Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae8089", "name": "Caifeng Shan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae808a", "name": "Ran He", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-06T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-08T00:35:55.282Z", "title": "Video-MME-v2: Towards the Next Stage in Benchmarks for Comprehensive Video Understanding", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "653b268cd1041ca9188954da", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/653b268cd1041ca9188954da/5Qy0fyQdRCIUUAzV6fg1k.png", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Chaoyou Fu", "user": "BradyFU", "type": "user", "name": "BradyFU"}, "summary": "With the rapid advancement of video understanding, existing benchmarks are becoming increasingly saturated, exposing a critical discrepancy between inflated leaderboard scores and real-world model capabilities. To address this widening gap, we introduce Video-MME-v2, a comprehensive benchmark designed to rigorously evaluate the robustness and faithfulness of video understanding. To systematically evaluate model capabilities, we design a progressive tri-level hierarchy that incrementally increases the complexity of video comprehension, ranging from multi-point visual information aggregation, to temporal dynamics modeling, and ultimately to complex multimodal reasoning. Besides, in contrast to conventional per-question accuracy, we propose a group-based non-linear evaluation strategy that enforces both consistency across related queries and coherence in multi-step reasoning. It penalizes fragmented or guess-based correctness and assigns credit only to answers supported by valid reasoning. To guarantee data quality, Video-MME-v2 is constructed through a rigorously controlled human annotation pipeline, involving 12 annotators and 50 independent reviewers. Backed by 3,300 human-hours and up to 5 rounds of quality assurance, Video-MME-v2 aims to serve as one of the most authoritative video benchmarks. Extensive experiments reveal a substantial gap between current best model Gemini-3-Pro and human experts, and uncover a clear hierarchical bottleneck where errors in visual information aggregation and temporal modeling propagate to limit high-level reasoning. We further find that thinking-based reasoning is highly dependent on textual cues, improving performance with subtitles but sometimes degrading it in purely visual settings. By exposing these limitations, Video-MME-v2 establishes a demanding new testbed for the development of next-generation video MLLMs.", "upvotes": 197, "discussionId": "69d5aff6b9b236b710ae808b", "projectPage": "https://video-mme-v2.netlify.app/", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/MME-Benchmarks/Video-MME-v2", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "Video-MME-v2 presents a comprehensive benchmark for evaluating video understanding models through a progressive hierarchy and group-based evaluation to assess robustness and faithfulness.", "ai_keywords": ["video understanding", "video MLLMs", "progressive tri-level hierarchy", "group-based non-linear evaluation", "human annotation pipeline", "multimodal reasoning", "visual information aggregation", "temporal dynamics modeling", "high-level reasoning", "hierarchical bottleneck", "thinking-based reasoning", "textual cues", "subtitles"], "githubStars": 279, "organization": {"_id": "69d37329f8abf3b5dfcab8fb", "name": "MME-Benchmarks", "fullname": "MME-Benchmarks", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/653b268cd1041ca9188954da/7c7leKgwQ0ZOzyRNblFwP.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u968f\u7740\u89c6\u9891\u7406\u89e3\u6280\u672f\u7684\u5feb\u901f\u53d1\u5c55\uff0c\u73b0\u6709\u57fa\u51c6\u6d4b\u8bd5\u9010\u6e10\u9971\u548c\uff0c\u5bfc\u81f4\u6392\u884c\u699c\u5206\u6570\u4e0e\u5b9e\u9645\u6a21\u578b\u80fd\u529b\u4e4b\u95f4\u5b58\u5728\u5dee\u8ddd\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u63a8\u51fa\u4e86Video-MME-v2\u57fa\u51c6\uff0c\u4ee5\u5168\u9762\u8bc4\u4f30\u89c6\u9891\u7406\u89e3\u7684\u7a33\u5065\u6027\u548c\u771f\u5b9e\u6027\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u8be5\u57fa\u51c6\u91c7\u7528\u9010\u7ea7\u590d\u6742\u6027\u8bc4\u4f30\uff0c\u4ece\u591a\u70b9\u89c6\u89c9\u4fe1\u606f\u805a\u5408\u5230\u65f6\u95f4\u52a8\u6001\u5efa\u6a21\uff0c\u518d\u5230\u590d\u6742\u7684\u591a\u6a21\u6001\u63a8\u7406\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86\u4e00\u79cd\u57fa\u4e8e\u7ec4\u7684\u975e\u7ebf\u6027\u8bc4\u4f30\u7b56\u7565\uff0c\u5f3a\u8c03\u76f8\u5173\u67e5\u8be2\u4e4b\u95f4\u7684\u4e00\u81f4\u6027\u548c\u591a\u6b65\u9aa4\u63a8\u7406\u7684\u8fde\u8d2f\u6027\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u901a\u8fc7\u4e25\u683c\u7684\u4eba\u7c7b\u6ce8\u91ca\u6d41\u7a0b\u6784\u5efa\uff0cVideo-MME-v2\u65e8\u5728\u6210\u4e3a\u6743\u5a01\u7684\u89c6\u9891\u57fa\u51c6\uff0c\u5e76\u63ed\u793a\u73b0\u6709\u6700\u4f73\u6a21\u578b\u4e0e\u4eba\u7c7b\u4e13\u5bb6\u4e4b\u95f4\u7684\u663e\u8457\u5dee\u8ddd\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Video-MME-v2 is a new benchmark for assessing video understanding, aiming to improve the evaluation of model capabilities.</li>\n    <li>The benchmark uses a three-level system that increases in complexity, from basic visual info to advanced reasoning.</li>\n    <li>It introduces a group-based evaluation method that checks for consistent and logical answers, rather than just correct ones.</li>\n    <li>Video-MME-v2 is built with high-quality data, involving many human annotators and extensive quality checks.</li>\n    <li>Experiments show that current top models still fall short compared to human experts, especially in understanding visual and temporal elements.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-05T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "Video-MME-v2: Towards the Next Stage in Benchmarks for Comprehensive Video Understanding", "summary": "With the rapid advancement of video understanding, existing benchmarks are becoming increasingly saturated, exposing a critical discrepancy between inflated leaderboard scores and real-world model capabilities. To address this widening gap, we introduce Video-MME-v2, a comprehensive benchmark designed to rigorously evaluate the robustness and faithfulness of video understanding. To systematically evaluate model capabilities, we design a progressive tri-level hierarchy that incrementally increases the complexity of video comprehension, ranging from multi-point visual information aggregation, to temporal dynamics modeling, and ultimately to complex multimodal reasoning. Besides, in contrast to conventional per-question accuracy, we propose a group-based non-linear evaluation strategy that enforces both consistency across related queries and coherence in multi-step reasoning. It penalizes fragmented or guess-based correctness and assigns credit only to answers supported by valid reasoning. To guarantee data quality, Video-MME-v2 is constructed through a rigorously controlled human annotation pipeline, involving 12 annotators and 50 independent reviewers. Backed by 3,300 human-hours and up to 5 rounds of quality assurance, Video-MME-v2 aims to serve as one of the most authoritative video benchmarks. Extensive experiments reveal a substantial gap between current best model Gemini-3-Pro and human experts, and uncover a clear hierarchical bottleneck where errors in visual information aggregation and temporal modeling propagate to limit high-level reasoning. We further find that thinking-based reasoning is highly dependent on textual cues, improving performance with subtitles but sometimes degrading it in purely visual settings. By exposing these limitations, Video-MME-v2 establishes a demanding new testbed for the development of next-generation video MLLMs.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.05015.png", "numComments": 6, "submittedBy": {"_id": "653b268cd1041ca9188954da", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/653b268cd1041ca9188954da/5Qy0fyQdRCIUUAzV6fg1k.png", "fullname": "Chaoyou Fu", "name": "BradyFU", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 4, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "69d37329f8abf3b5dfcab8fb", "name": "MME-Benchmarks", "fullname": "MME-Benchmarks", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/653b268cd1041ca9188954da/7c7leKgwQ0ZOzyRNblFwP.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": true}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.06628", "authors": [{"_id": "69d87f8679548974da94661d", "name": "Qihan Ren", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d87f8679548974da94661e", "name": "Peng Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d87f8679548974da94661f", "name": "Ruikun Cai", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d87f8679548974da946620", "name": "Shuai Shao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d87f8679548974da946621", "name": "Dadi Guo", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d87f8679548974da946622", "name": "Yuejin Xie", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d87f8679548974da946623", "name": "Yafu Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d87f8679548974da946624", "name": "Quanshi Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d87f8679548974da946625", "name": "Xia Hu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d87f8679548974da946626", "name": "Jing Shao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d87f8679548974da946627", "name": "Dongrui Liu", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-08T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-10T03:14:36.774Z", "title": "Rethinking Generalization in Reasoning SFT: A Conditional Analysis on Optimization, Data, and Model Capability", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "66e2624a436a1798365e4581", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/6c605807d34faa8fb505e135a4b47776.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Qihan Ren", "user": "jasonrqh", "type": "user", "name": "jasonrqh"}, "summary": "A prevailing narrative in LLM post-training holds that supervised finetuning (SFT) memorizes while reinforcement learning (RL) generalizes. We revisit this claim for reasoning SFT with long chain-of-thought (CoT) supervision and find that cross-domain generalization is not absent but conditional, jointly shaped by optimization dynamics, training data, and base-model capability. Some reported failures are under-optimization artifacts: cross-domain performance first degrades before recovering and improving with extended training (a dip-and-recovery pattern), so shorttraining checkpoints can underestimate generalization. Data quality and structure both matter: low-quality solutions broadly hurt generalization,while verified long-CoT traces yield consistent cross-domain gains. Model capability is essential: stronger models internalize transferable procedural patterns (e.g., backtracking) even from a toy arithmetic game, while weaker ones imitate surface verbosity. This generalization is asymmetric, however: reasoning improves while safety degrades, reframing the question from whether reasoning SFT generalizes to under what conditions and at what cost.", "upvotes": 152, "discussionId": "69d87f8679548974da946628", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/Nebularaid2000/rethink_sft_generalization", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "Supervised finetuning and reinforcement learning exhibit conditional cross-domain generalization in reasoning tasks, influenced by optimization dynamics, data quality, and model capability, with asymmetric outcomes between reasoning improvement and safety degradation.", "ai_keywords": ["supervised finetuning", "reinforcement learning", "cross-domain generalization", "optimization dynamics", "long chain-of-thought", "training data", "base-model capability", "dip-and-recovery pattern", "data quality", "model capability", "reasoning tasks", "safety degradation"], "githubStars": 63, "organization": {"_id": "68f716f832b31e42cbc2be7f", "name": "AI45Research", "fullname": "AI45Research", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/68f6ffaa04d1019724af41fc/EVBafPHXvChszTM5tJcc9.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u5728\u5927\u8bed\u8a00\u6a21\u578b\u7684\u540e\u671f\u8bad\u7ec3\u4e2d\uff0c\u76d1\u7763\u5fae\u8c03\uff08SFT\uff09\u548c\u5f3a\u5316\u5b66\u4e60\uff08RL\uff09\u6709\u4e0d\u540c\u7684\u6548\u679c\uff0c\u524d\u8005\u5bb9\u6613\u8bb0\u5fc6\uff0c\u540e\u8005\u66f4\u5177\u6cdb\u5316\u80fd\u529b\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5bf9\u957f\u94fe\u601d\u7ef4\uff08CoT\uff09\u76d1\u7763\u7684SFT\u8fdb\u884c\u5206\u6790\u53d1\u73b0\uff0c\u8de8\u9886\u57df\u7684\u6cdb\u5316\u4e0d\u662f\u4e0d\u5b58\u5728\uff0c\u800c\u662f\u6709\u6761\u4ef6\u7684\uff0c\u53d7\u4f18\u5316\u52a8\u6001\u3001\u8bad\u7ec3\u6570\u636e\u548c\u57fa\u7840\u6a21\u578b\u80fd\u529b\u7684\u5171\u540c\u5f71\u54cd\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u4e00\u4e9b\u62a5\u544a\u7684\u5931\u8d25\u662f\u7531\u4e8e\u4f18\u5316\u4e0d\u8db3\u9020\u6210\u7684\uff0c\u8de8\u9886\u57df\u8868\u73b0\u5148\u4e0b\u964d\u540e\u6062\u590d\uff0c\u8fd9\u79cd\u73b0\u8c61\u79f0\u4e3a\u201c\u4e0b\u964d\u4e0e\u6062\u590d\u6a21\u5f0f\u201d\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6570\u636e\u7684\u8d28\u91cf\u548c\u7ed3\u6784\u5f88\u91cd\u8981\uff0c\u4f4e\u8d28\u91cf\u7684\u89e3\u51b3\u65b9\u6848\u4f1a\u5e7f\u6cdb\u5f71\u54cd\u6cdb\u5316\uff0c\u800c\u7ecf\u8fc7\u9a8c\u8bc1\u7684\u957f\u94fe\u601d\u7ef4\u8f68\u8ff9\u80fd\u5e26\u6765\u4e00\u81f4\u7684\u8de8\u9886\u57df\u63d0\u5347\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6a21\u578b\u80fd\u529b\u81f3\u5173\u91cd\u8981\uff0c\u5f3a\u5927\u7684\u6a21\u578b\u80fd\u591f\u5185\u5316\u53ef\u8f6c\u79fb\u7684\u7a0b\u5e8f\u6a21\u5f0f\uff0c\u800c\u8f83\u5f31\u7684\u6a21\u578b\u5219\u53ea\u80fd\u6a21\u4eff\u8868\u9762\u7684\u590d\u6742\u6027\u3002\u6cdb\u5316\u662f\u975e\u5bf9\u79f0\u7684\uff1a\u63a8\u7406\u80fd\u529b\u63d0\u5347\u7684\u540c\u65f6\u5b89\u5168\u6027\u53ef\u80fd\u4e0b\u964d\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>There's a common belief that supervised finetuning (SFT) just memorizes information, while reinforcement learning (RL) helps models generalize better.</li>\n    <li>Our research shows that SFT with long chain-of-thought supervision can also generalize, but it depends on several factors like how the model is trained and its capabilities.</li>\n    <li>Some issues with performance are due to not training long enough; models may initially do worse but improve with more training.</li>\n    <li>The quality of training data is important; poor data leads to worse generalization, while high-quality long chain-of-thought examples help improve it.</li>\n    <li>Stronger models can learn useful patterns better than weaker ones, but while reasoning skills may improve, safety concerns can get worse.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-07T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "Rethinking Generalization in Reasoning SFT: A Conditional Analysis on Optimization, Data, and Model Capability", "summary": "A prevailing narrative in LLM post-training holds that supervised finetuning (SFT) memorizes while reinforcement learning (RL) generalizes. We revisit this claim for reasoning SFT with long chain-of-thought (CoT) supervision and find that cross-domain generalization is not absent but conditional, jointly shaped by optimization dynamics, training data, and base-model capability. Some reported failures are under-optimization artifacts: cross-domain performance first degrades before recovering and improving with extended training (a dip-and-recovery pattern), so shorttraining checkpoints can underestimate generalization. Data quality and structure both matter: low-quality solutions broadly hurt generalization,while verified long-CoT traces yield consistent cross-domain gains. Model capability is essential: stronger models internalize transferable procedural patterns (e.g., backtracking) even from a toy arithmetic game, while weaker ones imitate surface verbosity. This generalization is asymmetric, however: reasoning improves while safety degrades, reframing the question from whether reasoning SFT generalizes to under what conditions and at what cost.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.06628.png", "numComments": 3, "submittedBy": {"_id": "66e2624a436a1798365e4581", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/6c605807d34faa8fb505e135a4b47776.svg", "fullname": "Qihan Ren", "name": "jasonrqh", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 4, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "68f716f832b31e42cbc2be7f", "name": "AI45Research", "fullname": "AI45Research", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/68f6ffaa04d1019724af41fc/EVBafPHXvChszTM5tJcc9.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.04707", "authors": [{"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb17d", "name": "DataFlow Team", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb17e", "user": {"_id": "6671214c92412fd4640714eb", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/48fa84e7bc3bb92ad0192aa26b32de10.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "bohan zeng", "user": "zbhpku", "type": "user", "name": "zbhpku"}, "name": "Bohan Zeng", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-07T08:33:33.376Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb17f", "name": "Daili Hua", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb180", "user": {"_id": "6708920aeae29d1cd41a703b", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/922427a86523b0aa810412fd2d75f88e.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "kaixin zhu", "user": "czkk566", "type": "user", "name": "czkk566"}, "name": "Kaixin Zhu", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-07T08:33:40.660Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb181", "user": {"_id": "674e77fa59a127e4eacf5dba", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/674e77fa59a127e4eacf5dba/W7qr94Buvvaio8zhKrEha.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Yifan Dai", "user": "Moonwines", "type": "user", "name": "Moonwines"}, "name": "Yifan Dai", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-07T08:33:36.806Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb182", "name": "Bozhou Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb183", "user": {"_id": "65e71ef39cf349af2940b317", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/fc1cd8d3510946fc947d67b16b51834b.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Yuran Wang", "user": "Ryann829", "type": "user", "name": "Ryann829"}, "name": "Yuran Wang", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-07T08:33:28.962Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb184", "name": "Chengzhuo Tong", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb185", "name": "Yifan Yang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb186", "user": {"_id": "662db438137b72821671db2f", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/noauth/hLMBYuvyF6sfkS0sSrDt-.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Mingkun Chang", "user": "D4isyC", "type": "user", "name": "D4isyC"}, "name": "Mingkun Chang", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-07T08:33:53.660Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb187", "name": "Jianbin Zhao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb188", "name": "Zhou Liu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb189", "name": "Hao Liang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb18a", "user": {"_id": "65099d08f37afbab0d3fb268", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/cef45b7c6b7c90bbef341a39a9bb51be.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Xiaochen Ma", "user": "Sunnyhaze", "type": "user", "name": "Sunnyhaze"}, "name": "Xiaochen Ma", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-07T08:33:49.869Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb18b", "name": "Ruichuan An", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb18c", "name": "Junbo Niu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb18d", "name": "Zimo Meng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb18e", "name": "Tianyi Bai", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb18f", "name": "Meiyi Qiang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb190", "name": "Huanyao Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb191", "name": "Zhiyou Xiao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb192", "name": "Tianyu Guo", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb193", "name": "Qinhan Yu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb194", "name": "Runhao Zhao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb195", "name": "Zhengpin Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb196", "name": "Xinyi Huang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb197", "name": "Yisheng Pan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb198", "name": "Yiwen Tang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb199", "user": {"_id": "673c7319d11b1c2e246ead9c", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/673c7319d11b1c2e246ead9c/IjFIO--N7Hm_BOEafhEQv.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Yang Shi", "user": "DogNeverSleep", "type": "user", "name": "DogNeverSleep"}, "name": "Yang Shi", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-07T08:33:46.567Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb19a", "name": "Yue Ding", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb19b", "name": "Xinlong Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb19c", "name": "Hongcheng Gao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb19d", "name": "Minglei Shi", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb19e", "name": "Jialong Wu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb19f", "name": "Zekun Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb1a0", "name": "Yuanxing Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb1a1", "name": "Xintao Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb1a2", "name": "Pengfei Wan", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb1a3", "name": "Yiren Song", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb1a4", "name": "Mike Zheng Shou", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d482da2c523d36431fb1a5", "name": "Wentao Zhang", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-06T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-07T02:36:53.761Z", "title": "OpenWorldLib: A Unified Codebase and Definition of Advanced World Models", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "taesiri", "user": "taesiri", "type": "user", "name": "taesiri"}, "summary": "World models have garnered significant attention as a promising research direction in artificial intelligence, yet a clear and unified definition remains lacking. In this paper, we introduce OpenWorldLib, a comprehensive and standardized inference framework for Advanced World Models. Drawing on the evolution of world models, we propose a clear definition: a world model is a model or framework centered on perception, equipped with interaction and long-term memory capabilities, for understanding and predicting the complex world. We further systematically categorize the essential capabilities of world models. Based on this definition, OpenWorldLib integrates models across different tasks within a unified framework, enabling efficient reuse and collaborative inference. Finally, we present additional reflections and analyses on potential future directions for world model research. Code link: https://github.com/OpenDCAI/OpenWorldLib", "upvotes": 149, "discussionId": "69d482da2c523d36431fb1a6", "projectPage": "https://wcny4qa9krto.feishu.cn/wiki/XtPJwf5XQipP7RkeVv0ckyWlnNd", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/OpenDCAI/OpenWorldLib", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "OpenWorldLib presents a standardized framework for advanced world models that integrate perception, interaction, and long-term memory capabilities for comprehensive world understanding and prediction.", "ai_keywords": ["world models", "perception", "interaction", "long-term memory", "unified framework", "collaborative inference"], "githubStars": 415, "organization": {"_id": "61dcd8e344f59573371b5cb6", "name": "PekingUniversity", "fullname": "Peking University", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/noauth/vavgrBsnkSejriUF4lXDE.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u4e16\u754c\u6a21\u578b\u5728\u4eba\u5de5\u667a\u80fd\u7814\u7a76\u4e2d\u53d7\u5230\u5e7f\u6cdb\u5173\u6ce8\uff0c\u4f46\u7f3a\u4e4f\u7edf\u4e00\u7684\u5b9a\u4e49\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u672c\u6587\u4ecb\u7ecd\u4e86OpenWorldLib\uff0c\u4e00\u4e2a\u5168\u9762\u548c\u6807\u51c6\u5316\u7684\u9ad8\u7ea7\u4e16\u754c\u6a21\u578b\u63a8\u7406\u6846\u67b6\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6211\u4eec\u5b9a\u4e49\u4e16\u754c\u6a21\u578b\u4e3a\u4e00\u4e2a\u4ee5\u611f\u77e5\u4e3a\u4e2d\u5fc3\u3001\u5177\u5907\u4ea4\u4e92\u548c\u957f\u671f\u8bb0\u5fc6\u80fd\u529b\u7684\u6a21\u578b\uff0c\u7528\u4e8e\u7406\u89e3\u548c\u9884\u6d4b\u590d\u6742\u4e16\u754c\u3002</li>\n    <li>OpenWorldLib\u6574\u5408\u4e86\u4e0d\u540c\u4efb\u52a1\u7684\u6a21\u578b\uff0c\u4fc3\u8fdb\u9ad8\u6548\u91cd\u7528\u548c\u534f\u540c\u63a8\u7406\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6587\u7ae0\u8fd8\u63a2\u8ba8\u4e86\u4e16\u754c\u6a21\u578b\u7814\u7a76\u7684\u672a\u6765\u65b9\u5411\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>World models are important in AI but lack a clear definition.</li>\n    <li>The paper introduces OpenWorldLib, a framework for advanced world models.</li>\n    <li>A world model is defined as a perception-based model with interaction and memory for understanding the world.</li>\n    <li>OpenWorldLib allows different models to work together efficiently.</li>\n    <li>The paper discusses future research directions for world models.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-05T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "OpenWorldLib: A Unified Codebase and Definition of Advanced World Models", "summary": "World models have garnered significant attention as a promising research direction in artificial intelligence, yet a clear and unified definition remains lacking. In this paper, we introduce OpenWorldLib, a comprehensive and standardized inference framework for Advanced World Models. Drawing on the evolution of world models, we propose a clear definition: a world model is a model or framework centered on perception, equipped with interaction and long-term memory capabilities, for understanding and predicting the complex world. We further systematically categorize the essential capabilities of world models. Based on this definition, OpenWorldLib integrates models across different tasks within a unified framework, enabling efficient reuse and collaborative inference. Finally, we present additional reflections and analyses on potential future directions for world model research. Code link: https://github.com/OpenDCAI/OpenWorldLib", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.04707.png", "numComments": 7, "submittedBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "fullname": "taesiri", "name": "taesiri", "type": "user", "isPro": true, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 262, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "61dcd8e344f59573371b5cb6", "name": "PekingUniversity", "fullname": "Peking University", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/noauth/vavgrBsnkSejriUF4lXDE.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": true}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.08377", "authors": [{"_id": "69d85acc79548974da9464a7", "name": "Ziyu Ma", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d85acc79548974da9464a8", "name": "Shidong Yang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d85acc79548974da9464a9", "name": "Yuxiang Ji", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d85acc79548974da9464aa", "name": "Xucong Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d85acc79548974da9464ab", "name": "Yong Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d85acc79548974da9464ac", "name": "Yiming Hu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d85acc79548974da9464ad", "name": "Tongwen Huang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d85acc79548974da9464ae", "name": "Xiangxiang Chu", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-04-09T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-10T00:35:04.063Z", "title": "SkillClaw: Let Skills Evolve Collectively with Agentic Evolver", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "isPro": true, "fullname": "taesiri", "user": "taesiri", "type": "user", "name": "taesiri"}, "summary": "Large language model (LLM) agents such as OpenClaw rely on reusable skills to perform complex tasks, yet these skills remain largely static after deployment. As a result, similar workflows, tool usage patterns, and failure modes are repeatedly rediscovered across users, preventing the system from improving with experience. While interactions from different users provide complementary signals about when a skill works or fails, existing systems lack a mechanism to convert such heterogeneous experiences into reliable skill updates. To address these issues, we present SkillClaw, a framework for collective skill evolution in multi-user agent ecosystems, which treats cross-user and over-time interactions as the primary signal for improving skills. SkillClaw continuously aggregates trajectories generated during use and processes them with an autonomous evolver, which identifies recurring behavioral patterns and translates them into updates to the skill set by refining existing skills or extending them with new capabilities. The resulting skills are maintained in a shared repository and synchronized across users, allowing improvements discovered in one context to propagate system-wide while requiring no additional effort from users. By integrating multi-user experience into ongoing skill updates, SkillClaw enables cross-user knowledge transfer and cumulative capability improvement, and experiments on WildClawBench show that limited interaction and feedback, it significantly improves the performance of Qwen3-Max in real-world agent scenarios.", "upvotes": 143, "discussionId": "69d85acd79548974da9464af", "ai_summary": "SkillClaw enables collective skill evolution in multi-user LLM agent systems by aggregating user interactions to autonomously update and improve reusable skills across the ecosystem.", "ai_keywords": ["large language model agents", "reusable skills", "multi-user agent ecosystems", "autonomous evolver", "skill set refinement", "shared repository", "cross-user knowledge transfer", "cumulative capability improvement"], "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>SkillClaw\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u6846\u67b6\uff0c\u65e8\u5728\u5e2e\u52a9\u591a\u7528\u6237\u667a\u80fd\u4f53\u7cfb\u7edf\u4e2d\u7684\u6280\u80fd\u4e0d\u65ad\u8fdb\u5316\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u73b0\u6709\u6280\u80fd\u5728\u90e8\u7f72\u540e\u57fa\u672c\u4fdd\u6301\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u5bfc\u81f4\u7528\u6237\u95f4\u7684\u7ecf\u9a8c\u65e0\u6cd5\u6709\u6548\u5171\u4eab\u548c\u66f4\u65b0\u3002</li>\n    <li>SkillClaw\u901a\u8fc7\u6536\u96c6\u7528\u6237\u7684\u4f7f\u7528\u8f68\u8ff9\uff0c\u5206\u6790\u884c\u4e3a\u6a21\u5f0f\uff0c\u81ea\u52a8\u66f4\u65b0\u6280\u80fd\u96c6\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6539\u8fdb\u540e\u7684\u6280\u80fd\u5b58\u50a8\u5728\u5171\u4eab\u5e93\u4e2d\uff0c\u7528\u6237\u65e0\u9700\u989d\u5916\u52aa\u529b\u5c31\u80fd\u5171\u4eab\u8fd9\u4e9b\u6539\u8fdb\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5b9e\u9a8c\u8868\u660e\uff0cSkillClaw\u663e\u8457\u63d0\u9ad8\u4e86Qwen3-Max\u5728\u771f\u5b9e\u573a\u666f\u4e2d\u7684\u8868\u73b0\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>Large language models like OpenClaw use reusable skills to complete complex tasks, but these skills don't improve after they're deployed.</li>\n    <li>Users often face similar problems and rediscover the same solutions, which stops the system from learning from experience.</li>\n    <li>SkillClaw is a new framework that allows skills to evolve by learning from interactions across different users over time.</li>\n    <li>It collects and analyzes user experiences to identify patterns, leading to updates in skills that benefit all users without extra effort.</li>\n    <li>Testing shows that SkillClaw can significantly enhance the performance of agents in real-world scenarios by facilitating knowledge sharing among users.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-08T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "SkillClaw: Let Skills Evolve Collectively with Agentic Evolver", "summary": "Large language model (LLM) agents such as OpenClaw rely on reusable skills to perform complex tasks, yet these skills remain largely static after deployment. As a result, similar workflows, tool usage patterns, and failure modes are repeatedly rediscovered across users, preventing the system from improving with experience. While interactions from different users provide complementary signals about when a skill works or fails, existing systems lack a mechanism to convert such heterogeneous experiences into reliable skill updates. To address these issues, we present SkillClaw, a framework for collective skill evolution in multi-user agent ecosystems, which treats cross-user and over-time interactions as the primary signal for improving skills. SkillClaw continuously aggregates trajectories generated during use and processes them with an autonomous evolver, which identifies recurring behavioral patterns and translates them into updates to the skill set by refining existing skills or extending them with new capabilities. The resulting skills are maintained in a shared repository and synchronized across users, allowing improvements discovered in one context to propagate system-wide while requiring no additional effort from users. By integrating multi-user experience into ongoing skill updates, SkillClaw enables cross-user knowledge transfer and cumulative capability improvement, and experiments on WildClawBench show that limited interaction and feedback, it significantly improves the performance of Qwen3-Max in real-world agent scenarios.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.08377.png", "numComments": 5, "submittedBy": {"_id": "6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/6039478ab3ecf716b1a5fd4d/_Thy4E7taiSYBLKxEKJbT.jpeg", "fullname": "taesiri", "name": "taesiri", "type": "user", "isPro": true, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 265, "isUserFollowing": false}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2603.26164", "authors": [{"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dbc", "user": {"_id": "6751a4fedf636b0140a9b873", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/d75f7f6cfbfb4d646e0e557d1cfacdce.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Hao Liang", "user": "lhpku20010120", "type": "user", "name": "lhpku20010120"}, "name": "Hao Liang", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-03T09:08:55.763Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dbd", "name": "Zhengyang Zhao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dbe", "name": "Meiyi Qiang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dbf", "name": "Mingrui Chen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dc0", "name": "Lu Ma", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dc1", "name": "Rongyi Yu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dc2", "name": "Hengyi Feng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dc3", "name": "Shixuan Sun", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dc4", "name": "Zimo Meng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dc5", "name": "Xiaochen Ma", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dc6", "name": "Xuanlin Yang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dc7", "name": "Qifeng Cai", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dc8", "name": "Ruichuan An", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dc9", "name": "Bohan Zeng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dca", "name": "Zhen Hao Wong", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dcb", "name": "Chengyu Shen", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dcc", "name": "Runming He", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dcd", "name": "Zhaoyang Han", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dce", "name": "Yaowei Zheng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dcf", "name": "Fangcheng Fu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dd0", "name": "Conghui He", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dd1", "name": "Bin Cui", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dd2", "name": "Zhiyu Li", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dd3", "name": "Weinan E", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dd4", "name": "Wentao Zhang", "hidden": false}], "publishedAt": "2026-03-27T08:28:02.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-03T01:15:54.414Z", "title": "DataFlex: A Unified Framework for Data-Centric Dynamic Training of Large Language Models", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "6671214c92412fd4640714eb", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/48fa84e7bc3bb92ad0192aa26b32de10.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "bohan zeng", "user": "zbhpku", "type": "user", "name": "zbhpku"}, "summary": "Data-centric training has emerged as a promising direction for improving large language models (LLMs) by optimizing not only model parameters but also the selection, composition, and weighting of training data during optimization. However, existing approaches to data selection, data mixture optimization, and data reweighting are often developed in isolated codebases with inconsistent interfaces, hindering reproducibility, fair comparison, and practical integration. In this paper, we present DataFlex, a unified data-centric dynamic training framework built upon LLaMA-Factory. DataFlex supports three major paradigms of dynamic data optimization: sample selection, domain mixture adjustment, and sample reweighting, while remaining fully compatible with the original training workflow. It provides extensible trainer abstractions and modular components, enabling a drop-in replacement for standard LLM training, and unifies key model-dependent operations such as embedding extraction, inference, and gradient computation, with support for large-scale settings including DeepSpeed ZeRO-3. We conduct comprehensive experiments across multiple data-centric methods. Dynamic data selection consistently outperforms static full-data training on MMLU across both Mistral-7B and Llama-3.2-3B. For data mixture, DoReMi and ODM improve both MMLU accuracy and corpus-level perplexity over default proportions when pretraining Qwen2.5-1.5B on SlimPajama at 6B and 30B token scales. DataFlex also achieves consistent runtime improvements over original implementations. These results demonstrate that DataFlex provides an effective, efficient, and reproducible infrastructure for data-centric dynamic training of LLMs.", "upvotes": 139, "discussionId": "69ccf51d1f6782218d973dd5", "projectPage": "https://opendcai.github.io/DataFlex-Doc/en/", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/OpenDCAI/DataFlex", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "DataFlex is a unified framework for dynamic data-centric training of large language models that supports sample selection, domain mixture adjustment, and sample reweighting while maintaining compatibility with standard training workflows and enabling efficient large-scale deployment.", "ai_keywords": ["data-centric training", "large language models", "sample selection", "domain mixture adjustment", "sample reweighting", "LLaMA-Factory", "extensible trainer abstractions", "modular components", "embedding extraction", "gradient computation", "DeepSpeed ZeRO-3", "MMLU", "perplexity", "Qwen2.5-1.5B", "SlimPajama"], "githubStars": 143, "organization": {"_id": "61dcd8e344f59573371b5cb6", "name": "PekingUniversity", "fullname": "Peking University", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/noauth/vavgrBsnkSejriUF4lXDE.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>\u6570\u636e\u4e2d\u5fc3\u5316\u8bad\u7ec3\u53ef\u4ee5\u63d0\u9ad8\u5927\u578b\u8bed\u8a00\u6a21\u578b\uff08LLMs\uff09\u7684\u6027\u80fd\uff0c\u4e0d\u4ec5\u4f18\u5316\u6a21\u578b\u53c2\u6570\uff0c\u8fd8\u4f18\u5316\u8bad\u7ec3\u6570\u636e\u7684\u9009\u62e9\u3001\u7ec4\u5408\u548c\u52a0\u6743\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u73b0\u6709\u7684\u6570\u636e\u9009\u62e9\u548c\u4f18\u5316\u65b9\u6cd5\u901a\u5e38\u5728\u4e0d\u540c\u7684\u4ee3\u7801\u5e93\u4e2d\u5f00\u53d1\uff0c\u5bfc\u81f4\u91cd\u590d\u6027\u5dee\u548c\u6bd4\u8f83\u56f0\u96be\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u672c\u6587\u63d0\u51fa\u4e86DataFlex\uff0c\u4e00\u4e2a\u7edf\u4e00\u7684\u6570\u636e\u4e2d\u5fc3\u5316\u52a8\u6001\u8bad\u7ec3\u6846\u67b6\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u539f\u6709\u7684\u8bad\u7ec3\u6d41\u7a0b\u3002</li>\n    <li>DataFlex\u652f\u6301\u52a8\u6001\u6570\u636e\u4f18\u5316\u7684\u4e09\u79cd\u4e3b\u8981\u6a21\u5f0f\uff1a\u6837\u672c\u9009\u62e9\u3001\u9886\u57df\u7ec4\u5408\u8c03\u6574\u548c\u6837\u672c\u91cd\u52a0\u6743\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5b9e\u9a8c\u8868\u660e\uff0cDataFlex\u5728\u591a\u4e2a\u6570\u636e\u4e2d\u5fc3\u5316\u65b9\u6cd5\u4e0a\u8868\u73b0\u4f18\u5f02\uff0c\u4e14\u8fd0\u884c\u6548\u7387\u9ad8\uff0c\u9002\u7528\u4e8e\u5927\u578b\u8bbe\u7f6e\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n  <li>DataFlex is a new framework designed to improve large language models (LLMs) by optimizing how training data is selected and used.</li>\n  <li>It allows for better data management through three key methods: choosing samples, adjusting data mixtures, and reweighting samples.</li>\n  <li>DataFlex works seamlessly with existing training processes and can easily replace standard training methods.</li>\n  <li>Experiments show that dynamic data selection improves performance compared to using all data at once, particularly on specific tasks.</li>\n  <li>The framework also enhances runtime efficiency compared to older methods, making it a strong choice for training LLMs.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-03-27T04:28:02.000Z", "title": "DataFlex: A Unified Framework for Data-Centric Dynamic Training of Large Language Models", "summary": "Data-centric training has emerged as a promising direction for improving large language models (LLMs) by optimizing not only model parameters but also the selection, composition, and weighting of training data during optimization. However, existing approaches to data selection, data mixture optimization, and data reweighting are often developed in isolated codebases with inconsistent interfaces, hindering reproducibility, fair comparison, and practical integration. In this paper, we present DataFlex, a unified data-centric dynamic training framework built upon LLaMA-Factory. DataFlex supports three major paradigms of dynamic data optimization: sample selection, domain mixture adjustment, and sample reweighting, while remaining fully compatible with the original training workflow. It provides extensible trainer abstractions and modular components, enabling a drop-in replacement for standard LLM training, and unifies key model-dependent operations such as embedding extraction, inference, and gradient computation, with support for large-scale settings including DeepSpeed ZeRO-3. We conduct comprehensive experiments across multiple data-centric methods. Dynamic data selection consistently outperforms static full-data training on MMLU across both Mistral-7B and Llama-3.2-3B. For data mixture, DoReMi and ODM improve both MMLU accuracy and corpus-level perplexity over default proportions when pretraining Qwen2.5-1.5B on SlimPajama at 6B and 30B token scales. DataFlex also achieves consistent runtime improvements over original implementations. These results demonstrate that DataFlex provides an effective, efficient, and reproducible infrastructure for data-centric dynamic training of LLMs.", "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2603.26164.png", "numComments": 2, "submittedBy": {"_id": "6671214c92412fd4640714eb", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/48fa84e7bc3bb92ad0192aa26b32de10.svg", "fullname": "bohan zeng", "name": "zbhpku", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 10, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "61dcd8e344f59573371b5cb6", "name": "PekingUniversity", "fullname": "Peking University", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/noauth/vavgrBsnkSejriUF4lXDE.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": false}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.07430", "authors": [{"_id": "69d858ac79548974da946469", "name": "Tencent Robotics X", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da94646a", "name": "HY Vision Team", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da94646c", "name": "Xumin Yu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da94646d", "user": {"_id": "64f001bfabd9fb1914398bd5", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/64f001bfabd9fb1914398bd5/9teH82hkBI4csIz_WQh5q.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "liuzuyan", "user": "Zuyan", "type": "user", "name": "Zuyan"}, "name": "Zuyan Liu", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-10T07:43:58.012Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da94646e", "user": {"_id": "660e422a6455d218e942a668", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/43ebd2b438da2003ad340a2ea174ad0b.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Ziyi Wang", "user": "ziyiwang", "type": "user", "name": "ziyiwang"}, "name": "Ziyi Wang", "status": "admin_assigned", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-10T07:51:00.470Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da94646f", "name": "He Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da946470", "user": {"_id": "63e4865354f51ea342d45d78", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/2e7eccc878751331ca8b282f53e38899.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Yongming Rao", "user": "raoyongming", "type": "user", "name": "raoyongming"}, "name": "Yongming Rao", "status": "admin_assigned", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-10T07:51:08.986Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da946471", "user": {"_id": "6505a02f9310ce8c400edc63", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/bbf781594fc8c812316711aa8e2797aa.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Fangfu Liu", "user": "Liuff23", "type": "user", "name": "Liuff23"}, "name": "Fangfu Liu", "status": "admin_assigned", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-10T07:51:32.933Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da946472", "name": "Yani Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da946473", "user": {"_id": "6522e4fbd89bc7773ddc4b58", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/3e9b158af52c5f738a3eae72dcbb3824.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Ruowen Zhao", "user": "zzzrw", "type": "user", "name": "zzzrw"}, "name": "Ruowen Zhao", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-10T07:43:53.994Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da946474", "name": "Oran Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da946475", "name": "Yves Liang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da946476", "name": "Haitao Lin", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da946477", "name": "Minghui Wang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da946478", "name": "Yubo Dong", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da946479", "name": "Kevin Cheng", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da94647a", "user": {"_id": "642149592cc2b3c39e7ef6c9", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/fed5d447375cd8c3b2bc9e096fe681de.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Bolin Ni", "user": "nbl97", "type": "user", "name": "nbl97"}, "name": "Bolin Ni", "status": "admin_assigned", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-10T07:51:56.263Z", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da94647b", "name": "Rui Huang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da94647c", "name": "Han Hu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da94647d", "name": "Zhengyou Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da94647e", "name": "Linus", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69d858ac79548974da94647f", "name": "Shunyu Yao", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/64f001bfabd9fb1914398bd5/74X-jSbVoJBK05QTEW2OB.mp4"], "publishedAt": "2026-04-08T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-10T00:30:39.896Z", "title": "HY-Embodied-0.5: Embodied Foundation Models for Real-World Agents", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "64f001bfabd9fb1914398bd5", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/64f001bfabd9fb1914398bd5/9teH82hkBI4csIz_WQh5q.jpeg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "liuzuyan", "user": "Zuyan", "type": "user", "name": "Zuyan"}, "summary": "We introduce HY-Embodied-0.5, a family of foundation models specifically designed for real-world embodied agents. To bridge the gap between general Vision-Language Models (VLMs) and the demands of embodied agents, our models are developed to enhance the core capabilities required by embodied intelligence: spatial and temporal visual perception, alongside advanced embodied reasoning for prediction, interaction, and planning. The HY-Embodied-0.5 suite comprises two primary variants: an efficient model with 2B activated parameters designed for edge deployment, and a powerful model with 32B activated parameters targeted for complex reasoning. To support the fine-grained visual perception essential for embodied tasks, we adopt a Mixture-of-Transformers (MoT) architecture to enable modality-specific computing. By incorporating latent tokens, this design effectively enhances the perceptual representation of the models. To improve reasoning capabilities, we introduce an iterative, self-evolving post-training paradigm. Furthermore, we employ on-policy distillation to transfer the advanced capabilities of the large model to the smaller variant, thereby maximizing the performance potential of the compact model. Extensive evaluations across 22 benchmarks, spanning visual perception, spatial reasoning, and embodied understanding, demonstrate the effectiveness of our approach. Our MoT-2B model outperforms similarly sized state-of-the-art models on 16 benchmarks, while the 32B variant achieves performance comparable to frontier models such as Gemini 3.0 Pro. In downstream robot control experiments, we leverage our robust VLM foundation to train an effective Vision-Language-Action (VLA) model, achieving compelling results in real-world physical evaluations. Code and models are open-sourced at https://github.com/Tencent-Hunyuan/HY-Embodied.", "upvotes": 126, "discussionId": "69d858ad79548974da946480", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/Tencent-Hunyuan/HY-Embodied", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "HY-Embodied-0.5 is a foundation model family for embodied agents featuring Mixture-of-Transformers architecture and iterative post-training for enhanced visual perception and reasoning capabilities.", "ai_keywords": ["Vision-Language Models", "embodied agents", "Mixture-of-Transformers", "latent tokens", "iterative self-evolving post-training", "on-policy distillation", "Vision-Language-Action models"], "githubStars": 223, "organization": {"_id": "6645f953c39288df638dbdd5", "name": "Tencent-Hunyuan", "fullname": "Tencent Hunyuan", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/62d22496c58f969c152bcefd/woKSjt2wXvBNKussyYPsa.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>HY-Embodied-0.5\u662f\u4e00\u79cd\u4e13\u4e3a\u771f\u5b9e\u4e16\u754c\u7684\u5177\u8eab\u667a\u80fd\u4f53\u8bbe\u8ba1\u7684\u57fa\u7840\u6a21\u578b\u5bb6\u65cf\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u6a21\u578b\u589e\u5f3a\u4e86\u5177\u8eab\u667a\u80fd\u6240\u9700\u7684\u7a7a\u95f4\u548c\u65f6\u95f4\u89c6\u89c9\u611f\u77e5\uff0c\u4ee5\u53ca\u590d\u6742\u63a8\u7406\u80fd\u529b\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5305\u542b\u4e24\u4e2a\u4e3b\u8981\u7248\u672c\uff1a\u4e00\u4e2a\u662f\u9002\u5408\u8fb9\u7f18\u90e8\u7f72\u7684\u9ad8\u6548\u6a21\u578b\uff082B\u53c2\u6570\uff09\uff0c\u53e6\u4e00\u4e2a\u662f\u7528\u4e8e\u590d\u6742\u63a8\u7406\u7684\u5f3a\u5927\u6a21\u578b\uff0832B\u53c2\u6570\uff09\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u91c7\u7528Mixture-of-Transformers\u67b6\u6784\u6765\u63d0\u5347\u89c6\u89c9\u611f\u77e5\uff0c\u4f7f\u7528\u81ea\u6211\u8fdb\u5316\u7684\u540e\u8bad\u7ec3\u65b9\u6cd5\u6539\u5584\u63a8\u7406\u80fd\u529b\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u7ecf\u8fc722\u4e2a\u57fa\u51c6\u6d4b\u8bd5\u7684\u8bc4\u4f30\uff0c\u6a21\u578b\u5728\u591a\u4e2a\u4efb\u52a1\u4e2d\u8868\u73b0\u4f18\u5f02\uff0c\u5e76\u5728\u673a\u5668\u4eba\u63a7\u5236\u5b9e\u9a8c\u4e2d\u53d6\u5f97\u4e86\u826f\u597d\u7ed3\u679c\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>HY-Embodied-0.5 is a new type of model designed for real-world robots and agents that need to understand and interact with their environment.</li>\n    <li>It includes two versions: a smaller model for basic tasks and a larger model for more complex reasoning, both using a special architecture for better visual perception.</li>\n    <li>The models improve reasoning skills through a new training method and can share knowledge from the larger model to the smaller one for better performance.</li>\n    <li>Tests show that the smaller model outperforms other similar models in many tasks, and the larger model competes well with top models in the field.</li>\n    <li>The team has also created a Vision-Language-Action model for robots that performs well in real-world tests, and they have shared their work publicly online.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-07T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "HY-Embodied-0.5: Embodied Foundation Models for Real-World Agents", "summary": "We introduce HY-Embodied-0.5, a family of foundation models specifically designed for real-world embodied agents. To bridge the gap between general Vision-Language Models (VLMs) and the demands of embodied agents, our models are developed to enhance the core capabilities required by embodied intelligence: spatial and temporal visual perception, alongside advanced embodied reasoning for prediction, interaction, and planning. The HY-Embodied-0.5 suite comprises two primary variants: an efficient model with 2B activated parameters designed for edge deployment, and a powerful model with 32B activated parameters targeted for complex reasoning. To support the fine-grained visual perception essential for embodied tasks, we adopt a Mixture-of-Transformers (MoT) architecture to enable modality-specific computing. By incorporating latent tokens, this design effectively enhances the perceptual representation of the models. To improve reasoning capabilities, we introduce an iterative, self-evolving post-training paradigm. Furthermore, we employ on-policy distillation to transfer the advanced capabilities of the large model to the smaller variant, thereby maximizing the performance potential of the compact model. Extensive evaluations across 22 benchmarks, spanning visual perception, spatial reasoning, and embodied understanding, demonstrate the effectiveness of our approach. Our MoT-2B model outperforms similarly sized state-of-the-art models on 16 benchmarks, while the 32B variant achieves performance comparable to frontier models such as Gemini 3.0 Pro. In downstream robot control experiments, we leverage our robust VLM foundation to train an effective Vision-Language-Action (VLA) model, achieving compelling results in real-world physical evaluations. Code and models are open-sourced at https://github.com/Tencent-Hunyuan/HY-Embodied.", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/64f001bfabd9fb1914398bd5/74X-jSbVoJBK05QTEW2OB.mp4"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.07430.png", "numComments": 3, "submittedBy": {"_id": "64f001bfabd9fb1914398bd5", "avatarUrl": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/64f001bfabd9fb1914398bd5/9teH82hkBI4csIz_WQh5q.jpeg", "fullname": "liuzuyan", "name": "Zuyan", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 3, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "6645f953c39288df638dbdd5", "name": "Tencent-Hunyuan", "fullname": "Tencent Hunyuan", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/62d22496c58f969c152bcefd/woKSjt2wXvBNKussyYPsa.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": true}, {"paper": {"id": "2604.11784", "authors": [{"_id": "69ddb76daea31e227c22c57d", "name": "Fei Tang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ddb76daea31e227c22c57e", "name": "Zhiqiong Lu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ddb76daea31e227c22c57f", "name": "Boxuan Zhang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ddb76daea31e227c22c580", "name": "Weiming Lu", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ddb76daea31e227c22c581", "name": "Jun Xiao", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ddb76daea31e227c22c582", "name": "Yueting Zhuang", "hidden": false}, {"_id": "69ddb76daea31e227c22c583", "user": {"_id": "5e1058e9fcf41d740b69966d", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/ce74839ba871f2b54313a670a233ba82.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Yongliang Shen", "user": "tricktreat", "type": "user", "name": "tricktreat"}, "name": "Yongliang Shen", "status": "claimed_verified", "statusLastChangedAt": "2026-04-14T08:15:11.282Z", "hidden": false}], "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/5e1058e9fcf41d740b69966d/3ieX6KXGLJBwWI1j5MWmK.mp4"], "publishedAt": "2026-04-13T00:00:00.000Z", "submittedOnDailyAt": "2026-04-15T07:31:57.645Z", "title": "ClawGUI: A Unified Framework for Training, Evaluating, and Deploying GUI Agents", "submittedOnDailyBy": {"_id": "5e1058e9fcf41d740b69966d", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/ce74839ba871f2b54313a670a233ba82.svg", "isPro": false, "fullname": "Yongliang Shen", "user": "tricktreat", "type": "user", "name": "tricktreat"}, "summary": "GUI agents drive applications through their visual interfaces instead of programmatic APIs, interacting with arbitrary software via taps, swipes, and keystrokes, reaching a long tail of applications that CLI-based agents cannot. Yet progress in this area is bottlenecked less by modeling capacity than by the absence of a coherent full-stack infrastructure: online RL training suffers from environment instability and closed pipelines, evaluation protocols drift silently across works, and trained agents rarely reach real users on real devices. We present ClawGUI, an open-source framework addressing these three gaps within a single harness. ClawGUI-RL provides the first open-source GUI agent RL infrastructure with validated support for both parallel virtual environments and real physical devices, integrating GiGPO with a Process Reward Model for dense step-level supervision. ClawGUI-Eval enforces a fully standardized evaluation pipeline across 6 benchmarks and 11+ models, achieving 95.8\\% reproduction against official baselines. ClawGUI-Agent brings trained agents to Android, HarmonyOS, and iOS through 12+ chat platforms with hybrid CLI-GUI control and persistent personalized memory. Trained end to end within this pipeline, ClawGUI-2B achieves 17.1\\% Success Rate on MobileWorld GUI-Only, outperforming the same-scale MAI-UI-2B baseline by 6.0\\%.", "upvotes": 121, "discussionId": "69ddb76daea31e227c22c584", "projectPage": "https://zju-real.github.io/ClawGUI-Page/", "githubRepo": "https://github.com/ZJU-REAL/ClawGUI", "githubRepoAddedBy": "user", "ai_summary": "ClawGUI presents an open-source framework that addresses key challenges in GUI agent development through unified reinforcement learning, standardized evaluation, and cross-platform deployment capabilities.", "ai_keywords": ["GUI agents", "reinforcement learning", "environment instability", "closed pipelines", "evaluation protocols", "real-world deployment", "mobile applications", "GUI-only benchmark", "success rate", "hybrid CLI-GUI control", "persistent memory"], "githubStars": 404, "organization": {"_id": "61bac2af530e5c78d7b99667", "name": "zju", "fullname": "Zhejiang University", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/5e1058e9fcf41d740b69966d/7G1xjlxwCdMEmKcxNR0n5.png"}, "summary_zh": "<ul>\n    <li>ClawGUI\u662f\u4e00\u4e2a\u5f00\u6e90\u6846\u67b6\uff0c\u65e8\u5728\u89e3\u51b3\u56fe\u5f62\u7528\u6237\u754c\u9762\uff08GUI\uff09\u4ee3\u7406\u5728\u8bad\u7ec3\u548c\u8bc4\u4f30\u4e2d\u7684\u4e00\u4e9b\u95ee\u9898\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u5b83\u63d0\u4f9b\u4e86\u652f\u6301\u5e76\u884c\u865a\u62df\u73af\u5883\u548c\u771f\u5b9e\u8bbe\u5907\u7684GUI\u4ee3\u7406\u5f3a\u5316\u5b66\u4e60\u57fa\u7840\u8bbe\u65bd\u3002</li>\n    <li>ClawGUI-Eval\u786e\u4fdd\u5728\u591a\u4e2a\u57fa\u51c6\u6d4b\u8bd5\u4e2d\u6709\u7edf\u4e00\u7684\u8bc4\u4f30\u6d41\u7a0b\uff0c\u590d\u73b0\u7387\u8fbe\u523095.8%\u3002</li>\n    <li>ClawGUI-Agent\u80fd\u591f\u5c06\u8bad\u7ec3\u597d\u7684\u4ee3\u7406\u5e94\u7528\u4e8eAndroid\u3001HarmonyOS\u548ciOS\u8bbe\u5907\uff0c\u5e76\u652f\u6301\u6df7\u5408\u63a7\u5236\u65b9\u5f0f\u3002</li>\n    <li>\u901a\u8fc7\u8fd9\u4e2a\u6846\u67b6\uff0cClawGUI-2B\u5728MobileWorld GUI-Only\u4e2d\u53d6\u5f97\u4e8617.1%\u7684\u6210\u529f\u7387\uff0c\u8d85\u8fc7\u4e86\u540c\u89c4\u6a21\u7684MAI-UI-2B\u57fa\u51c6\u3002</li>\n</ul>", "summary_simple": "<ul>\n    <li>GUI agents can control applications visually, using taps and swipes, unlike traditional command-line agents.</li>\n    <li>Current progress in developing these agents is limited due to instability and closed systems in online training, inconsistent evaluation methods, and difficulty reaching real users.</li>\n    <li>ClawGUI is an open-source framework that addresses these issues by providing a comprehensive solution for training and evaluating GUI agents.</li>\n    <li>ClawGUI-RL offers a structure for training agents in both virtual and real environments, using advanced techniques for supervision.</li>\n    <li>ClawGUI-Eval standardizes evaluations across multiple benchmarks, and ClawGUI-Agent allows trained agents to work on various mobile platforms, achieving notable success rates.</li>\n</ul>"}, "publishedAt": "2026-04-12T20:00:00.000Z", "title": "ClawGUI: A Unified Framework for Training, Evaluating, and Deploying GUI Agents", "summary": "GUI agents drive applications through their visual interfaces instead of programmatic APIs, interacting with arbitrary software via taps, swipes, and keystrokes, reaching a long tail of applications that CLI-based agents cannot. Yet progress in this area is bottlenecked less by modeling capacity than by the absence of a coherent full-stack infrastructure: online RL training suffers from environment instability and closed pipelines, evaluation protocols drift silently across works, and trained agents rarely reach real users on real devices. We present ClawGUI, an open-source framework addressing these three gaps within a single harness. ClawGUI-RL provides the first open-source GUI agent RL infrastructure with validated support for both parallel virtual environments and real physical devices, integrating GiGPO with a Process Reward Model for dense step-level supervision. ClawGUI-Eval enforces a fully standardized evaluation pipeline across 6 benchmarks and 11+ models, achieving 95.8\\% reproduction against official baselines. ClawGUI-Agent brings trained agents to Android, HarmonyOS, and iOS through 12+ chat platforms with hybrid CLI-GUI control and persistent personalized memory. Trained end to end within this pipeline, ClawGUI-2B achieves 17.1\\% Success Rate on MobileWorld GUI-Only, outperforming the same-scale MAI-UI-2B baseline by 6.0\\%.", "mediaUrls": ["https://cdn-uploads.huggingface.co/production/uploads/5e1058e9fcf41d740b69966d/3ieX6KXGLJBwWI1j5MWmK.mp4"], "thumbnail": "https://cdn-thumbnails.huggingface.co/social-thumbnails/papers/2604.11784.png", "numComments": 5, "submittedBy": {"_id": "5e1058e9fcf41d740b69966d", "avatarUrl": "/avatars/ce74839ba871f2b54313a670a233ba82.svg", "fullname": "Yongliang Shen", "name": "tricktreat", "type": "user", "isPro": false, "isHf": false, "isHfAdmin": false, "isMod": false, "followerCount": 38, "isUserFollowing": false}, "organization": {"_id": "61bac2af530e5c78d7b99667", "name": "zju", "fullname": "Zhejiang University", "avatar": "https://cdn-avatars.huggingface.co/v1/production/uploads/5e1058e9fcf41d740b69966d/7G1xjlxwCdMEmKcxNR0n5.png"}, "isAuthorParticipating": true}]
};
